title: christmas bars
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Spread in ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Spread frosting over bars while hot. Sprinkle with coconut.

title: fruit and cottage cheese salad(diabetic recipe)
directions: Fold together all ingredients.
Do not add water to gelatin! Chill for 1 to 2 hours before serving.
Change flavors by using another flavor of gelatin.
Omit mandarin orange slices.
You may fold in some of the fruit to match the jello flavor.

title: green salad
directions: Dissolve marshmallows in milk in double boiler and bring to boil.
Add jello and cream cheese and dissolve.
Add pineapple; stir all together.
Chill, but don't jell.
Add Cool Whip. Garnish with cherries and chopped nuts.

title: toffee squares
directions: Cream butter, then sugar and others except chocolate and nuts.
Spread smoothly, thinly, and evenly on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 15-20 minutes in 350° oven. Melt the chocolate bits by sprinkling over hot dough.
Spread chocolate with spatula.
It then becomes icing.
Sprinkle nuts over top. Cut into 2 inch squares while hot.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Cook instant rice in chicken broth and water by box instructions and set aside.
Saute bell pepper and onion in margarine, but leave crisp.
Combine cooked rice, peppers, onions and chicken soup in casserole dish.
Sprinkle top with shredded cheese; bake at 400° until cheese melts.

title: chocolate cherry magic cake
directions: Use a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread marshmallows on bottom of pan.
Prepare cake mix according to box directions.
Spread batter over marshmallows.
Sprinkle the dry jello powder over batter.
Spoon canned cherry pie filling over.
Drizzle water over, but do not stir.
Carefully place cake in a 350° oven.
Bake 75 to 80 minutes or until done (until toothpick comes out clean). Let cool at least 30 minutes in pan.

title: 5-cup salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Transfer to a serving bowl and refrigerate overnight.

title: yogurt-pineapple dip
directions: Beat cream cheese at medium speed of an electric mixer until light and fluffy.
Add yogurt, lemon juice, orange rind and coconut extract.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in pineapple.
Cover dip, and chill thoroughly.
Yields 3 1/2 cups.

title: sour cream chicken
directions: Lay chicken breast in casserole dish.
Place 2 slices of bacon on each breast.
Mix sour cream with cream of mushroom soup.
Pour over chicken.
Do not cover.
Bake at 300° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: lemon lime rainbow cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as box says, then pour into pan.
Bake at 350°.
While cake is in oven, mix Jell-O as box says; let refrigerate for 10 to 15 minutes.
When cake is done, poke holes in it while still in pan.
Pour 1/2 the jello in the holes on cake. (Don't pour too much, you don't want it mushy or real wet.)
Turn cake over onto cake plate.
Put icing on it and serve.

title: chocolate treat
directions: Bake brownies and leave in pan.
Top with softened ice cream. Put crushed Oreos on top.
Place pan in freezer until ready to serve.
Cut into individual pieces.
Top with hot fudge whipped cream.

title: cabbage roll casserole
directions: Cook beef until lightly browned and crumbly.
Mix in onion, rice, salt and pepper; cook 2 to 3 minutes more.
Add soup and water; mix thoroughly.
Put cabbage in a 2-quart casserole dish. Pour meat mixture over cabbage; do not stir.
Cover and bake in slow oven at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: beer biscuits
directions: *Not 1 bottle.
The cook drinks the balance.

title: scalloped potatoes au gratin
directions: You will need a 6-cup baking dish (capable of being used on stove top).

title: pot roast
directions: Broil beef 4 inches from heat for 4 minutes on each side until browned.
Drain beef, pat with paper towels.
Spray large deep skillet with nonstick spray.
Place the beef, water, tomatoes (with juices), thyme, peppercorns and bay leaf in skillet.
Bring to boil, then reduce heat.
Cover; simmer for 2 hours.
Add carrots, potatoes, celery and onions.
Cover; simmer over low heat 45 to 60 minutes more or until beef and vegetables are tender, adding more water if needed as liquid evaporates.

title: marilyn mcconnell's meat casserole
directions: Mix the browned
hamburger,
garlic salt, onion, tomato sauce, salt and pepper into
a pot and simmer 15 minutes.
Mix the cooked noodles, cream
cheese and sour cream and stir into the meat sauce.
Turn
into
a
greased
casserole;
top
with mushrooms and grated cheese.
Bake for 45 minutes at 300°.

title: german chocolate upside down cake
directions: Grease baking pan.
Place coconut and pecans in the pan.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Place 1 1/2 cups cereal in Ziploc bag and crush cereal into crumbs. Combine honey and peanut butter until smooth. Add cereal crumbs. Roll into 1-inch balls. Roll in remaining uncrushed cereal. Chill.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Form dough into 1/2-inch balls and place 1-inch apart on baking
sheet.
Press
down
slightly
with
fork making waffle patterns on top of each cookie.
Makes about 3 dozen cookies.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash; drain well and mash. Combine all ingredients except 1/2 stick of margarine and 1/2 package of stuffing mix. Place all ingredients mixture in 2 1/2-quart casserole dish. Melt the 1/2 stick margarine and toss with stuffing mix. Spread over top of casserole. Bake, uncovered, for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate marshmallow cookie pie
directions: Microwave marshmallows and 2 tablespoons milk in medium microwavable bowl on High 45 seconds.
Stir.
(Marshmallows will be partially melted.)
Refrigerate 15 minutes to cool.
Stir in 1 cup of the Cool Whip.

title: apple cake
directions: Cream eggs and sugar.
Add oil; beat until creamy.
Add flour, salt, baking soda and cinnamon.
Fold in apples and nuts.
Pour into 8 x 15 x 2-inch casserole pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes. Cool and frost.

title: cheeseburger soup
directions: Brown beef; drain and set aside. In same pan, saut onion, carrots, celery, basil and parsley in 1 tablespoon butter until tender, about 10 minutes. Add broth, potatoes and beef; bring to a boil. Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 10 to 12 minutes or until potatoes are tender. Melt remaining butter in small skillet. Add flour; cook and stir for 3 to 5 minutes or until bubbly. Add to soup; bring to a boil. Cook and stir for 2 minutes; reduce heat. Add cheese, milk, salt and pepper. Cook until cheese melts. Remove from heat and blend in sour cream.

title: dried beef chip dip
directions: Put all ingredients into Food Processor and mix until creamy. Chill overnight. Serve with any crackers.

title: ham-potato-corn chowder
directions: Cook potatoes until tender in salted water. Drain (cut into small pieces) in large saucepan. Melt butter and saut onions until translucent. Add corn, salt and pepper. Bring to boil. Adjust heat and simmer 20 minutes. Enjoy!

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Mix the first 7 ingredients like a cake; beat it.
Pour into a 9-inch square baking pan or glass baking dish.
Spread over it the berries, 1 cup sugar (if unsweetened) and juice from the fruit. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix together and put in buttered dish.

title: cranberry pie-cake
directions: Grease a 10-inch pie plate.
Sprinkle cranberries, 1/2 cup of the sugar and the walnuts over the pie plate in that order.
Beat eggs thoroughly.
Add remaining 1 cup sugar, butter, sour cream and flour; beat only until dry ingredients are moistened.
Pour over cranberry mixture in plate.
Do not stir.
Bake in a 325° oven until brown on top, about 1 hour.
Makes about 8 servings. Quite good served warm.

title: pamadour pudding
directions: Scald, then cool milk.
Combine sugar, egg yolks, cornstarch, salt and vanilla and add to milk.
Stir constantly over low heat until thick.
Pour into casserole.
Cover with meringue made by melting together 2 squares chocolate, sugar and milk.
When cool, add this to stiffly beaten egg whites and vanilla.
Bake pudding in a pan of water about 15 minutes at 350°.

title: red devil's food delight
directions: Sift the first 4 ingredients into bowl.
Add shortening, milk and vanilla.
Beat with electric mixer on slow to medium speed for 2 minutes.
Scrape sides and bottom of bowl frequently.
Add eggs. Continue beating 2 more minutes, scraping bowl frequently.
Pour batter into prepared pans.
Cook at 375°.
Makes 2 layers.

title: indecent cookie bars
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together and press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cream together remaining ingredients and pour on top of crust.
Bake at 325° for approximately 35 minutes.

title: chicken oregano
directions: Put oil in baking dish, lay potatoes in bottom of dish. Then add chicken, salt and pepper. Sprinkle with oregano salt. Bake at 275 degrees for 2 hrs.

title: sweetened cheese spread
directions: Combine all ingredients. Stir until smooth.

title: strawberry and pretzel salad
directions: Mix together pretzels, margarine and 3 tablespoons sugar. Press into 13 x 9-inch pan and bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: punch
directions: Combine sugar and water.
Bring to a boil.
Add Kool-Aid and Jell-O.
Cool.
Add lemonade mix and pineapple juice.
Set overnight and add ginger ale.

title: cream of tomato soup
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a 2-quart saucepan.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Remove bay leaf.
Melt butter in a 2-quart saucepan; blend in flour.
Stir in milk.
Cook until thickened.
Slowly add hot tomato mixture, stirring constantly.
Use a whisk to stir this helps.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix margarine, shortening, eggs and sugar; beat well.
Add the rest of ingredients.
I roll these and use a cookie cutter, but you can roll them in a ball and flatten with a glass dipped in sugar.

title: no bake peanut oat cookies
directions: In medium saucepan, mix sugar and cocoa.
Add milk and butter. Put over medium heat and bring to a boil; boil for 1 minute. Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter and oats.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto foil-lined sheet paper.
Let stand until firm and cold.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: peach crisp
directions: Layer ingredients in order listed in a greased 9 x 13 dish. Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: cabbage pie
directions: Saute chopped cabbage,
onion
and
mushrooms in butter. Spread softened cream cheese on
bottom
of pie crust. Add half of cabbage mixture and top
with Mozzarella slices and top with 1/2 grated cheese.
Add remaining
cabbage mixture and top with Mozzarella
and
Cheddar cheese.
Bake
at
until
cheese melts.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix together with spoon and put in pie crust. Chill.

title: puppy chow for people
directions: Melt morsels and peanut butter over low heat. Remove pan from burner. Add cereal and stir until well coated. Put 1 cup of confectioners sugar into very large Ziploc bag. Add cereal mixture. Add 1 cup of confectioners sugar. Seal bag and shake gently to coat cereal.

title: foolproof apple cake
directions: Combine apples and sugar in a bowl.
Let stand 10 minutes. Combine flour and next 4 ingredients in a large bowl.
Stir well. Make a well in center of mixture.
Combine oil, vanilla and egg white; stir well.
Add to dry ingredients, stirring just until moistened.
Stir in apple mixture.

title: date and nut bars
directions: Pour boiling water over dates and cool.
Place shortening, sugar, salt, spices, eggs and cooled date mixture in large mixing bowl.
Beat until thoroughly blended.
Sift together flour and baking soda.
Add with nuts to first mixture.
Beat until blended. Place mixture in greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Spread evenly. Bake in 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool in pan and cut. Roll in powdered sugar.

title: charcoal grilled steaks
directions: Combine.
Pour over steaks and marinate 2 to 3 hours, turning occasionally.

title: snack mix
directions: Place popcorn, pretzels, cereal, peanuts and raisins in a large bowl.
Add margarine; toss to coat well.
Sprinkle with gelatin; toss until evenly coated.
Makes 10 cups.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Mix well and pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: butterscotch cheesecake squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (325° for glass dish).

In saucepan, melt morsels and butter; stir in crumbs and nuts. Press half of mixture firmly into bottom of greased 13 x 9-inch pan. Beat cheese until fluffy; beat condensed milk, vanilla and egg. Pour on top of pressed crumbs. Top with remaining crumb mixture.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until toothpick inserted near center comes out clean. Cool at room temperature. Chill before cutting. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: apricot squares
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking powder and oats.
Cut in butter until crumbly.
Pat mixture into 9 1/2 x 13-inch pan.
(Save some of the mixture.)
Spread jam over bottom layer.
Cover with remaining crumbs.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 35 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole(serves 12 to 14)
directions: Saute onions in 1/2 cup butter until tender.
Combine everything except stuffing and pour into two lightly greased casserole dishes.
Melt remaining 1/2 cup butter and stir into stuffing mix to use as topping.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken stew
directions: Cook chicken. Cool and pull chicken off bones. Cut in small pieces. Combine corn, onion, potatoes and soup in chicken broth. Cook until potatoes are tender.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix all ingredients, except crackers, in a 1-quart (Tupperware) casserole.
Cook on High 4 to 8 minutes in the microwave.
Serve hot on snack crackers.

title: dried beef dip
directions: Mix all ingredients except pecans.
Bake in a small baking dish at 300° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Top with pecans.
Serve with crackers.

title: low fat bran muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix flour, baking soda, baking powder and cinnamon in large bowl.
Mix cereal, milk and sugar in another. Let stand 5 minutes.
Stir in egg and applesauce.
Add to flour mixture.
Stir until moistened.
Spoon in muffin tins sprayed with oil 2/3 full.
Bake 18 to 20 minutes or until brown.

title: quick peanutty popcorn balls
directions: In a saucepan, mix corn syrup and sugar.
Cook over medium heat; stir constantly until mixture comes to a boil and sugar is completely dissolved.
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter until smooth.
Immediately pour mixture over popcorn in large bowl.
Stir until well coated.
Grease hands and shape into 8 (2 1/2-inch) balls.

title: shanghai chicken wings
directions: Set aside wings.
Mix rest of ingredients together.
Pour over wings.
Marinate 8 hours or more.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°. Serve warm, with plenty of napkins.

title: cranberry fruit bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Combine cranberries and sugar; set aside.
Stir together flour, cereal, baking powder, salt, cinnamon, baking soda and cloves.
Combine eggs, milk and oil.
Pour over dry ingredients.
Add cranberries and nuts.
Stir only until thoroughly moistened.
Pour into pan(s).
Bake 65 to 70 minutes (big pans) or until tester comes out clean.
Cool before removing from pan.

title: chocolate frosting
directions: In heavy saucepan, melt butter with milk.
Blend in ground chocolate and salt.
Remove from heat.
Add powdered sugar and vanilla.
Beat with electric mixer about 5 minutes or until smooth and glossy.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Melt butter in large flat casserole dish.
Add soup, water, seasoning and rice.
Lay chicken on rice mixture.
Sprinkle with salt and 1 teaspoon paprika.
Bake for 3 hours at 250°.

title: chocolate peanut butter cookies
directions: Bring sugar, milk, cocoa and butter to a boil.
Add vanilla flavoring, peanut butter and oatmeal.
Mix well and drop on wax paper.

title: spiced tea
directions: Boil water, add tea bags.
Set aside for 30 minutes.
Add spices.
Let set for 15 minutes.
Add all the juices and serve hot.

title: spinach squares
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Put margarine in an 8 x 10-inch baking dish and melt in oven.
Remove.
In a large bowl, beat eggs well, then add flour, milk, salt and baking powder.
Mix well. Add cheese, spinach and onion.
Mix well. Put into baking dish. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cut into squares when cooled, about 20 minutes.
Preparation time: 10 minutes.

title: chocolate drops
directions: Mix butter, milk, sugar and vanilla until light and fluffy. Add coconut and pecans.
Form balls and freeze over night.
Melt chocolate chips and paraffin in top of double boiler.
Keep warm and dip in this mixture.
Yield:
100 servings.

title: mary's cheese ball(makes 2)
directions: Combine all but last two ingredients, then add onions.
Divide in half.
Form into balls.
Roll in pecans.

title: baking powder cinnamon rolls
directions: Cut shortening into flour in which baking powder and salt were added.
Add milk.
Mix well.
Roll out to 3/4-inch thickness. Spread with melted butter, sugar and cinnamon.
Roll as log.
Cut about 1-inch thick and bake in a 350° oven until browned.

title: mama's chocolate ice cream
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Add beaten eggs.
Warm milk on stove, then add egg mixture.
Cook slowly in double boiler until milk coats spoon.
Cool.
Add 2 teaspoons vanilla.
Makes 1 gallon ice cream.

title: easy, any meat casserole
directions: Mix together macaroni, meat, peas, cheese and onion.
Mix soup and milk.
Add to first mixture.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle the Parmesan cheese and paprika on top.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Leave at room temperature 1 hour before baking.
Bake covered at 350° for 1 hour.

title: banana split pie
directions: Beat together for 15 minutes on medium speed oleo, confectioners sugar, eggs and vanilla.
After beating together 15 minutes, pour mixture into graham cracker crusts.
Slice bananas. Put on top of each pie.
Spread pineapple over bananas.
Spread Cool Whip equal over both pies.
Sprinkle chopped pecans over Cool Whip.
Put a maraschino cherry on each slice and one on the middle. Drizzle chocolate syrup over pies.
Cool in freezer 1 hour.

title: pecan fudge cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 3 (9-inch) layer cake pans.
In a large bowl, cream the butter.
Gradually add the sugar; beat until fluffy.
Add the beaten eggs and melted chocolate.
Sift the dry ingredients; blend in alternately with the milk.
Add the nuts and vanilla.
Pour into prepared pans.
Bake for 35 minutes, or until the center of the cake feels solid.
Cool and remove the layers from the pans.
Fill and frost.

title: cavatini
directions: Brown ground beef with onions and salt and pepper.
Cook noodles until tender.
In large baking dish, combine ground beef and noodles.
Pour spaghetti sauce over mixture; stir well.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
During the last 10 minutes, sprinkle Mozzarella cheese over casserole and finish baking.

title: cheese cake
directions: Will need a spring cake pan.

title: molded fruit salad
directions: Mix together gelatin, sugar and salt.
Let cool and add all ingredients except cream cheese and whip cream.
Pour cream into bowl and cut cream cheese into small pieces.
Whip together and fold into fruit ingredients.
Chill 4 hours.

title: cream caramels
directions: Bring sugar, corn syrup, butter and 1 cup cream slowly to a boil, stirring constantly.
Stir in gradually 1 more cup cream. Stir frequently as mixture begins to thicken, constantly as it darkens.
Cook to 254° (a little dropped into cold water forms a hard ball).
Pour into buttered 7-inch square pan with 1/2 cup broken nuts scattered over the bottom.
When cold, cut into squares.
Makes 5 dozen caramels.

title: baked yams
directions: Mash yams.
Add juice from pineapple, sugar and butter, beating well.
Add pineapple and pecans.
Spoon mixture into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Remove from oven and sprinkle on marshmallows.
Bake 10 minutes more.

title: lazy lady bread or rolls(no kneading)
directions: Combine 1 cup boiling water and milk in a bowl; add 3 teaspoons sugar and margarine.
Mix well.
Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup warm water.
Add to milk mixture.
Mix well; set aside.
Sift flour, salt and 1 1/2 teaspoons sugar together in large bowl.
Make well in center; pour liquid ingredients into flour mixture.
Mix thoroughly.
Cover with waxed paper.
Let rise until doubled. Divide in half.
Shape into 2 loaves.
Place in greased loaf pans. Let rise until double in bulk.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes. Reduce temperature to 350°.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes longer or until golden brown.

title: chicken and port wine ragout
directions: Sprinkle chicken with black pepper.
Heat oil in a skillet large enough to hold chicken in one layer.
Add chicken, skin side down and brown on one side.
Turn and brown on the other side. The time for browning is approximately 15 minutes.
Add onion, garlic, parsley, basil, tomato sauce and 2/3 cup of wine.
Cover and cook 25 to 30 minutes.
Add remaining wine.
Sprinkle with red pepper flakes and stir to blend.
Serve over bed of white rice. Serves 4.

title: chicken mandarin
directions: Coat chicken with flour.
In skillet, heat oil and margarine; brown the chicken.
Drain off fat.
Drain mandarin oranges saving juice.
Mix juice with lemon juice, honey, soy sauce, orange juice and ginger.
Pour sauce over chicken, cover and simmer 45 minutes or until tender.
Remove chicken, thicken with cornstarch.
Add chicken and mandarin oranges.
Serve over rice.

title: chicken imperial
directions: Combine all ingredients, except chicken and salt, in saucepan and blend over medium heat for 2 to 5 minutes, until smooth.
Salt chicken on both sides and place in an ungreased oblong pan, skin side down.
Brush chicken generously with sauce, using about 3/4 of sauce.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Uncover, turn chicken and add the rest of the sauce and continue baking for 30 minutes or until tender.
Yield: 4 servings.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix dressing.
Pour over other ingredients.
Stir well. Marinate overnight.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Melt oleo and peanut butter.
Add vanilla and sugar and beat well.
Pour into a buttered cake pan and refrigerate for 3 hours.

title: fish in tomato sauce on barbecue pit
directions: Place onions and parsley in olive oil and saute for a little while.
Add garlic and then the rest of the ingredients except fish.
Cook until the onions are nearly done.
Pour sauce over fish to be baked on the pit in a boat made from aluminum foil.

title: brown sugar (dark karo) peanut brittle
directions: Butter large cookie sheet and sides of 3-quart saucepan.
In saucepan, combine sugar, brown sugar or dark Karo, corn syrup, water, butter or margarine and salt.
Bring to boil, stirring to dissolve sugar.
Clip candy thermometer to side of pan.
Cook over medium heat with gentle boil to 275° (syrup turns a deep golden color), stirring constantly.
Stir in peanuts; continue cooking, stirring often until 295°.
Remove from heat; quickly stir in baking soda.
Immediately pour hot mixture onto buttered cookie sheet.
If desired, pull with forks to stretch thin; cool.
Break into pieces.
Makes about 2 1/4 pounds of candy.

title: recipe for a happy marriage
directions: Flavor with frequent portions of recreation and a dash of happy memories.
Stir well and remove any specks of jealousy, temper, or criticism.
Sweeten well with generous portions of love and keep warm with a steady flame of devotion.
Never serve with cold shoulder or hot tongue.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake as directed.
When cool, crumble 1/2 of cake in punch bowl.

title: sweet-sour cabbage
directions: Cook in bacon grease.
Add caraway seeds and 1 beef bouillon cube.
Cook cabbage 15 minutes, no more.

title: swiss fondue
directions: Mix cheese with cornstarch, salt, pepper and paprika.
In a chafing dish, heat buttermilk with garlic clove over low heat. When hot, remove garlic and add cheese.
Stir constantly until cheese is melted.
Serve from chafing dish.
Each person helps himself from the common dish, dipping chunks of bread speared on long forks into the cheese sauce.

title: double decker fudge
directions: Line a 13 x 9-inch pan with foil.
Put 1 cup peanut butter chips in medium bowl.
Set aside.
In second medium bowl, blend 1/4 cup melted butter, cocoa and vanilla until smooth.
Add 1 cup peanut butter chips.
In heavy 4-quart saucepan, combine sugar, Marshmallow Creme, evaporated milk and 1/4 cup butter.
Cook, stirring constantly, over medium heat until mixture comes to a rolling boil.
Boil and stir 5 minutes.
Remove from heat. Immediately add half of the mixture to bowl with peanut butter chips only.
Pour remainder into cocoa mixture and stir to blend. Beat peanut butter mixture until chips are completely melted. Spread evenly in prepared pan.

title: roxies petite gateaus
directions: In a large mixing bowl cream butter and both sugars, add eggs and vanilla.
Then mix together all dry ingredients; add to cream mixture, mix well.	Add remaining ingredients; roll into balls, place two inches apart on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 6 to 10 minutes.
Makes about 100 cookies.

title: fruit topper
directions: Mix all together.
Drop on fruit.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: tortilla soup(soup)
directions: Drain pimentos, reserving liquid. In medium saucepan, cook onion and cumin in margarine over medium heat for 2-3 minutes. Stirring occasionally. Stir in reserved pimentos juice, chicken broth, corn and parsley. Heat to a boil. Reduce heat, cover and simmer 10 minutes.

title: homemade pizza
directions: Mix crust by package directions. Bake until light brown 350°.

title: orange spectacular
directions: In bowl, empty the container of cottage cheese.
Sprinkle with dry jello.
Add pineapple and oranges.
Mix and add Cool Whip. Mix again until thoroughly combined.
Chill overnight.

title: "dorito dip"
directions: Layer each of the ingredients.
Make beans on bottom and cheese on top.

title: dried beef cheese ball
directions: Stir all together and roll into a ball.
Keep refrigerated.

title: barbecue beans
directions: *I like Van Camp's the best.

title: sauerkraut
directions: I cook my pork before and cut it up in small pieces, then add to the sauerkraut mixture.
Bake at 350° several hours.

title: stuffed hot peppers
directions: Clean hot peppers and take out seeds.
Stuff with sauerkraut. Cook sugar, vinegar and mustard seed until it comes to a boil. Pour over hot peppers that are packed in jars.
Cold pack for 20 minutes.

title: orange slice cookies
directions: Combine beaten eggs, brown sugar, vanilla and water in bowl; mix well.
Stir in flour and candy.
Add coconut and pecans; mix well.
Drop by tablespoonfuls 2 inches apart onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool on cookie sheet for 2 minutes.
Remove to wire rack to cool completely.
Yield:
24 servings.

title: angel crisp cookies
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugars.
Add other ingredients in order given.
Roll into balls the size of a walnut; dip top in sugar.
Place on cookie sheet, sugar side up, and bake at 375° for 8 minutes.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Hull out loaf of pumpernickel bread and put dip in loaf.
Use pieces of bread to dip with.

title: hawaii pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into lined pie shell.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease cookie sheets. Combine in a large bowl all ingredients.
Stir until moistened.
Roll into balls about the size of walnuts.
Place on cookie sheets about 1 1/2-inches apart.
Bake for 10 to 15 minutes until light golden brown.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: christmas puffs
directions: Beat egg whites with salt. Add brown sugar. Continue beating. Add pecans. Put on greased cookie sheet 1 teaspoon-size or small as possible. Bake 30 minutes at 300°.

title: turtle cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to directions and add margarine. Put 1/2 batter in 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake 12 minutes in 350° oven.
Melt caramels with 1/2 cup evaporated milk.
Takes 4 or 5 minutes in microwave.
Pour melted caramels over baked cake mixture.
Sprinkle chips and nuts over this.
Add remaining cake batter and spread over top.
Bake 30 minutes.
Serve plain or with whipped cream.

title: orange rice
directions: Combine orange juice and salt in skillet, bring quickly to a boil.
Stir in rice.
Cover and remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes.

title: play doh
directions: Dip large macaroni into different food colors for a few seconds.
Lay the macaroni on paper towels until it dries.
Cut a piece of yarn long enough to make a necklace or bracelet.
Wrap it at one end with transparent tape.
Tie a piece of macaroni at the other end.
String the macaroni.
Then untie the piece of macaroni and tie the yarn ends together.

title: white fruit cake
directions: Mix fruit and nuts and coat with the flour, baking powder and salt.
Separate eggs and beat whites stiff; add last.
Beat yolks and add to mixture with sugar beaten with yolks and add vanilla ad 1 cup of orange juice.
Pour other cup of orange juice over cakes after baking before wrapping with foil.
Grease tins (bread tins, fruit cake tins or a tube pan).
Bake 2 hours at 250° to 300° in tube tin and others depend on the size of tin and the size you make the cakes.
Small ones bake in 1 hour.
Test with toothpick in center to see if done.

title: dirt dessert
directions: Blend Oreos, cream cheese and sugar together.
Mix until thick the pudding, milk and vanilla.
Add the Cool Whip.
Layer in a bowl, cookie mixture, then pudding mixture and repeat ending with cookie mixture.

title: raspberry chocolate chip muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Coat a 12-cup muffin tin or a 6-cup jumbo tin with vegetable cooking spray or line with papers.
Mix flour, baking soda and salt in a medium bowl; set aside.
Beat melted butter and eggs until combined; add sugar and beat until fluffy.
Mix in half of dry ingredients.
Mix in yogurt; add remaining dry ingredients.
Mix until incorporated.

title: sunshine golden yellow cake
directions: In mixing bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt. Add the 3/4 cup milk and the Crisco.
Beat vigorously by hand or at medium speed of electric mixer for 2 minutes.
Add eggs, the 1/2 cup milk and the vanilla.
Beat 2 minutes more.
Pour batter into 2 greased and floured 9 x 1 1/2-inch round layer pans or a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chocolate brownies
directions: Melt 1 cup (8 ounces) of chocolate chips and margarine in saucepan.
Mix flour, sugar, baking soda, eggs and vanilla.
Add melted chips and butter.
Put mixture in greased 9 x 9-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle top with remaining chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: zucchini cookies
directions: Mix zucchini, sugar, oil, egg and vanilla. Stir in the rest of the ingredients. Drop mixture by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 12-15 minutes.

title: old-fashioned cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add egg yolk, nutmeg, baking soda and flour.
Stir in milk and vanilla until a stiff dough forms.
Chill 15 minutes, if desired.
Roll out on lightly floured board; cut with round cookie cutter about 2 1/2 inches in diameter.
Bake at 400° for 5 to 8 minutes or until brown.

title: old fashioned corn meal mush
directions: Mix the corn meal, flour and sugar with the cold water, then stir into the boiling water to which the salt has been added. When thoroughly mixed, cover tightly.
Reduce the heat to the lowest point and let simmer for 30 minutes, or longer, stirring occasionally to prevent lumping.
Then turn off the heat and let steam for 30 minutes without lifting the cover.
Serve warm with milk or cream or pour into a greased loaf pan.
When cool, slice and fry.
Serve with syrup.

title: fish soup
directions: In large saucepan saute onion, celery and garlic in margarine or batter until tender.
Stir in tomatoes, wine, parsley, salt, pepper and thyme.
Cover.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Add fish and simmer for 7 to 10 minutes or until fish is opaque and flakes easily with fork.

title: best ever banana bread
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Pour into greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Do not double recipe.
Yields one 9 x 5-inch loaf.

title: honey nut grahams
directions: Melt the butter/sugar.
Bring to a boil for 2 minutes.
Pour mixture over grahams. Sprinkle nuts.
Bake at 350 for 8 minutes.

title: chicken pie
directions: Cook chicken.
Remove meat from bones.
Place meat in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix chicken broth with cream of celery soup and pour over chicken.
Mix Bisquick with milk (mixture will be thin).
Pour over chicken.
Top with melted margarine.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: lemon-zucchini rice
directions: Bring broth, water, salt and pepper to a boil in saucepan. Add rice.
Return to boiling.
Lower heat; simmer, covered, 20 minutes.
Set aside, covered, 5 minutes.
Uncover and fluff rice with a fork.
Add zucchini and lemon juice.

title: summer sausage
directions: Mix together well.
Roll out in 3 small rolls and put on shiny side of aluminum foil.
Let stand 24 hours in refrigerator. Punch holes in bottom of foil and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours in broiler pan.

title: strawberry pretzels
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients. Bake at 350° for 6 to 10 minutes.

title: raspberry cake
directions: Mix all together. Bake in 13 x 9 pan at 325° for 50 minutes.

title: beef tenderloin
directions: Marinate beef for 30 minutes in combination of French vinaigrette dressing and Dale's steak sauce, half and half. Preheat oven to 425°.
Place bacon on top of tenderloin.
Cook 10 to 11 minutes per pound.
Enjoy immediately.
Sauteed mushrooms go great with this.

title: ranch ham roll-ups
directions: In small mixing bowl, beat the cream cheese and salad dressing. Mix until smooth. Add onions and mix well. Spread about 3 tablespoons over each tortilla. Top with ham slices. Roll up tightly and wrap in plastic wrap. Refrigerate until firm. Unwrap and cut into 3/4-inch slices. Yields about 7 1/2 dozen.

title: george jr.'s mustard chicken
directions: Heat butter and oil in casserole and brown chicken.
Season to taste with salt and pepper and remove.
In fat remaining, cook onions until brown.
Add flour, milk, mustard and chicken broth. Return chicken to skillet and cook under low heat for 20 minutes.

title: cocoa fudge
directions: Butter pan and set aside.
Stir together cocoa, sugar, salt and milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture comes to a full rolling boil.
Let boil (do not stir) until soft ball stage (forms a ball when dropped in cold water). Remove from heat; add vanilla and butter but do not stir.
Cool to lukewarm and then stir until fudge starts to thicken.
Spread into buttered pan.

title: beet pickles
directions: To cook beets, wash and drain.
Leave 2 inches of stems and the top roots.
Cover with boiling water and cook until tender. Combine all ingredients except beets; simmer 15 minutes.
Pack beets into hot jars, leaving 1/2-inch headspace.
Remove cinnamon. Bring liquid to boil.
Pour boiling hot over beets, leaving 1/2-inch headspace.
Adjust caps.
Process pints and quarts 30 minutes in boiling water bath, about 6 pints.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix together the first 5 ingredients. Stir the flour into the sugar well.
Add the pecans. Top casserole. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: sue hammer's bread and butter pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers and slice as thin as possible.
Chop onions and peppers; combine cucumbers, onions and peppers.
Mix salt in enough water to cover.
Let stand 3 hours.
Combine vinegar, sugar and spices.
Bring to a boil.
Add drained cucumbers, onions and peppers.
Heat thoroughly but do not boil.
Pack in sterilized hot jars.
Cover with liquid and seal.
Yield:
12 to 15 pints.

title: sinful pie
directions: Melt butter and chocolate.
Mix the eggs and sugar.
Add vanilla, rum, cinnamon and orange peel.
Fold in melted ingredients.
Pour into graham shell.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle nuts and coconut in the bottom of the pan.
Mix cake acccording to directions on box; pour over nuts and coconut.
Beat powdered sugar and cream cheese together.
Add melted margarine.
Beat until smooth.
Add vanilla and pour over cake mix.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until cake tests done.
Let cool 10 minutes and invert on a serving dish, if desired.

title: chicken nuggets
directions: Combine Parmesan cheese, Cheddar cheese, crumbs, monosodium glutamate, thyme, salt, basil and pepper.
Blend well.
Dip chicken pieces into melted butter.
Roll in crumb mixture. Arrange chicken in single layer in ovenware dish.
Cover with plastic wrap, poking several holes in the plastic wrap.
Cook chicken for 10 minutes.
Serve hot or cold.
May be garnished with parsley.
Total cooking time 10 minutes.
Recipe yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: schweinbraten(roast pork)
directions: Sprinkle pork with onion salt, marjoram and pepper.
Secure on spit; insert thermometer.
Adjust spit about 8 inches from heat source, placing foil pan under pork to catch drippings.
Roast 15 minutes or bake uncovered on rack at 350° until the thermometer registers 170° to 185° according to family taste.
Allow 35 to 40 minutes per pound for roasting.
Shortly before serving, combine in skillet the sauerkraut, thinly sliced apples, cider and butter. Cover and simmer 5 minutes or until apples are tender.
Garnish with extra apple slices and parsley.
Serve with pork.

title: tiger butter
directions: In a 2 quart microwave dish melt white chocolate at medium (50% power) stir in peanut butter. Spread this mixture on a waxpaper coated cookie sheet. Immediately melt a 6 oz. package of semisweet chocolate chips at medium power for 3 to 5 minutes and drizzle over the peanut butter layer. With knife swirl mixture. Refrigerate until firm then break into pieces.

title: blueberry pie marnier
directions: Spread 2 cups blueberries in pie crust.
Refrigerate until well chilled.
Simmer remaining 2 cups berries, sugar, water, cornstarch and salt in heavy saucepan until thickened, stirring constantly, about 7 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Mix in Grand Marnier and butter.
Cool completely.
Pour blueberry sauce over berries in pie crust.
Refrigerate until well chilled.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Dice up red onion.
Mix 3/4 cup cheese, pecans, 1/2 cup bacon bits and 2 cups broccoli tops.

title: apple pandowdy
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Prepare pastry for 8-inch two crust pie as directed on package. Stir together apple slices and brown sugar. Turn into pastry lined pie pan.
Top with butter and 3 tablespoons of the syrup. Cover with top crust which has slits cut in it. Seal and flute. Bake 15 minutes.
Remove from oven.

Make crisscross cuts about 1-inch apart through top crust and filling. Drizzle remaining syrup on top. Cover edge with 2 to 3-inch strips of aluminum foil to prevent excessive browning. Bake 25 minutes longer. Serve warm, and, if you wish, pour on additional syrup.

title: sunday roast
directions: Preheat oven to 350° on Sunday morning before Sunday school. Peel carrots and potatoes and leave in large chunks; set aside. Pam the bottom of the roasting pan with lid.
Put chuck roast in pan and place raw vegetables on top and around the roast.
Sprinkle garlic salt and chili powder on meat and vegetables.
Place onion rings on top and pour your favorite barbecue sauce over it all. Put in oven at 9:30 a.m. and you have a wonderful meal when you get home!

title: cherry pie
directions: Combine juice, sugar, flour, salt and lemon.
Cook until thick; add butter.
Pour over cherries in an 8-inch pastry lined pie pan.

Cut strips of pie dough for twisted lattice top crust. Flute edge and trim. Bake in a 450° oven for 10 minutes, then in a 350° oven for 30 minutes. If fresh cherries are used, increase sugar to 1/2 cup.

title: tex-mex enchiladas
directions: Prepare chili as directed on package using ground beef, water and tomato sauce.
Place approximately 2 tablespoons chili on each tortilla; roll tightly.
Place seam side down in a 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
Top with remaining chili.
Cover and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Top with process cheese cubes and bake, uncovered, for 5 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: yum yum salad
directions: Prepare pasta as directed on box, drain and cool.
Mix chopped eggs, celery, pimentos and onion; add to cooked pasta.
Pour Italian dressing over mixture; add pepper and salt.
Toss to coat. Refrigerate at least 1 hour.
Toss before serving.

title: honey glazed carrots
directions: Wash, scrape and slice carrots.
Cook in boiling water until tender.
Melt butter in skillet.
Stir in mint leaves; let stand. Add carrots, salt, brown sugar and honey.
Cook until well glazed. Turn often.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix well. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: el slop o
directions: Brown ground beef, drain.
Add onion and pepper.

title: barbecue meatballs
directions: Combine ingredients (mixture will be soft).
Shape into walnut-size balls.
Place in single layer on wax-paper-lined cookie sheets and freeze until solid.
Store in freezer bags until ready to cook.

title: bread
directions: Take it out and roll it in hand.
Put it in the black thing. Then put in the stove 5000° for 40 minutes.
After it cooks we eat it's good!

title: orange balls
directions: Mix all together.
Form small balls.
Roll in coconut. Refrigerate.

title: creamy egg nog pie
directions: In a medium saucepan combine pudding mix, 1/4 teaspoon nutmeg and egg nog.
Mix well.
Over medium heat, cook and stir until thick and bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in rum.
Cool.
Fold in whipped cream.
Spoon into pie shell.
Chill 4 hours or more.

title: microwave apples
directions: Peel, core and slice apples.
In a 2-quart casserole dish, place apples and water, cover and microwave 10 to 15 minutes, or until tender.
Stir once during cooking.
Stir in sugar and spices.
Cover and let stand 15 minutes.
Serves well warm or cold.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix peanut butter and powdered sugar; press firmly into bottom of a cooled 9-inch (deep) shell.

title: pineapple muffins
directions: Drain pineapple liquid into a measuring cup.
Add enough milk to make 1 cup.
Combine egg and orange rind.
In separate bowl, sift together flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and nutmeg.
Blend milk mixture into dry ingredients, along with melted butter mixing just until batter is blended.
Stir in crushed pineapple.
Spoon into lightly buttered muffin pans.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until golden and set.
Cool slightly.
Then remove from pan and serve warm.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: orange chiffon cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Set out, but do not grease, a 10-inch tube pan.
Stir flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Make a well in the mixture and add egg substitute, orange juice, oil and orange peel and mix until smooth.
Beat egg whites and cream of tartar until stiff peaks form.
Pour first mixture slowly over egg whites and fold gently with spatula until just blended. Spoon batter into tube pan.
Bake in lower third of oven for 50 to 55 minutes.
Invert and let cool completely before removing from pan.
Run a thin knife up and down between cake and pan to loosen and remove.
Drizzle Orange Glaze over top and sides of cake. Makes 16 servings.

title: stuffed baked potatoes
directions: Prick potatoes and place in oven.
Microwave on High for 10 to 12 minutes or until tender.
Cut potatoes in half.
Carefully scoop cooked potato out of shells and into mixing bowl.
Add butter, milk, salt and pepper.
Mash until lump free.
Fill potato shells; top with cheese and place on glass serving platter. Continue cooking on High for 4 to 5 minutes.
Let stand 3 minutes before serving.
Makes 4 to 8 servings.

title: sweet potato salad
directions: In a large pot, cover sweet potatoes with water. Add salt and bring to a boil over moderately high heat. Cook until just tender, about 10 minutes; drain well. Refresh with cold water and drain again.

title: giant tacos
directions: Brown meat and chopped onions.
Add other ingredients.
Simmer about 20 minutes, stirring several times.
Put amount of regular Fritos on your plate that you think you need.
Add the meat mixture, sharp grated cheese, chopped lettuce and fresh chopped tomatoes.

title: hamburg stuffing
directions: Cook meat together in frying pan and put aside.
Mix hot water, bread, Bell seasoning and onion powder.
Add egg and mix. Add meat and mix together.
Bake 45 minutes at 325° or use as stuffing for turkey.

title: oven fried potatoes
directions: Place potatoes in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan in a single layer, slightly overlapping.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Brush potatoes with 1/2 oil mixture.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 45 minutes, basting occasionally, with the rest of the oil mixture. Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: crab dip
directions: Melt butter and cheese together (I use microwave) and beat with mixer until fluffy.
Fold in picked crab meat.
Freezes well. Will make enough dip for 15 hungry people along with other foods. Also delicious over baked potatoes.

title: cherry fruit squares
directions: Put 2/3 of dough in pan.
Then put fruit filling on top, then the rest of dough on top in globs.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes. Make a glaze of powdered sugar and water and drizzle over top.

title: fireside casserole
directions: Heat large skillet.
Add beef, onion and garlic; brown about 5 minutes.
Drain off fat.
Stir in tomatoes, beans, cumin, salt, oregano, Tabasco and bay leaf.
Spoon mixture into 2-quart baking dish.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Uncover.
Bake 15 minutes longer until heated through.
You can add grated cheese and let melt and brown.

title: hawaiian salad
directions: Cook macaroni as directed.
Drain juice from oranges, pineapples and cherries. In small bowl, mix together eggs, flour, sugar and salt. Mix into fruit juice and cook until lightly thickened. Cool, then mix with macaroni.
Refrigerate overnight. Add fruit and Cool Whip.

title: prune coffee cake
directions: Cut prunes into pieces, discarding pits and set aside.
Cream margarine and sugar until light.
Add eggs, beating well after each addition.
Toss flour, baking powder and salt into the mix. Add vanilla, almond and milk, alternating additions.
Fold in prunes to distribute evenly.

title: 3 bean casserole
directions: Fry bacon to a crisp.
Brown onion and hamburger.
Discard all grease.
Drain kidney beans and butter beans.
Add all ingredients together and cook to blend.

title: mama's orange julius
directions: Crunch ice cubes and water in blender until fairly smooth. Add remaining ingredients and blend until smooth.

title: apple chunks
directions: Place apples in casserole dish, sprinkle with remaining ingredients.
Cover and cook on High in microwave 7 to 8 minutes. I usually double everything.

title: strawberry shortcut cake
directions: Generously grease bottom only of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle marshmallows on bottom of pan.
In a bowl, combine strawberries, syrup and gelatin thoroughly; set aside.

title: chewy squares
directions: Mix and place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cut while warm.

title: easy low-fat chocolate chip cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
With mixer, beat cheese until fluffy, gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk until smooth. Add egg and vanilla; mix well.
Toss chips with flour and stir into cheese mixture.
Pour into crust.
Bake for 35 minutes or until center springs back when touched.
Serve chilled.
Refrigerate.

title: lemon cake
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Pour into greased and floured pan. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: prune cake
directions: Mix oil and sugar.
Add eggs and prunes.
Sift flour, salt, soda and spices together.
Add dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk to prune mixture.
Add vanilla and pecans.
Pour into lightly greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes in a 350° oven.
Pour icing on cake while cake is still warm.
Cake is best if baked a couple of days before serving.

title: pecan muffins
directions: Combine sugar, flour, salt and pecans and mix well.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix well.
Fill greased muffin pans half full and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: In frying pan, brown hamburger with onion, salt and pepper. Drain off grease.
Separately fix potatoes according to box.
In casserole dish, put browned hamburger. Spread the mashed potatoes evenly over the hamburger.
Place cheese slices on top.
Put in oven at 350° until cheese melts.

title: texas corn bread
directions: Mix well all ingredients, except for cheese.
Put 3 tablespoons corn oil in deep iron skillet.
Heat.
Sprinkle with corn meal.
Pour in half the batter.
Sprinkle with the cheese, then pour in remaining batter.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour, oleo, vanilla, eggs, milk and coconut.
Put in unbaked pie shell.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: favorite carrot salad
directions: Combine carrots, raisins, celery and nuts.
Blend mayonnaise and salt.
Mix lightly with carrot mixture.
Chill.

title: breakfast strata
directions: Cook and crumble the sausage.
Combine all ingredients and pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch oven dish.
Refrigerate 12 hours. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until firm and golden brown on top.

title: candy basic
directions: Make 3 balls in 3 bowls (after mixing together first 3 ingredients).
Then add extract.
Roll round balls and chill.
Dip into melted chocolate (use double boiler) with toothpick.

title: meat ball soup
directions: Heat broth to simmer.
Mix beef, egg, salt, pepper and oregano.
Shape in 1 1/2-inch balls. Drop in broth.
Add onions, celery, carrots, cabbage, tomatoes, noodles, bay leaf, basil and parsley.
Simmer 35 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Discard bay leaf.
Stir in soy sauce.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: chewy oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening with sugar and vanilla.
Add beaten eggs. Dissolve soda in boiling water.
Mix flour, oats, raisins and nuts to first mixture.
Drop onto greased cookie sheet by teaspoon. Bake for 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: colorful vegetable medley
directions: Place 1 inch of water in a saucepan; add carrots.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 4 minutes.
Add asparagus; simmer 3 to 5 minutes longer or until vegetables are crisp-tender. Drain.
In a saucepan, melt butter over medium heat; stir in the vinegar, Worcestershire sauce, thyme and ginger.
Add carrots, asparagus, water chestnuts and parsley.
Cook and stir 1 to 2 minutes or until heated through.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar together. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Sift dry ingredients together 3 times.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk.
Add vanilla.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: mushroom roll-ups
directions: Cut off crust from each slice of bread.
Roll slices thin and flat with rolling pin.
Saute mushrooms in butter for five minutes.
Stir in flour until well blended.
Stir in cream or milk; cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Stir in salt, m.s.g., chives and lemon juice.
Remove from heat.
Place one to two teaspoons of the mixture on each slice of bread and roll up like a jelly roll.
Butter the top side of each with the softened butter.
Freeze.
When ready to serve, cut in half and place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for about 30 minutes or until light brown.

title: divinity fudge
directions: Boil sugar, Karo and water until it forms a hard ball when dropped in cold water.
Beat slowly into well beaten egg whites (beat with mixer).
Add nuts and vanilla.
When it begins to thicken, drop by the spoonful on heavy waxed paper.
Pack in airtight bowl.

title: sunday cornbread
directions: In a bowl mix cornmeal, flour and sugar. Combine butter, eggs and buttermilk together. Pour into dry ingredients and mix well. Pour in to a hot oil skillet. Bake at 400° for
25 minutes or until brown.

title: *old fashioned taffy
directions: Combine together and boil until it forms soft ball in water. Grease plate; pour in and cool until you can pick up in hand and work with it.
Pull until you can't pull anymore.
Roll into sticks.
Put on greased plate and cool, then break it with knife. (It will be brittle.)

title: shrimp curry
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Add celery and green pepper; cook until soft.
Add soup, shrimp, water and rice; heat and add olives.
Mix and serve.

title: baked apple crunch
directions: Arrange apples in greased, 2-quart casserole; sprinkle with water.
Combine tapioca, sugar, cinnamon, raisins and pecans. Spread over apples.
Mix oats, flour and brown sugar; cut in butter or margarine until crumbly.
Sprinkle over apples.

title: vidalia onion casserole
directions: Cover bottom of a 9 x 12-inch pan with crushed Ritz crackers. Saute onions in margarine; put on top of crushed crackers.
Beat egg and pour into a 1-cup measuring cup.
Fill remainder of cup with milk.
Add this mixture to cream of mushroom soup; pour over onions.
Sprinkle with crackers or cheese.
Bake at 350° for 3 minutes.

title: freezer pickles (sweet)
directions: Mix all ingredients and let stand 2 hours Stir once in a while. Drain and rinse.
Add 1 1/2 cups sugar, stir to dissolve; add 1 1/2 cups vinegar, mix and put in freezer cartons or jars and put in freezer.
Let stand 1 week before using.

title: coffee cake(diabetic recipe)
directions: Spray spring-form pan with vegetable spray.
Combine ingredients, except apple.
Spread in pan.
Arrange apple slices around outside edge of dough.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Thaw potatoes and pat dry.
Spread rolls on the bottom and up the sides of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer sausage, half of eggs, onion, pepper and then other half of eggs. Put cheese on top.
Bake for 50 or 60 minutes.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown meat; drain off excess fat.
Layer ingredients in a 9 x 13-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Combine macaroni, eggs, milk, salt, pepper and cheese in a bowl. Spoon into a 2-quart casserole. Dot with margarine.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until set. Yields 4 servings.

title: cheese pie
directions: Place one pie crust on cookie sheet sprayed with Pam.
Slice the Mexican Velveeta cheese thin and place on uncooked crust, leaving about an inch around edge.
On top of Velveeta, place the Montery Jack cheese, sliced thin.
Layer the green chilies and pinto beans on top of cheese.
Top with second pie crust and seal the edges.
Beat an egg and brush the top crust.

title: split lemon cake
directions: Make cake as directed using 8 or 9 inch round pans.

title: spicy enchiladas
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown the ground meat; boil the chicken with onion and pepper.
Drain excess grease from ground meat and water from chicken.
Add hot links; mix well.
Heat enchilada sauce and refried beans.
Dip tortilla in sauce; spread refried beans on tortilla.
Add meat; sprinkle small amount of cheese and fold with seams side down.
Add remaining cheese on top and pour remaining sauce over top.
Bake until cheese melts.
If desired, sprinkle chopped olives, sour cream and guacamole (spicy or mild).
Bake at 350°.

title: eagle brand fruit cake
directions: Mix together all drained fruit and lemon juice.
Mix together Eagle Brand and Cool Whip.
Fold into fruit.
Pour into pie crust. Decorate with green or red cherries, according to season.

title: grandma's oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix eggs, raisins and vanilla and let stand for 1 hour.
Mix oleo and sugars.
Add eggs and raisins, then add remaining ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: jim's little ribs
directions: Prepare ribs by wiping with wet towel.
Place in single layer in shallow roasting pan.
Roast at 450° for 20 minutes, turning once.
Prepare basting sauce.
Mix all ingredients.
Remove ribs from oven.
Brush with sauce on both sides.
Return to oven.
Bake at 450° for 20 minutes longer or until tender.
Baste from time to time while baking.
Serves 4.

title: souper burger
directions: Brown beef and onion in shortening; stir to separate meat particles.
Add seasonings and soup.
Simmer 5 to 10 minutes to blend flavors.
Stir often.
Serve on buns.
Makes 6 servings.

title: swiss steak
directions: Salt and pepper steak, dip steak in flour and pound flour into steak with side of saucer, until it won't hold any more.
Heat oil in skillet and cut meat into serving size; brown.
Remove steak and place in small roasting pan.
Place tomatoes into skillet and heat through until thick.
Add small amount of flour, if necessary.
Place cut vegetables over meat and cover with thickened tomatoes.
Cover with foil.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: pineapple dessert
directions: Mix all ingredients together in baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour or until browned.
Yields 6 servings.

title: green enchiladas
directions: Fry ground beef and onions in large frying pan.
Add the 3 cans of soup and milk to meat mixture.
Mix well.
Stir in green chilies and simmer while preparing tortillas.
Dip tortillas in hot oil (or water) for a few seconds to soften.
After all tortillas are ready, spread bottom of baking dish with just enough meat mixture to cover bottom of dish.
Layer tortillas on top of this, overlapping tortillas.
Spoon more meat mixture over tortillas and sprinkle with cheese.
Put another layer of tortillas, meat and cheese.
Layer until all meat mixture is used, ending with meat and cheese.
Bake in oven at 350° until hot and bubbling.
(Chicken can be used instead of beef.)

title: corn souffle
directions: In a large skillet, saute onions and peppers in margarine. Add flour and cook until golden brown.
Remove from heat; blend in milk, salt and dry mustard.
Return to heat; bring to a boil. Remove from heat and add corn (drained) and egg (slightly beaten). Stir to blend.
Place in a baking dish; sprinkle paprika on top. Bake in 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: mozzarella-tomato canapes
directions: Place Mozzarella slice on cracker.
Sprinkle with some of chopped basil and top with tomato slice.
Repeat with remaining crackers.
Arrange on serving platter.
Serve at room temperature. Makes 12 appetizers.

title: marinated cole slaw
directions: Begin by shredding (not chopping) cabbage. Spread onions and bell peppers over top of cabbage. Sprinkle with sugar. In a saucepan, bring oil, vinegar and all the dry ingredients to a rolling boil. Pour over the cabbage. Mix thoroughly. Cool before serving. Serves 10.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown ground chuck and drain well.
In a large pan, mix tomato paste and tomato special with chopped mushrooms, chopped garlic and onion.
Stir in drained meat.
Simmer 2 to 4 hours.

title: ham and cabbage cajun style
directions: In a large frying pan place oil, sliced cabbage, cubed ham, sliced mushrooms, crushed red pepper, salt and pepper.
Cook on medium heat, uncovered, stirring occasionally.
Cook until cabbage is tender.
Add Louisiana hot sauce to taste, then cook another 5 minutes.
Serve hot.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni until tender.
Drain and add cheese and oleo. Blend well and add sour cream.
Pour into casserole dish and bake in 350°
oven for 10 minutes.

title: vanilla pudding dessert
directions: Bake cake mix in a greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan as directed on package.
Mix pudding until thickened and fold in drained pineapple.
Pour mixture over baked cake. Cover with Cool Whip and sprinkle with nuts. Can be made a day ahead.

title: rice cooker jambalaya
directions: Add all ingredients raw (do not cook before putting in cooker).
Season to taste.
Cook for about 45 minutes.

title: chocolate cream pie
directions: Heat water and Milnot until hot.
Mix 3/4 cup sugar, cocoa, flour and salt.
Add hot milk and cook until almost thick.
Beat egg yolks.
Pour 1/2 of mix in egg yolks.
Stir, pour back in pan and cook until thick.
Pour in a 9-inch baked pie shell.

title: melting moments
directions: Mix flour, cornstarch and sugar in bowl.
Blend in butter until a soft dough is formed.
If dough is too soft to handle, cover and chill.
Shape into 3/4-inch balls.
Roll in coconut. Place 1 1/2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheets.
Bake at 300° for 20 to 25 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: chocolate dessert
directions: Crush cookies into cake pan and pour hot butter over top. Cool.

title: african chow mein
directions: Brown celery and onions in butter.
Brown meat in small amount of fat.
Combine all ingredients and put in well-greased, large casserole.
Stir once during baking.
Bake for 2 hours at 325°. Makes 8 servings.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Saute onion and ground meat until brown; drain.
Add Ranch Style beans, salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Simmer on low.
Line a greased casserole dish with 6 corn tortillas, pour meat and bean mixture on top.
Add Velveeta cheese slices.
Add remaining tortillas.
Mix cream of celery soup and Ro-Tel tomatoes in separate bowl.
Pour on top of casserole and bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: hobo's
directions: Put hamburger patty on foil slice onion, carrots, and potato and put on top of hamburger patty.
Salt and pepper.
Wrap in foil and bake 1 hour at 350 degrees.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Prepare pudding according to directions on box but use only 3 cups of milk for 2 packages.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Line a 9x 13-inch baking dish with graham crackers.
Pour half of the pudding mixture over crackers.
Place another layer of graham crackers over the pudding mixture and cover with the remaining pudding mixture.
Then top with a final layer of graham crackers. Place frosting in microwave for a few seconds to soften and spread over top layer of graham crackers.
Refrigerate overnight before serving.

title: sugar-free punch
directions: All juices and Sprite should be sugar-free.

title: caesar salad
directions: Wash romaine; remove outside leaves.
Break the tender leaves crosswise into pieces about 1-inch wide.
Store in plastic bag in fridge until ready to use.
When ready to serve, place romaine in large wooden bowl.
In a small mixing bowl, combine seasonings, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce, sugar, oil, vinegar and 3 anchovy fillets which have been mashed or minced.
Mix thoroughly. Break coddled egg over greens, then pour salad dressing over all and toss lightly.
Serve immediately on chilled salad plates.
Top each serving with 2 anchovy fillets.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a bowl and refrigerate.
Serve with assorted crackers or chips.

title: cut-a-shape cookies
directions: In large mixing bowl, mix first four ingredients with wooden spoon or fork until creamy.
Then fold in the next three ingredients until well mixed.
Divide into 2 balls and chill for 1/2 hour.
Roll out on pastry sheet lightly dusted with flour. Roll dough 1/8-inch thick.
Cut out and place about 1 1/2 inches apart on lightly oiled cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes, depending on your oven.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Butter in cold skillet; add garlic, sugar, salt and pepper. Add meat and brown; drain.
Add tomato sauce.
Simmer uncovered for 20 minutes.
Cook spaghetti.
Combine sour cream, cream cheese and onion.
Place spaghetti in greased 13 x 9-inch casserole dish. Top with cream cheese mixture and then meat mixture.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese over top.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: peanut clusters
directions: In microwave or double boiler, melt the chocolate chips, almond bark and a small amount of paraffin.
Add the Spanish peanuts.
Drop onto waxed paper; allow to cool.

title: reuben appetizers
directions: Place bread slices on cookie sheet.
Add corned beef, sauerkraut, dressing and cheese.
Broil about 6 inches away from heat for 2 to 3 minutes or until cheese melts.
Garnish with olive slice or tomato slice.
Serves 30.

title: the best chocolate chip cookies in the world
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Place length of foil on flat surface.
In large bowl, beat shortening, brown sugar, milk and vanilla on medium speed of electric mixer until well blended.
Add egg; beat well.
Stir together flour, salt and baking soda.
Gradually add to sugar mixture, beating on low speed just until blended.
Stir in chocolate chips.

title: stuffed green peppers(microwave)
directions: Saute hamburg, onion and garlic until onions are soft and clear.
Mix, in a medium bowl, beef mix, rice, tomato sauce, basil, salt and pepper.
Remove tops, pulp and seeds from peppers.
Fill each one with a fourth of mixture.
Place in an 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Microwave at High 10 to 15 minutes or until peppers are tender and rice is rehydrated.
Top with cheese during last minute of cooking.
Stand 3 minutes.
(I pour an additional 8 ounces tomato sauce over peppers before cooking.)

title: marinated green beans
directions: Combine sour cream and Italian dressing.
Add beans, tomato and onion.
Chill 3 to 4 hours.
Serve in lettuce, if desired.

title: sour cream noodle casserole
directions: Mix onions, salt and pepper with hamburger.
Heat last 5 ingredients.
When hot, add Velveeta cheese until melted.
Mix all together.
If too thick, add more milk.
Bake at 350° until bubbling hot.
Last, place more cheese slices on top to melt.
One batch makes 1 roaster full!

title: chicken ala king
directions: Saute green pepper and mushrooms in margarine.
When cooked, add sherry and chicken.
Add cream sauce.
Season to taste.
Just before serving, add egg yolks beaten in small amount of cream sauce.
Simmer for 1/2 minute.
Do not boil.
After egg yolks are added, serve over hot toast.
Serves 4.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Thaw
shrimp,
if
frozen.
Remove
shells
and devein. Gently pat
dry with a paper towel.
In a large skillet, melt butter over medium heat; add onions, garlic, lemon peel, lemon juice, salt
and hot pepper sauce.
Cook until boiling point, add	shrimp and cook for about 5 minutes or until shrimp turns pink.
Serve with hot cooked rice, top with parsley and lemon peel.
Yield: 4 servings.

title: roast chicken with herbs
directions: Preheat oven to 450°. Cut chicken in

half. Arrange in roasting pan, skin side up. Combine butter, lemon juice, oregano, rosemary, sage, salt and pepper in a small bowl and mix well. Brush chicken with this mixture and bake for 25 to 30 minutes. Then you may want to broil 6-inches from heat for 3 minutes.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix chicken, eggs, pickles and chopped seasonings and season to taste.
(Food processor may be used, but don't chop too fine.) Add broth and enough mayonnaise to get a spreading consistency. Allow to chill at least 2-3 hours for flavors to blend.
Spread on sandwiches or stuff into tomatoes or scooped out cucumbers for a refreshing summer lunch.

title: molasses butter ball cookies
directions: In mixing bowl, beat butter or margarine on medium speed of the electric mixer for 30 seconds.
Add molasses and beat until fluffy.
Add flour to butter mixture.
Beat at low speed until well blended.
Stir in nuts, using about 1 tablespoon dough for each.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased baking sheet. Bake in a 325° oven for about 20 minutes.
Remove to wire rack to cool, when cookies are cool gently roll them in powdered sugar to coat.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: poor man's fruitcake
directions: Measure first 8 ingredients into a large saucepan and simmer together over low heat for 5 minutes.
Cool.
Sift flour, baking powder and baking soda together.
Add to first mixture.
Fold in nuts and candied fruit.
Pour into 2 loaf pans that have been greased and lined with wax paper or into a prepared tube pan. Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours, until cake tests done.
If raisins and fruit on top of cake begin to brown too much, cover with foil.
Serve plain or frosted or with a hard sauce or lemon sauce.

title: chicken stir-fry
directions: Combine 1/4 c. orange juice and cornstarch; mix well.
Stir in chicken, cover and chill for at least 2 hours.

title: easy fruit pudding
directions: Spread 1 can, 20 to 22 ounces, fruit pie filling in 8-inch square dish.
Microwave at High 7 minutes.
In small bowl, combine 1 box 1 layer cake mix, 2 tablespoons sugar, 1 teaspoon cinnamon and 1/2 cup nuts.
Cut in 1/4 cup butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Sprinkle over fruit.
Microwave on High 10 to 12 minutes.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Pull cauliflower and broccoli into flowerets.
Combine with green pepper and onions.

title: blackberry dumplings
directions: In a large pot, combine berries, 1 cup sugar, 1/4 teaspoon salt and lemon extract.
Bring to a boil, lower heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Meanwhile, in bowl, combine flour, baking powder, nutmeg and remaining sugar and salt.
Add milk, stir until just mixed (dough will be thick).
Drop by tablespoonfuls into mounds onto hot blackberry mixture.
Cover tightly and simmer 15 minutes.
Spoon into serving dishes.
Serve with cream.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: rice au gratin supreme
directions: Combine first four ingredients in a large bowl; mix well. Combine soup, mayonnaise, 1 cup cheese and milk.
Stir into rice mixture.
Spoon mixture into lightly greased, 2-quart casserole. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with remaining 1 cup of cheese and bake 5 more minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Cream butter and sugar. Add potatoes and eggs.
Mix well.

title: meat loaf
directions: Soak bread cubes in the milk.
Mix hamburger and onion together.
Add bread cubes after they have absorbed all the milk. Add salt and pepper to taste.
Mix well and put in loaf pan.

title: rice krispie date roll
directions: Melt margarine.
Add sugar.
Mix well.
Add dates; stir in vanilla.
Remove from heat; stir in Rice Krispies and dates.
Form into balls and roll in powdered sugar.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash mushrooms under cold running water and dry on paper towel.
Brush outside of caps lightly with butter; place on greased baking pan or cookie sheet.
Fill each cap with Spam spread.
Heat 5 to 8 minutes in 375° oven.

title: taco salad
directions: Toss all ingredients together in a large bowl.
Salsa can be kept to the side for individual use.

title: rice pilaf
directions: Cook onion, mushrooms, celery and garlic in butter. Stir in rice, bouillon, pepper and water. Bring to boil and reduce heat. Cover and simmer 15 minutes. Add bacon.

title: easy chocolate cherry cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix dry cake mix with diet cherry Coke and stir until smooth.
Spray a 9 x 13 cake pan with Pam.
Put batter in and follow baking instructions on box.
Unbelievably moist and low-fat.

title: po boy ice cream
directions: Finish filling ice cream can with milk.
Freeze.

title: basil grilled chicken
directions: Press 3/4 teaspoon pepper into the meaty sides of the chicken breasts.
Combine 1/3 cup melted butter and 1/4 cup chopped basil and then stir well.
Brush the chicken lightly with the melted butter mixture.
Combine 1/2 cup softened butter, 2 tablespoons basil, Parmesan cheese, garlic powder, salt and pepper in a bowl. Beat with an electric mixer at low speed until the mixture is well blended and smooth.

Transfer to small serving bowl and set aside. Grill chicken on an outdoor barbecue at medium temperature setting for 8 to 10 minutes on each side, basting frequently with remaining melted butter mixture.
Serve grilled chicken with the basil butter mixture and garnish with fresh basil sprigs.
This recipe makes 4 servings in an hour of preparation time.

title: cowboy stew
directions: Saute hamburg in skillet until brown.
Pour off fat.
In casserole dish, add browned hamburg.
Sprinkle some salt, pepper and garlic powder over hamburg.
Pour the jar of gravy over hamburg.
Spread can of veggies over that.
Now spread the mashed potatoes.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Real easy to make and very good.

title: slow cooked italian chicken
directions: Place the chicken in a slow cooker. In a bowl, combine the next 11 ingredients; pour over chicken. Cover and cook on low for 4 to 5 hours or until chicken juices run clear. Remove chicken pieces and keep warm. Pour cooking juices into a saucepan; skim fat. Combine flour and cold water until smooth; stir into juices. Bring to a boil. Cook and stir for 2 minutes or until thickened. Serve over chicken and noodles. Yields 4 servings.

title: pecan pie
directions: In large bowl, stir together first 5 ingredients until well blended.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into pastry shells.
Bake in a 350° oven for 50 to 55 minutes or until knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean.

title: black beans and rice
directions: Wash beans thoroughly.
Cover with water and put in large pot to soak overnight.
Drain beans and place in crock-pot with 3 to 4 cups of water.
Add all other ingredients, except the rice.
Cook on high for 1 hour, then cook 8 to 10 hours on low.
Remove bay leaf.
Cook rice according to directions on package.
Serve beans over rice.
Garnish as desired.
This is a low-fat, high fiber meal.

title: nick's favorite chicken enchiladas
directions: Mix chicken, soup, sour cream, scallions and, if desired, peppers.
Heat thoroughly.
Set aside.

title: christmas punch
directions: Mix well.
Add 1 1/2 quarts ginger ale, cold.
Pour over ice cubes (recipe below).

title: apple salad
directions: Blend together sugar and cream cheese.
Fold in Cool Whip, apples, nuts and snickers.
Refrigerate.

title: vicki's broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until almost tender.
Saute onion slightly. Combine all ingredients (except crackers) in a large baking dish; mix well.
Crush crackers and place on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Shape into long rolls and freeze until ready to cook.
Slice thin.
Bake at 350° on ungreased pans until light browned.

title: kaffee kuchen (coffee cake)
directions: Set aside the dough until it doubles in bulk.
After kneading, turn dough onto a floured board, roll out and put on a large baking sheet.
Cover with Strausseln Topping and let rise again. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown bacon, pour off half of the grease.
Add onion and garlic, cook until onion is tender.
Add ketchup, brown sugar, salt, mustard and vinegar.
Add drained beans.
Mix well and bake in a covered dish at 350° for 40 minutes.
Can add a little molasses.

title: cookie balls
directions: Make into balls and dip in chocolate.
Instead of using just Corn Flakes, you can also use half Rice Krispies.

title: butterfinger favorite
directions: Crush
candy
bars and set aside.
Pinch half the angel food cake into small pieces and spread into a long Pyrex pan. In another
bowl,
mix
butter, egg yolks and sugar.
Fold in whipped topping.
Mix
until
creamy.
Spread
whipped mixture over cake pieces.
Sprinkle 1/2 the crushed candy bars on
top
of cake.
Repeat process to make 2 layers.
Refrigerate.

title: raisin sauce
directions: Bring first four ingredients to a boil.
Mix remaining ingredients then add to first part and boil until thick.
Makes 3 cups.

title: party meatballs(serves 8 to 10)
directions: Combine beef, bread crumbs, soup mix and eggs in bowl. Mix well. Form into meatballs. Place uncooked meatballs in a glass 9 x 13 baking dish. Set aside while preparing sauce.

title: microwave divinity candy
directions: In 3-quart bowl, combine sugar, corn syrup and water.
Cook on High for 8 minutes or until mixture is clear; stir.
Cook on High for 6 1/2 to 8 minutes longer or until syrup reaches 260°.
Do not leave candy thermometer in oven.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Combine beans, soup, milk and half of onion rings.
Pour into casserole dish.
Cover with remaining onion rings.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: roast pork barbecue
directions: Mix catsup, water, Worcestershire sauce, onion, sugar, dry mustard, salt, black pepper and cayenne pepper in bowl.
Pour over roast in roasting pan.
Roast, covered, at 350° for 4 hours.
Let stand until cool; drain.
Bone and pull roast apart; return to pan.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour longer.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: vanilla or chocolate shake
directions: Combine all ingredients in container of an electric blender. Top with cover; process until smooth.
Serve immediately.
To make chocolate shake, use 4 1/2 cups chocolate nonfat yogurt.
Add 1/3 cup chocolate syrup.
Omit vanilla.
Contains 162 calories per serving.

title: impossible pumpkin pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 1 1/4-inch or 10 x 1 1/2-inch pie plate.
Beat all ingredients until smooth, 1 minute in blender on high or 2 minutes with hand mixer.
Pour into pie plate and bake until knife inserted in center comes out clean, 50 to 55 minutes.

title: spanish sauce for omelet
directions: Melt margarine in a heavy 2 quart saucepan.
Add salt.
Saute onion until transparent.
Add bell pepper slices over onions. Saute on low 3 to 4 minutes.
Drain the tomatoes.
Reserve liquid for paste.
Add bay leaves.
Add drained tomatoes.
Add cloves. (Preferably in a small stainless steel tea bag for easy removal.) Simmer about 20 minutes, covered.
Prepare flour paste from reserved tomato liquid (add water to make 1/2 cup) and 1/4 cup flour.
Remove bay leaves and cloves.
Add most of paste in pockets.
Stir.
Test for thickness.
It should fall off a tilted spoon easily.
Add more paste if it runs off the spoon like a juice.
Bring to boil.
Cook the flour for 1 minute.
Stir continuous.
Adjust salt to taste.
Enough for an 8 egg omelet.

title: graham treats
directions: Melt chocolate in double boiler (don't let water touch boiler).
Pour over dry mix.
Drop over wax paper.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Mix together and put in unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: california veg.  pie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In skillet, brown beef and onion, drain and stir in salt and pepper; set aside.
Saute zucchini and green pepper in the margarine for 5 minutes, stirring frequently.
Stir in dill weed.
Separate dough and press over bottom and sides of 9-inch pie pan, or cake pan.
Spoon meat mixture over crust. Sprinkle 1/2 cup cheese over meat.
Spread zucchini mixture evenly over the meat.
Top with tomato slices.
Bake 10 minutes.
Sprinkle remaining cheese over tomatoes and bake an additional 15 minutes. Cool 5 minutes before serving.
Garnish with sour cream and alfalfa sprouts, if desired.
Serves 6.

title: jello salad
directions: Add 1 (20 ounce) can crushed pineapple, drained and 1 can mandarin oranges, drained.
Mix well.
Chill several hours.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Make patties big and fat and place in large skillet filled with mushroom soup.
Mix with water or milk.
Place one slice of onion on each patty and one slice of cheese on top of the onion. Cook at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate eclair delight
directions: Combine milk and pudding until smooth.
Stir in Cool Whip. Refrigerate and line bottom of square pan with 1 layer of graham crackers.
Spoon and smooth on pudding and Cool Whip.
Place another layer of crackers, then pudding, etc., ending with a layer of crackers.
Mix syrup and powdered sugar together and pour on top of crackers and pudding.
Let sit in refrigerator 24 hours.

title: quick oreo dessert
directions: Roll cookies fine (filling also).
Mix in Cool Whip and nuts. Chill at least one hour.
