title: turkey salad
directions: Tear lettuce in large bowl; add chopped celery, grapes, turkey pieces and seasonings.
Toss together with mayonnaise.

title: chili
directions: Heat oil in a skillet; add meat, garlic and onion.
Cook, stirring slowly until meat browns.
Add remaining ingredients. Fold gently.
Cover and simmer until chili is hot.

title: chocolate divine
directions: Soften the gelatin in the water.
Mix cocoa and milk.
Heat over boiling water.
Add softened gelatin and liquid artificial sweetener.
Stir until dissolve; remove mixture from heat.
Add vanilla.
Combine ice water and dry milk in bowl and beat until mixture is thick.
Beat gelatin until smooth and add to whipped milk.
Turn into pan sprayed with Pam.
Chill until firm.
Yield: 5 servings.
Carbohydrate 6 g, protein 4 g, fat .2 g, calories 40. One serving = 1/2 skim milk exchange.

title: italian chicken
directions: Sprinkle breasts with seasonings, then cover with cheese. Fold breasts over.
Dip in egg or milk, then roll in bread crumbs. Bake in 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: parmesan potatoes
directions: Put flour, cheese, salt and pepper in a plastic bag.
Pare and cut potatoes into halves.
Moisten and place in bag.
Shake bag until potatoes are covered.
In baking dish, melt 1 stick oleo. Place potatoes in melted oleo and bake at 350° for 1 hour, turning once on the half hour.

title: no bake peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine sugar, butter, flour and milk.
Bring to full boil. Boil 3 minutes hard.
Remove and add the rest.
Drop onto wax paper until cool.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients, adding cornmeal mix last. Bake in a 9 x 13 pan at 400° for 25 minutes. Serve while hot.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cocoa together.
Combine milk, eggs, oleo and vanilla.
Mix all together and cook until thick.
Pour into baked pie shells and top with meringue and brown.
Use one or two pie shells.

title: sloppy chocolate cake
directions: Mix all ingredients except water; add water last.
Mixture will be thin.
Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: jared's dip
directions: Heat together in crock-pot.
Serve with chips.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Cut all fruit into small pieces and chop nuts. Dust fruit and nuts with 1/2 cup flour. Cream Crisco and sugar. Add eggs, then bourbon, flour and spices. Mix well. Pour over fruit and nuts; mix. Drop
on greased cookie sheet with teaspoon. Bake at 300° for 20 minutes.

title: shrimp and macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on package.
Cool and blend mayonnaise and mustard.
Add other ingredients and mix well.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Tip:
These pickles are wonderful as a side dish for fish, barbecues, picnics or Sunday night sandwich suppers.

title: isabuzzer bars
directions: Mix the ingredients together and press into square 8 x 8-inch pan sprayed with Pam.
Bake in a 375° oven for 20 minutes or until golden on top.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni in 2 quarts salted water for 6 to 8 minutes; drain.
Cube (small) cheese and oleo.
Crush crackers into fine crumbs.
Mix together with evaporated milk into macaroni.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
I think pepper gives it the extra taste.
Pour into a greased 8 to 9-inch square baking pan.
Bake in a 350° oven until brown.

title: salsa
directions: Mix all together.
Boil to desired thickness.
Put in jars. Seal.
Pressure or cold pack for 10 minutes.

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix sugar and cinnamon together in a large Baggie.
Cut each biscuit into quarters.
Shake biscuit pieces in the sugar and cinnamon; layer in well-greased tube pan.
(Optional:
Sprinkle nuts between layers.)
Usually makes 3 complete layers.
Melt butter in a saucepan.
Add brown sugar; boil for 1 minute and pour over the top layer.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool 15 to 20 minutes before removing from pan.

title: aunt alice's lemon-lime punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a punch bowl.
Add lemon slices for color.
Very good punch!

title: bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in water; sprinkle with the 1 teaspoon sugar. Combine milk and butter; whisk in sugar and salt.
Whisk in the raised yeast (should be to the top of a 1-cup measure).
In a mixing bowl, mix the bread flour with the yeast and milk mixture. Now, mix in the all-purpose flour; knead mixture for approximately 2 minutes.
Put dough in a well-greased bowl; cover with plastic wrap.
Set over a pot of hot water; let rise 55 minutes.
Take out; knead and separate.
Form into 2 loaves.
Put into well oiled loaf pans; set over hot water to rise (they should be above the pans, approximately 60 minutes).
Bake in a 400° oven for 10 minutes; turn oven to 325° and bake until done, approximately 15 minutes.
Cool out of pan on a wire rack.

title: herman starter(friendship sourdough)
directions: Begin cycle over with days
1 through 4.
Stir once daily. If not used on tenth day, add 1 teaspoon sugar and repeat every tenth day until used.
Remaining batter can be used or give 1 cup to a friend with instructions about feeding and care of Herman.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all together and pour into 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
In last 15 minutes, put more grated cheese and crushed Ritz crackers on top to brown.

title: glaze for cakes
directions: Mix together and bring to boil. Pour over cake while warm.

title: broccoli cheese casserole
directions: Saut onion in butter and combine with cooked rice and broccoli.
Heat soup and cheese in double boiler (so it won't burn).
Mix all together in casserole and bake for about 20 minutes at 350°.

title: tunnel of fudge cake
directions: Preheat oven at 350° for baking in a Teflon-coated Bundt pan. Cream butter in a large mixing bowl, then add the eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add sugar gradually. Continue creaming mixture until it is light and fluffy.
Stir in flour, frosting mix and pecans.
Pour batter into greased Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 65 to 70 minutes.
Cool 1 hour; remove from pan and let it cool 1 hour more.

title: rhubarb custard bars
directions: In a bowl, combine the flour and sugar; cut in butter until the mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Press into a greased 13 x 9 x 2 inch baking pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 10 minutes. Meanwhile, for filling, combine sugar and flour in a bowl.
Whisk in cream and eggs.
Stir in the rhubarb.
Pour over crust.
Bake at 350 degrees for 40-45 minutes or until custard is set.
Cool.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix onions, egg, milk and meal.
Drop by spoonful into hot shortening (also can be shortening left over from frying fish). Shortening should be over an inch deep.
Turn once when browned. Remove to platter spread with paper towels to drain excess shortening.
Serve with fried fish or any meat.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cut shortening in flour (like pie crust).
Mix remaining ingredients together and add to flour mixture.
Roll out on floured cutting board.
Cut out shapes.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: barbecue brisket
directions: Cover brisket with spices.
Wrap in heavy foil overnight. Change foil for baking.
Bake at 350° on top shelf with pan of water underneath.
Cook 4 hours.
Bring to boil vinegar, sugar, ketchup, 1 teaspoon mustard and onion salt; add steak sauce and soy sauce.
Change foil.
Pour mixture over brisket and cook 1 hour.

title: mini cheese cake
directions: Cream first four ingredients.
Add eggs and beat well.
In mini muffin pan, put in cupcake liners, put 1 vanilla wafer in liner. Fill 2/3 full with creamed mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until set.
Cool.
Refrigerate.
Top with cherry or blueberry pie filling or fresh fruit before serving.

title: double decker jello blocks
directions: In large bowl, combine Knox gelatine with flavored gelatin. Add boiling water; stir until completely dissolved.
Stir in cream.
Pour into shallow baking dish.
Chill until firm.
To serve, cut into one-inch squares.
Recommended pan size is 9 x 9-inch.

title: burnt sugar cake
directions: Heat 1/2 cup sugar and boiling water until mixture measures 1/2 cup.
Cool.
Cream together 1 cup sugar and butter.
Add vanilla. Mix well egg yolks and milk.
Add syrup mixture and dry mixture. Fold in beaten egg whites.
Bake in 375° oven for 30 to 35 minutes in either 8 x 12-inch pan or 2 layer pans.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix and chill for two hours.
Serve with any raw vegetables.

title: easy potato au gratin
directions: Combine potatoes and celery in greased baking dish.
Blend soup and mustard.
Pour over vegetables.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: sausage rolls
directions: Work all together well; roll in ball.
Cook at 350° until done. Grease a cookie sheet lightly.
Let the sausage get soft before working it.
These freeze nicely.

title: zippy crisp chicken bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brush chicken with salad dressing. Coat with combined crumbs and cheese.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Place in 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Bake 1 hour or until tender.
Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: microwave quick fudge
directions: Pour sugar into large glass microwave-safe bowl.
Add margarine, milk and cocoa; do not stir.
Place in microwave oven 2 1/2 minutes until margarine melts.
Take bowl out and add nuts and vanilla.
Stir well.
Pour into 8-inch dish.
Place in freezer 10 to 15 minutes, then cut into squares and serve.

title: teriyaki chicken wings
directions: Combine ingredients.
Pour over chicken wings.
Marinate 6 hours.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes or grill on open fire basting frequently.
Or put in crock-pot on low and cook.

title: chicken divan
directions: Boil chicken in salt and pepper water.
Let cool.
Cook broccoli.
Melt butter in saucepan.
Add flour and 2 cups chicken broth.
Salt and pepper.
Remove from heat.
Add wine and cream. Skin and debone chicken.
Place broccoli in bottom of baking dish (9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish works well!).
Add 1/2 of chicken, then 1/2 of sauce.
Add rest of chicken.
Add 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese to sauce.
Pour on top.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.
Cook until heated at 350°.
Broil to golden brown (15 to 20 minutes).

title: gingerbread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly spray an 8-inch square baking pan with vegetable oil.
In a large bowl, blend together molasses, brown sugar, oil and spices.
Stir in boiling water.
Mix in flour; set aside.
In a small bowl, dissolve baking soda in 2 tablespoons hot water; stir to mix well.
Add to batter.
Bake in prepared baking pan 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and slice into 12 equal portions.
Serve warm.

title: almond puff pastry
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cut 1/2 cup butter into 1 cup flour. Sprinkle 2 tablespoons water over mixture; mix with fork.
Round into ball; divide in half.
On ungreased baking sheet, pat each half into a strip, 12 x 3-inches.
Strips should be about 3 inches apart.

title: creole pork chops
directions: Sprinkle pork chops with "Pork and Veal Magic."
Heat oil in skillet over medium-high heat.
Brown pork chops and transfer to a plate.
Chop onion and bell pepper in a food processor and add to skillet and stir until golden.
Add garlic and cook the mixture for 1 minute.
Add 1/4 cup water and tomatoes.
Stir occasionally for 15 minutes. Add the chops and any juices.
Add salt and pepper to taste and simmer the chops for 8 to 10 minutes or until tender and no longer pink.
Serve with rice and spoon the sauce over the rice.
I added "Pork Magic" to the original recipe.

title: sour cream rolls
directions: Mix until moist.
Divide equally into cupcake wells.
Melt margarine; pour over batter.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes at 375° or until brown.
Makes 12 rolls.
These can be frozen.

title: skyline dip
directions: In a small casserole dish, layer the cream cheese, chili, then cheese.
Microwave for 4 minutes.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix together the sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning mix; set aside.
In a 9-inch square casserole dish, layer in the following order:
Refried beans (spread to cover bottom), guacamole, green onions, black olives, cherry tomatoes, sour cream mixture and Cheddar cheese.
Chill; serve with tortilla chips.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Stir together Cool Whip and Eagle Brand milk.
Then add pineapple, nuts and lemon juice.
Stir together.
Pour into graham cracker crusts and chill.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Follow directions on package for pudding, except use 3 cups milk for the 2 packages.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Line bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan with whole graham crackers, then the rest of the pudding mixture.
Next a third layer of graham crackers, then spread on chocolate frosting.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: peanut butter cake
directions: Mix peanut butter with shortening and add sugar.
Then add vanilla.
Next, add eggs (one at a time).
Next add milk and flour.
Cook in oven at 350° for 35 or 40 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Place in Pam-sprayed 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: no peek chicken
directions: Mix together cream of mushroom soup, cream of chicken soup, water, parsley and rice.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Arrange pieces of chicken on top of mixture. Sprinkle onion soup over top and cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.
Do not peek, it will be done at that time.

title: cocoa teabread(kakao tebrod)
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and cocoa.
Set aside.
Cream butter and add sugar, creaming well.
Add 1 beaten egg.
Blend in dry ingredients.
Chill 2 hours.
Divide dough into 4 parts on ungreased baking sheet.
Flatten with fork into a strip 1/4-inch thick.
Beat 1 egg with 1 tablespoon cold water; brush lightly over strips.
Sprinkle chopped almonds and sugar over dough.
Bake in hot oven at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes until set. Cut in 1-inch bars and remove from baking sheet.

title: best pancakes i ever ate
directions: Mix oil, egg and milk.
Sift dry ingredients and add to previous mixture.
Thin the mixture to desired consistency with milk using a whisk.
Fry on hot griddle at medium heat.
Makes approximately 12 to 14 (3-inch) pancakes.

title: french breakfast muffins
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 12 muffin cups.
Mix thoroughly the shortening, 1/2 cup sugar and the egg.
Stir in flour, baking powder, salt and nutmeg, alternately with milk.
Fill muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.

title: ritz cracker dessert
directions: Mix crumbled crackers, margarine and chopped nuts; reserve 1/2 cup.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix pudding and milk; stir in ice cream.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup reserved topping.
Freeze.

title: 5 minute fudge
directions: Mix together
milk, sugar and salt in a saucepan.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture comes to a boil.
Then boil five
minutes
stirring constantly, remove from heat and add marshmallows,
nuts,
chocolate
and vanilla.
Stir until marshmallows melt.
Pour into buttered 8-inch pan and cool.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Drain and wash shrimp.
Mash with fork.
Blend with softened cream cheese.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Chill.
Serve with bread sticks or chips.

title: aaron's grilled chicken
directions: Combine oil, lemon juice and lemon pepper in a recloseable plastic bag or shallow platter.
Add chicken breasts to plastic bag and coat well with oil mixture.
Allow to marinate for 30 minutes in refrigerator, turning once after 15 minutes.
Grill over low flame, 7 to 8 minutes per side, basting with any leftover marinade. When chicken juice runs yellow, not pink, meat is done.

title: pizza melba rounds
directions: Combine the ground chuck and sausage in large skillet.
Cook until browned.
Drain well.
Stir in tomato sauce, Italian seasoning and Tabasco.
Add cheese in small chunks.
Cook over low heat until cheese melts, stirring constantly.
Spoon small mounds of mixture onto Melba rounds.
At this point, the rounds can be frozen on a baking sheet and then transferred to plastic bags for cooking later.
When ready to serve, remove from freezer and place on baking sheet.
Bake at 400 degrees until bubbly.

Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese over top of each round before baking. No baking is necessary if you do not freeze the rounds. Simply sprinkle the Mozzarella cheese over the top of the rounds while the filling is hot.
Makes about 3 1/2 doz.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Sift dry ingredients into a large bowl; cut in shortening with a pastry blender.
Add buttermilk and yeast mixture; stir until thoroughly moistened. Turn dough out onto floured board and knead 1 or 2 minutes.
(No rising is required.)
Roll dough out to 1/2-inch thickness and cut with a 2-inch biscuit cutter.
Place on ungreased baking sheet; brush with melted butter and bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: refrigerator cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars.
Add eggs and spices.
Add sifted dry ingredients.
Add peanut butter.
Add nuts; form into a roll. Wrap in wax paper.
Refrigerate several hours.
Slice 1/8-inch to 1/4-inch thick.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes or until done.

title: lemon crinkles
directions: In mixing bowl, cream shortening with 1 1/4 cups sugar and salt.
Add egg and extract.
Combine thoroughly.
Gradually beat in evaporated milk.
Add dry ingredients and beat thoroughly, scraping sides of bowl often.
Chill 60 minutes.
With wet hands, shape into 1-inch balls and roll in sugar.
Place on greased cookie sheet about 2 inches apart.
Bake at 350° for about 10 to 12 minutes or until cookies are golden brown.
Remove from oven. Makes about 5 dozen.

title: scalloped oysters
directions: Drain oysters; reserve liquid.
Remove any shell particles. Set oysters aside.
Lightly toss 1 cup of crumbs with melted butter.
Add enough cream or milk to reserved oyster liquid to yield 2 cups liquid.
Stir in salt and pepper.
Line a shallow, buttered 2-quart casserole with 1 cup of unbuttered crumbs. Arrange 2 cups of the oysters on the crumbs.
Pour 1 cup liquid over all.
Sprinkle with 1/2 of the chopped onion.
Dot with 1/2 of the butter.
Repeat procedure.
Top with the buttered crumbs. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until thoroughly heated.

title: chocolate almond zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until lemon colored.
Beat in sugar and oil.
Stir chocolate, vanilla and zucchini into egg mixture.
Sift flour with salt, cinnamon, baking powder and baking soda.
Stir into zucchini mixture.
Add almonds.
Mix thoroughly.
Bake at 350° for one hour in 2 well-greased loaf pans.
Turn out onto rack.

title: shrimp spread
directions: Blend well and spread in pie pan all ingredients, except shrimp and chili sauce.
Cover with 1/2 bottle chili or cocktail sauce and crumble baby shrimp over top.
Refrigerate and serve with crackers.

title: barbecued hot dogs
directions: Split hot dogs lengthwise.
Place in shallow pan.
Make sauce of other ingredients and cook for 30 minutes.
Pour over hot dogs and cook, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken pie
directions: Mix soup and broth together.
Pour over chicken that has been placed in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place cut up boiled eggs over this.
Mix together flour and milk.
Add butter (or oil). This makes a thin batter on top.
Bake until golden brown at 400°.

title: mayo delight
directions: Spread mayo on slice of bread and fold over.
Eat middle out and feed crust to doggie.

title: pecan pie
directions: Heat oven to 375° (quick med).
Beat eggs, sugar, salt, butter and corn syrup together with rotary beater.
Mix in pecan halves. Pour into pastry.
Line pie pan.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes or until set and pastry is nicely brown.
Cool.
Serve cold or slightly warm.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Beat egg whites stiff.
Mix in with spoon pecans, chips, sugar and vanilla.
Line cookie sheet with foil and drop mixture by teaspoon onto foil.
TURN OVEN OFF!! Place cookie sheet in oven and leave overnight.

title: turkey noodle casserole
directions: Mix all but margarine and bread crumbs in a 1 1/2-quart greased casserole dish.
Bake in a 400° oven for 25 minutes.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix ingredients.
Use 2 teaspoons to a cup of water.

title: onion-beef-cheese dip
directions: Mix all together and serve.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Mix 1/2 cup peanut butter with chocolate.
Melt 1 1/2 cups peanut butter in a measuring cup in saucepan of water.
Cut cupcake paper; place in pans.
Put 2 tablespoons of chocolate in cups; let cool.
Put 1 to 2 tablespoons of peanut butter on top, 1 tablespoon on to just cover peanut butter.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Cook carrots until almost tender.
Drain and set aside.
Chop onion and melt 3 tablespoons butter and salt.
Add cream of celery soup, salt and pepper.
Add around 3/4 can of water.
Heat until warm.
Place carrots in casserole pan.
Pour soup mixture over. On top, add Mozzarella cheese.
Melt 1/2 cup butter.
Pour over bread stuffing, then put on top of Mozzarella cheese.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fruit dip
directions: Layer ingredients on plate.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix sugar, margarine and cream. Add egg and flavoring.
Mix until thoroughly blended.

title: hot tamale dip
directions: Mash tamales.
Combine all ingredients and heat until cheese melts.
Serve with chips.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Cream sugar, butter and flour.
Add eggs, buttermilk and vanilla.
Bake in unbaked pie crust at 425° for 10 minutes, then at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Saute onion, garlic and red pepper until soft.
Add ground beef and brown.
In a casserole dish, add soup, tomato sauce and seasonings.
Add meat mixture and stir well.
If you are using left over cooked meat, just add it to the soup; do not cook again.
Mash the potatoes and spoon over the soup and meat mixture around the dish, leaving a hole in the middle to let steam escape.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes; the potatoes should be browned and mixture bubbling.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Wash and separate cauliflower.
Fry bacon until crisp; drain and crumble on top of cauliflower.
To the bacon drippings, add remaining ingredients.
Mix together and pour over cauliflower and bacon.
Chill for 1/2 hour before serving.

title: herb loaf
directions: Mix flour, salt, baking powder and herbs.
Cut butter into small pieces and rub into dry ingredients.
Stir in the sugar; add eggs to the milk and stir into mixture.
Mix well; put into a greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: carrot bread
directions: Sift flour, sugar, cinnamon, baking soda and salt.
Beat eggs well.
Stir in shredded carrots and oil into eggs.
Add flour mixture and chopped nuts.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions on box.
Mix all other ingredients together and toss with the macaroni.

title: cheese 'n broccoli salad
directions: In large bowl, toss together all ingredients until well combined.
Cover; refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Serves 6.

title: buttermilk breakfast scones
directions: Stir together flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Stir in dates.
In a small bowl, mix buttermilk, egg and vanilla.
Add buttermilk mixture to flour mixture and stir to combine.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Grease bottom only of a 10 x 14-inch baking pan (don't use a smaller pan).
Mix pecans and coconut and sprinkle in bottom of pan.
Prepare cake mix per package directions.
Pour over top of nuts and coconut.
Mix remaining four ingredients and dab over cake batter.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: spanish rice
directions: In skillet over medium heat, cook bacon until crisp, stirring often.
With slotted spoon, remove to paper towels.
In drippings, over medium heat, cook green pepper, onion and garlic until tender crisp.
Remove to bowl.
In same skillet, brown ground beef.
Add tomatoes with liquid, rice, water, seasonings and green pepper mixture.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes until rice is tender.
Stir occasionally.
Sprinkle with cooked bacon.

title: quick lasagna
directions: You will need 9 x 13-inch baking pan.

title: wild mushroom gougere
directions: Boil mushrooms for 10 minutes, reserve mushrooms and add butter to water used for cooking mushrooms.
When butter melts, add flour and mix until ball forms off the heat.
Add eggs, one at a time and beat well after each egg.
Mix in cheese and reserved chopped mushrooms.
Place on cookie sheet in two thin loaves and bake in 400° oven for 35 to 45 minutes.
Serve hot or room temperature, sliced.
Omit mushrooms entirely for traditional gougere.

title: death row salsa
directions: Add all
ingredients in a bowl, mixing well.
Chill and serve. This is best if used the same day.

title: hot percolator punch
directions: Pour first 3 ingredients into a 12 cup percolator.
Place remaining ingredients in percolator basket.
Perk through complete cycle of electric percolator.
Serve with cinnamon sticks if desired.

title: apache cheese bread
directions: Cut the top off bread, reserving top, scoop out the inside. Combine remaining ingredients and mix well.
This will be a very stiff mixture.
Fill the bread with the cheese mixture, replace the top and place on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Serve with tortilla chips or the bread you have scooped out.
To save half the baking time heat the cheese mixture in a microwavable bowl in your microwave until cheeses melt and are thoroughly heated.
Then pour into crust.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Mix sour cream, cream cheese, onions, olives, cheddar cheese and chiles. Spread on tortillas. Roll them up, jelly roll style. Wrap each roll in wax paper and refrigerate for several hours. Slice, like a jelly roll and serve. May have salsa on the side for dipping.

title: eggless, milkless, butterless cake
directions: Boil the sugar, water, shortening, raisins and apples together for 5 minutes. When cool, add the remaining ingredients.
Bake in a thick sheet in a slow oven.

title: zucchini nut loaf
directions: Mix bananas and sugar.
Use electric mixer; mix all dry ingredients together and add oil and eggs.
Add banana and sugar mixture and vanilla.
Stir in zucchini and nuts.
Grease and flour 2 loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Cool 10 minutes and turn out. Wrap in plastic wrap when cooled.

title: strawberry delite
directions: Break up angel food cake in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water, add in defrosted strawberries.
Pour mixture over cake.
Fold 8 ounces Cool Whip into cake mixture. Refrigerate overnight.
Top with 8 ounces Cool Whip to serve.
Can be cut into squares or spooned out.

title: mr. n's favorite brownie recipe
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Add eggs and butter and stir.
Mix in nuts and vanilla.
Pour into 9-inch square pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 minutes.

title: ginger cookies
directions: Mix shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and molasses.
Then add all other ingredients.
Dough will be real thick.
Make into balls. Roll in sugar and bake for about 8 to 10 minutes at about 350° or 375°.

title: yummy bars(cookies)
directions: Melt butter in a 15 1/2 x 11 x 2 1/2-inch jelly roll pan. Sprinkle German chocolate cake mix evenly over butter.
Then sprinkle miniature marshmallows over the cake mix.
Next, sprinkle butterscotch chips over marshmallows, and then coconut on top. Last, drizzle condensed milk over the top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli 5 minutes; drain. Combine soup, mayonnaise, beaten eggs, cheese and onion. Mix well and add broccoli. Put in greased baking dish. Sprinkle with crushed crackers. Dot with butter. Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: yummy potatoes
directions: Mix potatoes with the next 5 ingredients.
Pour potato mixture into greased baking dish.
Sprinkle on top more bacon bits, Parmesan cheese, minced onion, melted butter and paprika.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool 15 minutes before serving.

title: spanish rice
directions: Place mixture in large greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, leaving cover off last 15 minutes.
This may have meat added by using 1 pound browned ground beef and crumbling bacon over top.

title: kottbular(swedish meat balls)
directions: Stir bread crumbs into milk or water.
Mix well.
Beat in egg and onion.
Add salt, pepper, nutmeg and ground beef.
Mix thoroughly.
Divide meat mixture into 50 to 60 even portions. Shape into small balls.
Melt butter in skillet.
Add meat balls. Brown thoroughly, shaking pan occasionally to keep balls round. Add water.
Cover skillet.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Yields 50 to 60 small meat balls.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Place all in a large pot and bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer slowly over low heat at least an hour.
Remove lid and cook down to thickness desired.

title: pretzel dessert
directions: Mix chopped pretzels and melted butter. Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 400° for 10 minutes. Cool in refrigerator until set.

title: cindy's white peanut butter cookies
directions: Make a sandwich cookie out of peanut butter and the Ritz cracker.
Grate a block of almond bark into the top of a double boiler; melt on medium heat.
When almond bark has melted, dip a cookie in with a fork.
Bring cookie out, supported on the tongs of the fork.
Gently tap fork on the edge of the pan to remove excess almond bark.
Scrape bottom of fork tongs with another fork.
Place cookie on wax paper to dry; tap fork on top of cookie to make a pretty design.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix eggs, sour cream, salt, corn and oil.
Add corn meal, bell peppers, hot peppers and baking powder.
Grease pan.
Heat pan until hot.
Pour half of mixture in dish.
Sprinkle 1/2 of cheese over this; pour remainder of mixture over cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Add remaining cheese on top and let melt.

title: no sugar apple pie
directions: Place apple juice concentrate in a saucepan and bring to a boil.
Combine margarine, cornstarch and spices in a small bowl. Add small amount of apple juice; stir until well blended.
Stir cornstarch mixture into apple juice.
Pour over apples.
Stir to coat all apple slices.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Place top crust over apples.
Bake at 425° for about 30 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 350° for 30 minutes longer.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Melt butter; mix with basil, salt and pepper.
Pour over veggies.
Sprinkle over veggies the Parmesan cheese (enough to coat them entirely).
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Take out and cut any cheese slices to place on top.
Return to oven for 10 minutes.

title: never fails pie crust
directions: Mix flour and salt; cut in shortening. Combine remaining ingredients and stir into shortening mixture. Let stand a few minutes. Roll dough on floured board to desired thickness. Makes 4 (9-inch) pie shells.

title: saucy meatballs
directions: In large bowl combine beef, cheese, bread crumbs, milk and egg; mix well and form into balls, about 20 balls.
Brown in a large pan with oil. Cook and drain excess fat.

Sprinkle flour over meatballs stirring gently to coat. On medium heat combine; tomatoes sauce and salt. Cook uncovered for 25 minutes or until sauce is desired thickness. Serve meatballs and sauce over cooked noodles.

title: chocolate chip brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease 13 x 9-inch baking pan. Beat sugar, margarine, eggs and vanilla until smooth.
Add one cup chocolate, melted.
Mix well.
Add flour, oats, baking powder, remaining 1 cup chocolate and nuts, mixing well.

title: shoo-fly pie
directions: Line 2 pie pans with pastry.
Make crumbs by combining flour, sugar, salt and shortening.
Dissolve soda in hot water and combine molasses.
Add 3/4 cup crumbs, pour into pastry lined pans and top with remaining crumbs.
Bake in very hot oven at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce to 350° for 20 to 30 minutes more.

title: pineapple dessert
directions: Dissolve sugar and Jell-O in hot water.
Drain pineapple and add enough water to pineapple juice to make one cup.
Add to Jell-O.
Refrigerate until a little hard.

title: egg yolk biscuits
directions: Beat egg yolks, vanilla, salt and water together until lemon colored.
Stir sugar into flour; mix liquid and dry ingredients together.
Knead on a floured board until surface blisters.
Cut to 2-inch parallelograms and slit center from longest points of dough.
Curl back tops to slit in opposite directions.
Fry in deep hot pot until brown.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: party biscuits
directions: Cream the margarine or butter with the sour cream.
Mix in the self-rising flour.
Grease muffin tins or spray with no-stick. Fill small muffin tins about 1/2 full.
Bake in 350° oven about 15 or 20 minutes.
Check for browning to suit you.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese, add other ingredients.
Chill at least 1 hour.
Roll in chopped pecans.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: hot asparagus dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes. Serve with corn chips.

title: ham and broccoli casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook broccoli as directed on package; drain.
Spread in ungreased rectangular baking dish, 13 x 9 x 2-inches.
Layer ham and cheese over broccoli.
Beat remaining ingredients with hand beater until smooth; slowly pour over cheese.
Bake uncovered 1 hour.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: crock-pot baked beans
directions: Cook hamburger meat and onion in skillet and drain. Brown bell pepper and smoked sausage in skillet; drain.
Put all ingredients in crock-pot. Stir and cook for 5 to 6 hours on high or overnight on low.

title: dream bars
directions: Sift together and set aside 1 cup flour, brown sugar and salt. Cut in until fine crumbled shortening.
Pat into greased 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Sift together and set aside 1/4 cup flour, baking powder and salt.
Beat until very thick eggs and brown sugar.
Add to flour mixture chocolate chips and vanilla.
Spread over baked mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Yield: 32 (2 x 1-inch) bars.

title: hot sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in a 2-quart saucepan.
Bring to a boil, cut down heat
and simmer for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: zucchini custard
directions: Cook zucchini, covered, in salted, boiling water until tender. Drain very well.
Put in shallow baking dish.
Beat together the egg, sour cream, salt, pepper and half of the cheese.
Pour over zucchini.
Dot with butter and sprinkle with remaining cheese. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Serves 4 generously.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Mix Jell-O and water until dissolved.
Add pie filling, nuts and pineapple.
Pour into oblong dish, set until firm.
Whip sour cream and cream cheese.
Add sugar and vanilla.
Beat until it stands in peaks.
Spread over Jell-O.
Chill well.
Sprinkle with nuts.

title: hot cider punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together and heat to boiling point.
Makes 3 quarts or 24 punch cups.
Garnish with orange slices, if desired.

title: italian stuffed zucchini boats
directions: Boil zucchinis 7 to 10 minutes, drain and let cool.
Cut each zucchini in half, lengthwise and scrape out pulp.
Set zucchini aside and mash pulp and pour off liquid.
Fry sausage and onion and drain well.
Combine sausage with pulp mixture.
Add egg and remaining ingredients and mix well.
Fill zucchini halves with mixture.
Sprinkle extra parmesan cheese on top of zucchini boats and bake at 350 degrees for 20 minutes.

title: kahlua
directions: Mix all together. Bring to a boil on medium heat. Let cool and add 1/5th bottle vodka. Kahlua is ready to drink.

title: yummy in the tummy chocolate pudding
directions: In a heavy saucepan, combine chocolate, sugar and milk.
Heat and whisk constantly until chocolate is melted.
Avoid scorching or burning the milk.
If you have a double boiler, use it.

title: cheese dip
directions: Mix together the cheese.
Shred chipped beef, add to cheese. Add green onions.
Mix all together.
Serve with crackers.

title: caramel nut pound cake
directions: Cream the butter or oleo, Crisco, brown sugar and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add the flour, salt and baking powder alternately with the milk and vanilla.
Fold in the chopped pecans.
Bake in a large tube pan at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: In a mixing bowl cut flour and shortening into small balls; add water, vinegar and sugar.
Mix well.
Place in refrigerator to chill or store up to 3 days.
Yields 4 to 5 crusts.

title: fruited chicken
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients; add enough salad dressing to hold together.
Chill well.
Serves 8.

title: yum yum salad
directions: Heat water and sugar to boiling point; add jello.
Dissolve over heat.
Add pineapple; refrigerate to thicken.
Fold in Cool Whip; add cheese and nuts.
Refrigerate to congeal.
Serve on lettuce as salad.
Cut in squares; top with cherries for dessert.

title: ant killer
directions: Mix into a paste.
Coat one side of small squares of cardboard and put them where the ants are.
When the paste gets dry, replace with the fresh paste.
Continue until all gone.

title: old fashioned sugar cookies
directions: Cream the oleo, oil, sugar, powdered sugar and vanilla.
Add the eggs.
Sift and add the flour, soda, cream of tartar and salt. Roll in little balls.
Press down.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 375° for 5 to 7 minutes on greased cookie sheet.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, lay whole graham crackers down. Mix puddings, milk and Cool Whip together and pour 1/2 of mixture on top of graham crackers.

title: oatmeal muffins
directions: Soak oats and sour milk for 15 minutes.
Make sour milk by adding 1 tablespoon vinegar or lemon juice to 1 cup whole milk. Beat in egg, sugar and vanilla.
Mix dry ingredients; stir into mixture.
Add the melted butter.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: holiday stuffed turkey
directions: To prepare stuffing:
In 4-quart saucepan over medium heat, in hot butter, cook mushrooms and onion with savory and nutmeg until tender.
Remove from heat.
Add broccoli, stuffing, rice and broth. Toss to mix.
Spoon stuffing mixture lightly into neck and body cavities.
Fold shin over stuffing; skewer closed.
Tie legs.
On rack in roasting pan, place turkey breast-side up.
Insert meat thermometer into thickest part of meat between breast and thigh, not touching bone.
Roast, uncovered, at 325° for 4 hours or until internal temperature reaches 180° and drumstick moves easily. Baste occasionally with pan drippings.
When skin turns golden, cover loosely with tent foil.
Makes 14 to 16 servings.

title: lemon glaze cake
directions: Mix cake mix and pudding together. Mix or beat the eggs, oil and water into the cake mixture for 4 minutes. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: uncooked fresh tomato relish
directions: Combine
all ingredients;
chill 2 to 3 hours. Serve as a relish with meats, fish or poultry.
Yields 3 cups.

title: health pudding
directions: Simmer all fruit and vegetables for approximately 15 minutes. Combine 1 cup water from vegetables and fruit with starch, spices, sugar and egg whites.
Add to vegetables and fruit.
Continue simmering and stirring until thickened.

title: holiday cranberry punch
directions: Mix together and serve in punch bowl.

title: caramel peanut butter dip
directions: In a microwave-safe bowl, microwave caramels and water on high for 1 minute; stir. Microwave 1 minute more or until smooth. Add peanut butter and mix well; microwave for 30 seconds or until smooth. Stir in peanuts if desired. Serve warm with apples.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Whip altogether.
Pour in unbaked pastry shell.
Bake at 350°.

title: foolproof meringue
directions: Beat egg whites with salt until soft peaks form; gradually add Marshmallow Creme, beating until stiff peaks form.
Spread over pie filling, sealing to edges of crust.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool.

title: easy brownies
directions: Measure and sift together into bowl dry ingredients.
Add melted butter, eggs and vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
Fold in nuts and pour into greased and floured cake pan.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: party potatoes
directions: Let potatoes thaw.
Then mix remaining ingredients into them. Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan, uncovered at 350° for 1 hour.
Crush potato chips and spread for topping.

title: brownie mocha torte
directions: Stir up the "cake-like" version (not fudge-like) and spread into two 9-inch layer cake pans (round).
Bake as directed, about 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: yogurt crescent rolls
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients; set aside.
Dissolve yeast in warm water in a large mixing bowl.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Stir in yogurt mixture, egg and egg white.
Combine flour and salt.
Stir 2 cups flour mixture into yogurt mixture; beat at medium speed of an electric mixer until smooth.
Gradually stir in remaining flour mixture.
Cover and refrigerate 8 hours.

title: baked chicken and rice
directions: In a 13 x 9-inch baking dish, put 1 cup uncooked (raw) rice. Sprinkle with salt.
Combine in a mixing bowl the soups and 1 1/2 cups water.
Pour half of mixture over uncooked rice.
Place raw chicken (4 to 6 breasts) over rice mixture.
Salt and pepper chicken, then add the rest of soup mixture.
Sprinkle with 1/2 package of dry onion soup mix.
Cover dish with foil.
Bake at 350° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: lime-cottage cheese salad
directions: Boil together jello and pineapple juice.
Stir in marshmallows until dissolved and add the rest of the ingredients.
Let stand in refrigerator.

title: holodetz(jellied pig's feet)
directions: Wash pig's feet and hocks and place in a 4-quart pot filled with cold water.
When it comes to a boil, skim several times. Then add the peppercorns, bay leaves and salt.
Cook slowly for several hours or until meat falls off the bones easily.
Remove the feet and hocks; let cool.
When cool, separate meat from the bones, discard bones and place the meat in containers for molding. Strain the stock through a sieve or cheesecloth.
Add the garlic to stock and taste for salt, if needed.
Pour the stock over the meat and refrigerate.
When holodetz is jelled, remove the fat which accumulated on the surface.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Grease bottom of pans.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: In a large skillet, put sugar, oleo and crushed pineapple and let bubble 5 minutes.
Place sliced pineapple around in skillet and add cherries for color.
Mix cake mix as directed on package and pour on top of pineapple.
Bake until cake is done.
Turn right side up on cake plate.

title: grated sweet potato pudding
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar and beat well (until light).
Add milk and the butter which has been melted.
Add vanilla, salt and the sweet potatoes.
Butter baking dish.
Bake in moderate oven 350° about 25 minutes.

title: nutty fingers
directions: Mix together butter, salt, sugar and vanilla.
Add flour and nuts.
Mix until dough gets stiff.
Shape into balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 300° for 30 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix 1/2 pint of whipping cream with eggs and a dash of salt.
Add corn and green chilies.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish and bake, uncovered, for 45 minutes. Can be doubled; bake for 1 1/2 hours.

title: reuben casserole
directions: Spread sauerkraut in bottom of an oiled 2-quart casserole. Sprinkle half of caraway seed over sauerkraut.
Layer corned beef slices over sauerkraut and drizzle dressing over all.
Layer tomato slices and cheese over dressing.
Toss bread crumbs and remaining caraway seed in butter and spread over cheese.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: spaghetti and meatballs
directions: In a large bowl, combine first ten ingredients; mix thoroughly.
With hands, firmly shape into 1-inch meatballs.

title: avocado dunk
directions: Peel avocados; mash pulp.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well. Cover; let stand for one hour.
Serve with corn chips.
Yields 1 1/2 cups.

title: apple cinnamon bread(gram newton's recipe)
directions: Scald milk. Cool to lukewarm.
Pour over sugar, salt and margarine.
In a mixing cup, dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup warm water. Add to above ingredients.
Add 3 eggs and 2 cups of the flour and beat to mix.
Add remaining flour and knead for 10 minutes.
Let rise.
Punch down. Separate into 2 loaves.

title: berries of your choice pie
directions: Blend together and press into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Refrigerate while preparing filling.

title: mulled apple cider
directions: In a small heavy saucepan (preferably nonmetallic), place the apple cider, cinnamon sticks, allspice, cloves and orange peel and bring to a boil over moderately high heat.
Adjust heat to that the mixture barely bubbles.
Cover and simmer for 15 minutes. Strain the cider mixture into 4 mugs and put an orange slice and cinnamon stick in each mug, if you like.
Serves 4.

title: pie crust
directions: Blend first 4 ingredients together.
Beat the egg, then add with vinegar and water.
Mix these ingredients together, then blend in first batter.
Chill batter before using.
Makes from 5 to 7 crusts.

title: bean casserole
directions: Combine onion, bell pepper, pimento, soup, Cheez Whiz and sour cream.
Pour over drained beans and corn.
Mix well and pour into large buttered casserole.
Melt oleo and pour over 1/2 box crushed Cheese Nip crackers.
Sprinkle on top and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until it bubbles.
Real good!

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown ground meat and onion together; drain.
Combine meat and soup.
Place in bottom of casserole dish.
Layer cheese on top, then Tater Tots.
Lightly salt and pepper the top.
Bake in 350° oven about 20 minutes or until the potatoes are brown.

title: easy holiday punch
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 2 cups boiling water in large bowl.
Add frozen juices.
Stir until well blended.
Stir in 6 cups cold water and pineapple juice.
Pour over ice ring in punch bowl.
Add ginger ale just before serving.

title: sloppy joe sandwiches
directions: Brown together meat, onions and bell pepper.
Drain. In microwave melt together soup and cheese.
Mix everything together for delicious sandwiches.

title: orange cake
directions: Mix with mixer.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix ingredients and put in baking dish and cook at 350° for 50-60 minutes or until done.

title: cream cheese squares
directions: Mix the margarine, 1 egg and cake mix.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Set aside.
Combine 2 eggs, cream cheese, powdered sugar and vanilla.
Beat until fluffy.
Spread over the first layer.
Bake at 300° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool on rack.
Cut into 2-inch squares.
Makes 24.

title: surprise strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Allow to chill until partially set. Meanwhile, thaw the strawberries. Stir strawberries and pineapple into jello. Add lemon juice.
Chill until firm.

title: mussel soup with saffron
directions: Remove beards from mussels and rinse well.
Heat a 6-quart pot with oil and garlic.
Saute a few seconds.
Do not burn.
Add cleaned mussels and vermouth.
Cook, covered, over medium heat. Steam mussels open, about 4 minutes.
Stir once.
Strain mussels and save broth.
Cool mussels on sheet.
Return pot to stove.
Add butter, onion and celery until clear (saute).
Add cream, chicken broth, clam juice and saffron.
Heat to gentle simmer and cook 15 minutes.
Remove meat from mussels.
Discard shells.
Add green onions and parsley to pot and simmer 2 minutes.
Add mussels and any juices.
Salt and pepper.
Serves 4.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix together as you would any cornbread.
Bake at 400° until golden brown.

title: creamy salsa dip
directions: Stir all ingredients until well mixed.
Cover and chill for 2 hours.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: cottage cheese sandwich spread
directions: Makes enough for 4 sandwiches.
Mix together all ingredients. Chill.

title: shrimp cheese ball
directions: Mix well.
Roll into ball.
Roll in chopped pecans and parsley flakes.

title: salad dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in a jar.
Cover tightly and shake vigorously.
Makes 1 cup.

title: cincinnati chili
directions: Combine the hamburger, onions and 1 quart water; simmer together for 30 minutes.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Simmer, uncovered, for 2 to 3 hours, until thickened.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: cucumber tea sandwiches
directions: In small bowl, mix the first 4 ingredients.
With fork, score unpeeled cucumber lengthwise.
Cut cucumber lengthwise in half, then crosswise in very thin slices.
With 1 3/4-inch round biscuit cutter, cut 4 rounds from each slice of bread.
Spread 1 side of each bread round with cream cheese.
Top with 2 cucumber slices. Line jelly roll pan with damp paper towels.
Place sandwiches in pan and cover with damp paper towels to keep bread from drying out.

title: fried potato cakes
directions: Prepare potatoes as if they were going to be served as mashed potatoes.
Add egg and stir in onion.
Add flour until potatoes are slightly stiff and will stay together in patties.
Preheat oil in skillet.
Fry patties until golden brown.

title: easy appetizer
directions: In bottom of pie plate -
layer softened cream cheese, chili and cheddar cheese.
Warm in microwave oven for 45 seconds or until cheese melts.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Boil chicken, then debone.
Mix together onion, cream of mushroom soup, cream of chicken soup, chicken broth and Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Layer chicken, sauce, tortillas and cheese in a pan around 14 x 10 x 2-inches.
Spray pan with Pam.
Bake uncovered for 1 hour at 350°.
Yields 8.
Top with sour cream before serving.

title: railroad cookies
directions: Boil raisins in water for 5 minutes.
(Set aside.)
Mix butter, sugar and eggs until fluffy.
Mix remaining ingredients to butter mixture, adding flour and raisins last.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: divinity
directions: Boil ingredients until mixture makes a firm ball in cold water.
Beat egg whites stiff, adding a pinch of baking powder while beating.
Pour syrup very slowly over egg whites.
Add another pinch of baking powder, beating all the while.
Add vanilla while beating.
Fold in nuts.
Drop on wax paper.

title: corn bread salad
directions: Bake Jiffy corn bread mix as directed on box. Let cool. Crumble bread in large bowl. Add chopped pepper, tomato, onion, mayonnaise, lemon juice and salt. Stir well and refrigerate overnight.

title: champagne chicken
directions: Season chicken with salt and pepper.
Melt butter in a large frying pan and saute chicken 6 to 8 minutes until lightly browned. Lower heat.
Remove chicken.
Stir flour into drippings.
Slowly add broth, stirring to make a smooth sauce.
Slowly add light cream, stirring constantly.
Stir in mustard and cook until sauce bubbles.
Return chicken to pan and spoon sauce over each piece. Cover and simmer until cooked (about 10 to 15 minutes).
Serve over rice.

title: mccordie's fried vegetables
directions: Heat cooking oil or grease in skillet.
Add potatoes and onion.
Cook 5 minutes on low heat.
Stir in okra, squash, salt and pepper.
Cook, stirring occasionally, until tender.

title: sue's house dressing
directions: Mix together.
Refrigerate until ready to use.

title: cashew chicken
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Put small can of Chinese noodles over top before serving.
Serve over rice.

title: petit sucre
directions: Beat powdered sugar and egg white
for 15 minutes (no less) on medium-high speed (again no less than 15 minutes).
Do not double!

title: marshmallow creme fudge
directions: Bring sugar, milk and butter to a boil.
Cook to medium soft-ball stage (236°), stirring frequently.
Remove from heat. Then immediately add Marshmallow Creme, nuts and chocolate chips. Stir until Creme and chocolate chips are melted.
Pour into 9 x 9-inch square buttered pan.
Let cool and cut into squares.

title: sunday dinner mashed potatoes
directions: Place potatoes in a Dutch oven; cover with water. Cover and bring to a boil. Cook for 20 to 25 minutes or until very tender; drain well. In a large mixing bowl, mash potatoes. Add sour cream, cream cheese, 2 tablespoons butter, salt, onion salt and pepper; beat until fluffy. Transfer to a greased 2-quart baking dish. Dot with the remaining butter. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until heated through. Yield: 8 servings.

title: capanada(microwave)
directions: In a 4-quart casserole, saute onion, bell pepper and celery in olive oil.
Cover with wax paper and cook on High 30 minutes. Stir once or twice.
Stir in eggplant.
Cover and cook on High 30 minutes.
Stir once.
Add tomato sauce and paste.
Cook on High 10 minutes.
Stir in garlic, olives, vinegar, sugar, capers, oregano, salt and peppers.
Cook on High 5 minutes.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream butter, margarine and cream cheese together; beat until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each egg. Add vanilla.
Gradually add flour; mix until smooth.

title: strawberry cookies
directions: Mix; drop on cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 6 to 8 minutes.

title: strawberry glaze
directions: Stir together first 3 ingredients.
Add strawberries.
Bring to boil 1 minute over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Strain. Stir in juice and coloring.
Cool slightly.
Arrange whole strawberries on cheese cake.
Cover with glaze.

title: taco dip
directions: Mash avocados.
Combine sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning (start with 1/2 package and add to taste).
Combine all ingredients, adding lemon juice and salt to taste.
Serve with chips.

title: italian green beans
directions: Cook and crumble bacon; cook green beans using package instructions.
Drain.
Combine bacon and green beans in a medium bowl.
Add salad dressing; toss.
Serve.

title: squash fritters
directions: Combine squash, onion, salt, pepper, sugar and flour.
Beat eggs and add to squash.
Then add melted butter.
Drop by tablespoon into hot oil and fry at 375° to 400°.

title: cranberry ring salad
directions: Wash cranberries; add 1 cup cold water. Cook until tender. Add sugar and cook for 5 minutes. Soften gelatin in 1/2 cup cold water; dissolve in hot cranberries and add salt.

Chill until mixture begins to thicken. Add nuts and celery. Mix thoroughly. Pour into oiled ring mold. Chill until firm. Unmold and place on a large salad plate. Place light lettuce around salad, arrange shrimp in center or serve on a bed of chicory on individual plates and garnish with mayonnaise. Serves 8.

title: honey-mustard swordfish
directions: Arrange steaks in a baking dish.
Combine wine and next 4 ingredients; pour over steaks.
Cover and marinate in refrigerator 1 hour.
Remove steaks from marinade, reserving 1/4 cup marinade. Place reserved marinade in a small saucepan; bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.

title: hodge podge soup
directions: Brown meat and onions; drain fat.
Add the rest of the ingredients and their liquids; simmer for 20 minutes.
Makes a good potluck dish served from a crock-pot.

title: caramel corn
directions: Pop the corn; put in roaster and keep in oven on warm.
Boil the brown sugar, butter, corn syrup, salt, cream of tartar and peanuts for 5 minutes.
Add the soda; stir and put on corn.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour, stirring often.

title: butter roll
directions: Melt butter.
Add all ingredients together and pour over separated buns into a small baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: soft molasses cookies
directions: Cream together sugar, molasses and egg.
Pour melted shortening over and continue mixing.
Add 2 cups flour and soda; mix.
Add raisins; mix.
Add remaining flour, spices and salt and mix well.
Dough will be very stiff.
Pour boiling water over mixture and blend thoroughly.
Bake 12 minutes on greased cookie sheet at 350°.

title: brown sugar pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening; add egg, one at a time, then flour and milk, starting with flour and ending with flour.
Add baking powder and salt.
Stir in nuts.
Pour in tube pan that has been greased and floured.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: chicken livers and mushrooms
directions: Cook together for 5 minutes, bacon (cut in pieces) and butter. Remove bacon bits.
Add chopped onion; cook 2 minutes and add chicken livers.
Cook until light brown all over (until they look done).
Add flour, beef bouillon, lemon juice and sliced mushrooms.
Add cooking sherry; cook 2 minutes.
Sprinkle with chopped parsley and serve on toast or rice.
Serves 4.

title: 5 minute fudge
directions: Mix milk, sugar and salt together in pan.
Heat to boiling; cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients; stir 1 to 2 minutes until marshmallows melt.
Pour into buttered 9-inch square pan.
Makes 2 pounds.

title: easy spinach roll-yes
directions: Use whatever amount you choose.

title: one dish hamburger supper
directions: Make patties of hamburger meat and place on foil.
On each pattie put a slice of potato and onion.
Put extra ones all over. Put on large sheet of foil and fold and seal.
Put in oven and bake at 400° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Serve with tossed salad and drink.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Cream soup and cream cheese.
Blend in shrimp and all the other ingredients. Serve with chips or raw vegetables.

title: jiffy barbecue sauce
directions: Cook onion until soft in hot oil.
Add remaining ingredients. Simmer 15 minutes.
This can be doubled just fine.

title: cheese squash casserole
directions: Boil squash with onion until soft.
Drain and add seasonings. Put in greased baking dish.
Top with mixture of cheese, milk and mayonnaise.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until light brown and cheese is melted on top.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Saute chopped onion in butter.	Steam broccoli.
Mix all ingredients and pour into a 9x13 glass baking dish.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 8.

title: hummos bi tahini
directions: Place ingredients into a food processor and blend well.
Serve with Labanese bread.

title: gotabki(cabbage rolls)
directions: Remove core from cabbage.
Scald cabbage in boiling water and remove leaves as they soften.

title: sweet and sour vinaigrette
directions: Heat the vinegar; add sugar and stir until dissolved.
Remove from heat. Add oil and soy sauce. Mix in salt and pepper. Cover and
refrigerate until ready to use. Put in blender or food processor to emulsify.

title: spanish pinto beans
directions: Boil beans until tender. In a large skillet put olive oil and heat for 3 to 4 minutes.
Add the other ingredients and saute for 5 minutes.
Pour this sauce over the beans and cook for 10 minutes.
For better flavor, add cut up lean ham to the sauce.

title: russian noodle pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter; set aside.
Beat eggs, add sour cream, softened cream cheese, sugar and salt.
Add mixture to melted butter and vanilla.
Fold in cooked noodles , 1/2 cup raisins, optional.

title: buckeyes
directions: Pour first 4 ingredients into large mixing bowl; mix well and make into 1-inch balls.
Place balls in refrigerator about 1 hour.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach; squeeze dry and set aside.
Stir sour cream and mayonnaise together.
Add vegetable soup mix and stir until well blended, scraping sides of bowl periodically.
Stir in spinach and water chestnuts.
Add green onions and blend well.
Cover and chill for at least 2 hours before serving.
Serve with your favorite brand of crackers.

title: hominy-green chilies casserole
directions: Reserve 1 1/4 cups cheese for topping.
Toss all ingredients until well mixed.
Pour into casserole dish; top with reserved cheese.
Bake at 325° until cheese melts and is lightly browned and bubbly around edge of dish.
Delicious!

title: fudge
directions: Boil butter, sugar and milk for 11 minutes.
Add marshmallow cream, chocolate chips, vanilla and nuts.
Beat until stiff. Spread in buttered jelly roll pan.
Cool for several hours. Yield: 5 pounds.
Very good!

title: corn pudding(side dish)
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes, or until toothpick inserted in middle comes out clean.

title: chicken gumbo
directions: Heat margarine in saucepan. Saute onion and green pepper for 10 minutes.
Place in a large soup pot. Add broth, tomatoes (cut into small pieces), bay leaf and thyme. Bring to a boil. Add the okra and pepper. Cover over low heat 15 minutes. Stir in the rice and chicken.

title: chewy cakes
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs; blend.
Add flour, blending in before you add vanilla and nuts.
Bake 20 minutes at 325° if fast oven and 350° if slow oven.

title: grilled garlic chicken
directions: In medium bowl, combine garlic mushroom mix with oil.
Add chicken and toss to coat.
Grill or broil until chicken is no longer pink.
Makes 4 servings.
Results guaranteed.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs thoroughly with sugar, salt, corn syrup and melted butter.
Add pecans.
Pour into unbaked pastry shell.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 50 minutes, or until knife inserted halfway between outside and center of filling comes out clean. Cool pie before serving.

title: pineapple upside-down cake(microwave)
directions: Things you will need: Tupperware measuring cup set, large Mix-N-Stor, 2 cup measuring pitcher, Vienese spatula, olive dipper and 9-inch quiche pan.

title: mom's spaghetti meat sauce
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Drain off excess grease.
Add other ingredients and cook slow until real thick.
Serve over spaghetti noodles or any other pasta.

title: fruit punch(excellent)
directions: Mix and pour over ice block; serve.
Excellent!!!

title: spinach topped tomatoes(serves 6.  easy.  do ahead.)
directions: Cook spinach according to package; drain.
Combine all ingredients except tomatoes.
Make into small patties to fit on top of 1/2 tomato.
Put on cookie sheet, freeze, then bag.
To serve, place patty on tomato half, put in oven at 350° and bake 30 minutes if frozen, 20 minutes if thawed.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Cream together cream cheese, mayonnaise, Worcestershire sauce and garlic.
Spread mixture on a rimmed plate.
Cover and refrigerate.
Just before serving, layer avocado dip on cheese, then spread picante sauce on avocado layer.
Top with shrimp. Sprinkle with green onions and serve with tortilla chips.

title: orange julius
directions: Place all ingredients in blender and blend until smooth. Serve immediately.

title: baked apple crunch
directions: Place sliced apples in buttered 9 x 13-inch baking dish and sprinkle with sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt.
In medium bowl, combine butter, flour and brown sugar.
Spread mixture evenly over apples.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes at 350°.
Serve immediately.

title: captain's quiche
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Beat eggs and remaining ingredients.
Drain hamburger, then add to egg mixture.
Pour into quiche pan and bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: dot's apple cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat in the eggs. Sift all of the dry ingredients together and gradually beat into the butter/sugar mixture.
Fold in the apples.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: shrimp etouffee
directions: Cook shrimp by boiling in water, seasoned with salt and pepper, 15 minutes.
Drain, peel and remove black veins.
Melt butter in large skillet.
Saute onions, pepper and celery.
Add dried parsley and Italian seasoning; cook until tender.

title: crabmeat quiche
directions: Line a 9 inch quiche dish with pastry. Prick bottom and sides of pastry with a fork. Bake at 400° for 3 minutes; remove from oven and gently prick with fork, bake an additional 5 minutes. Set aside.

title: chicken with capers
directions: In a shallow bowl, combine flour, paprika, salt and pepper. Dip cutlets in flour mixture.
Saute chicken in butter and olive oil on medium-high heat until golden brown.
Remove cutlets. Discard oil mixture.
Add lemon juice and capers.
Return cutlets to pan.
Saute over low heat for about 5 minutes.
Serve over rice.
Makes 6 servings.

title: embutido
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients, blend thoroughly.
Spread pork mixture on an 8 x 10-inch piece of leaf lard.
Arrange slices of hard-cooked eggs, chorizo de bilbao or Vienna sausage and raisins on pork mixture.
Roll as for jelly roll.
Wrap in cheesecloth or aluminum foil.
Boil in soup stock for 1 hour or if wrapped in aluminum foil, bake in a moderate oven (350°) for 1 hour.
Chill. Before serving, remove wrappings and slice.
Makes 2 rolls.

title: salmon patties
directions: In a large bowl, mash salmon.
Add all other ingredients.
Stir until all is mixed together.
If not stiff enough to drop from spoon, add more flour.
Heat oil in frying pan until hot.
Drop by spoonful into hot oil.
Brown on both sides.

title: pea salad
directions: Mix all
together with salad dressing.	Better made the day before you plan to serve it.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients except nuts.
Stir in nuts.
Shape into loaves 3-inches wide and 2-inches high.
Chill overnight.
Slice and bake 10 to 12 minutes at 370°.
Yield:
about 6 dozen.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mini marshmallows may also be added.

title: squash rolls
directions: Combine the warm water, yeast, and 1 teaspoon of the sugar in a small bowl. Stir to mix. Set aide.
In a large bowl, combine the melted shortening, milk, squash, remaining sugar, and salt.
Mix well. Add yeast and 1 cup of the flour. Mix well.

Continue adding flour until the dough is no longer sticky. Place in a well-greased bowl and cover with a dish towel. Allow to rise until double in bulk. This will probably take 1 hour to 1 1/2 hours. Punch down and knead until smooth.
Pinch off portions about size of golf ball. Roll in palms of hands until round.
Place on greased baking sheet. Cover with dish towel and allow to rise until light (probably about 45 minutes). Bake at 425 degrees for 12 to 15 minutes or until lightly browned.
Remove from oven and brush with butter.
Makes about 15 rolls.

title: buttermilk pancakes
directions: Sift together first 5 ingredients.
Add last 3.
Stir until just moistened.
Bake on griddle.
Serves 2 to 4.

title: blueberry cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs.
Combine all dry ingredients. Add alternately with the milk and vanilla.
Add blueberries.
Pour in pan and sprinkle with sugar.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: tortilla torte
directions: Beat cream cheese with electric mixer for 30 seconds.
Add 2 tablespoons diced chili, deviled ham, sour cream, 2 tablespoons taco sauce and hot pepper sauce to cream cheese.
Beat well until blended.
Cover and chill.

title: mexican salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except Fritos, in large bowl. Refrigerate.
Toss in Fritos before serving.
Makes 12 to 15 servings.

title: sylvia's collard greens with smoked turkey
directions: In a 4-quart saucepan, bring the water and smoked turkey to a boil over high heat. Reduce the heat and simmer, covered, for 1 hour. While the turkey is cooking, wipe the collards with a damp towel, then wash two or three times or until all the dirt and grit has been removed. Chop the greens into 1/2-inch pieces. You will have 10 cups of chopped greens. Add the collards, oil, salt, black pepper, sugar and red pepper flakes to the saucepan. Return to a boil. Reduce the heat and simmer, covered, for 30 minutes longer. Discard the turkey before serving or chop the turkey meat and add it to the collards. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: quick italian spaghetti
directions: In a skillet, brown ground beef and onions.
Add next five ingredients; cover and simmer for 10 minutes.
Add olives; simmer 5 minutes longer.
Spoon over spaghetti; sprinkle with cheese and bacon bits, if desired.
Yields 4 servings.

title: chocolate caramel bars
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients until crumbly. Melt caramels and Carnation milk. Put half of first mixture in 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 6 minutes at 350°.
Remove and sprinkle chocolate chips on top, then pour the caramel mixture over and then sprinkle the rest of the cake mixture on top and bake 15 to 20 minutes more.

title: barbecue smokies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Simmer in crock-pot for 2 to 3 hours. Serve hot.

title: senior breakfast cheese grits
directions: Stir grits slowly into boiling water, salted, in heavy saucepan.
Return to boil.
Reduce heat.
Cook 3 to 5 minutes, stirring often.
When thick, remove from heat.
Add 1 package garlic cheese.
When it melts, add butter, milk and eggs.
Put in greased baking dish.
Top with mild grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
Let stand a few minutes before serving.
Serves 6.

title: angel food fruit cake
directions: Crumble angel food cake in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Slice bananas and layer on cake.
Then cut up strawberries and layer on bananas.
Separately, mix 2 small boxes of instant vanilla pudding with milk (use directions on box).
Then pour this over cake and fruit.
Let stand 2 hours.
When ready to eat, top with Cool Whip.

title: tuna steak with lime and capers
directions: Saute the tuna over high heat in hot oil and butter for 3-4 minutes on each side, until barely cooked through.
Squeeze the lime juice over the hot steaks.
Cut into portions and garnish with capers and parsley.

title: nutty peach crisp
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Layer all ingredients in ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake 55 to 60 minutes or until top is golden brown. Let stand at least 15 minutes before serving.
Serve warm or cool.
If desired serve with Cool Whip or ice cream.
Makes 12 to 15 servings.
tags: Betty Crocker Supreme moist butter pecan mix

title: kid's paint brush cookies
directions: Let the Picassos do their own thing.
A sure bet.
The three year olds will win the Picasso Title.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Peel and slice carrots.
Cook in salt water just until tender. Drain.
Add pepper and onion.
Mix soup, vinegar, oil, mustard, sugar, salt and pepper. Pour over warm carrots. Refrigerate and marinate overnight or longer.

title: pear preserves
directions: Mix pears with sugar, then with vinegar.
The vinegar keeps preserves from turning to sugar.

title: pistachio bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients and beat on medium speed for 5 minutes.
Grease and flour loaf pans.
Mix 2 tablespoons sugar, 1 tablespoon cinnamon and 1 teaspoon nutmeg. Pour 1/2 the dough in the bottom of the pans.
Sprinkle with the sugar mixture.
Add the remaining dough on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Makes 2 large or 3 medium loaves.

title: spoon rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water; beat egg well and add to water.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Put in well-greased muffin pan. Bake at 400° until brown, approximately 30 minutes.
Dough can be kept in refrigerator a few days.
Bring to room temperature before baking.

title: hot sauce
directions: Combine tomatoes, onion, sugar, salt, garlic cloves and white vinegar.
Boil slow 4 hours.
Cook in canner for 45 minutes in hot water bath.
Makes 16 quarts.

title: new orleans red beans(sister virginia's centennial southern surprise)
directions: Note:
One large ham hock or 2 small ham hocks may be substituted if bone not available.

title: southern plantation cake
directions: Place all ingredients in bowl.
Beat together 3 to 4 minutes. Do not add any other liquid.
Place in 3 layers.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Cook together the margarine, sugar, syrup and salt for 3 minutes.
Add soda and vanilla.
Pour over popcorn and mix well. Put in baking pan and bake for 1 hour at 250°.
Stir several times while baking.
If desired, add peanuts.

title: orange-pineapple ice cream
directions: Mix condensed milk and pineapple in churn container.
Add enough orange drink to fill the churn to the fill line.
Churn according to manufacturer's instructions.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: In large bowl, place salmon, drained.
Remove bones and mash with fingers.
Add next 7 ingredients and mix.
In large frying pan, heat oil.
Shape mixture into the size of small hamburgers and fry until brown on both sides.
Remove from pan and drain on paper towels.
Serve warm or at room temperature.
Cooking time: Under 1 hour.
Makes 12 patties.

title: green enchiladas
directions: Dip tortillas in hot grease and lay on paper towel to absorb some of grease.
Stuff tortillas with meat, onions and cheese. Roll and place on cookie sheet or pan with sides.
Mix rest of ingredients.
Pour over tortillas.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Place in 350° oven until cheese is melted and tortillas are thoroughly heated.

title: poached fish(microwave)
directions: Place onion and butter in 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
Microwave on High 1 to 1 1/2 minutes until onion is transparent.
Stir in wine, salt, sugar, tarragon and pepper.
Add fillets, turning to coat fish well with sauce.
Top with mushrooms.
Cover with plastic.
Microwave at High 6 to 8 minutes or until fish flakes. Rotate and spoon sauce over fish at 1/2 cooking time.

title: angel hair pasta with oriental sauce(serves 2)
directions: Combine the sherry, sesame oil, 1 tablespoon soy sauce and 1 tablespoon ginger in a bowl and mix well.
Add the shrimp. Marinate in the refrigerator.
Combine the lemon juice, rice vinegar, 2 tablespoons soy sauce, sugar and red pepper in a bowl and set aside.
Stir-fry the garlic with 1 tablespoon ginger in the peanut oil in a large saucepan.
Add the shrimp with the marinade. Stir-fry until the shrimp are cooked through.
Stir in the lemon juice mixture.
Cook until heated through.
Thicken with a paste of cornstarch and water if needed for the desired consistency.
Serve over the hot pasta.

title: mashed potato cake
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, butter, flour and milk.
Beat good and add cocoa, cinnamon, nutmeg, vanilla, potatoes and nuts.
Bake in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch cake pan at 350°.
Ice with Potato Cake Icing.

title: spaghetti a la zike
directions: Cook spaghetti 12 minutes.
Drain.
Cut up tomatoes (or run through blender).
Add to spaghetti.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Add chopped onion and bell pepper to ground beef and cook until beef is browned.
Add mixture to spaghetti.
Mix well.
Pour into 2 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Cover with slices of cheese.
Let stand several hours before baking for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream margarine and shortening.
Add sugar; beat until smooth. Add egg yolks and beat well.
Combine flour and soda; add to cream mixture with buttermilk.
Stir in vanilla, coconut and pecans.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Pour into greased and floured pans.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Thaw pie crust for 10 to 15 minutes.
While crust is thawing, combine butter, flour, 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1/8 teaspoon pepper. Stir in broth and milk.
Cook and stir until thick, then stir in peas and carrots and chicken.
Pour into crust, put a crust on top.
Cut slits in top crust.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: lemon lush
directions: You will need a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.

title: wassail
directions: Mix all ingredients together in crock-pot.
Insert cloves into orange and put in mixture.
Simmer slowly for 2 hours.

title: raspberry whip
directions: Stir boiling water into gelatin in large bowl for 2 minutes or until completely dissolved.
Mix cold water and ice cubes to make 2 cups.
Add to gelatin, stirring until slightly thickened with the consistency of unbeaten egg whites.
Remove remaining ice. Stir in 2 1/4 cups whipped topping with wire whisk until smooth. Spoon into 8 individual souffle cups or dessert dishes.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Mix shortening into dry ingredients.
Add milk and yeast dissolved in warm water.
Mix until all flour is moist.
Cover bowl and store in icebox.
Use as needed.
Make in small balls. Bake in 400° oven for 12 to 15 minutes or until done.
The dough keeps in the refrigerator about a week.

title: starter juice for friendship cake
directions: Make starter in one-gallon glass jar.
Combine apple juice, water, sugar, lemon juice, yeast, cherries and juice.
Use container that has lid.
Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Cover and let stand at room temperature, stirring twice each day.

title: honey glazed chicken
directions: Stir together the 1/2 cup soy sauce, onion, garlic, oil and ginger root.
Place chicken in a plastic bag; set in a bowl.
Pour the soy sauce mixture over chicken; close bag.
Chill for 2 to 3 hours, turning chicken occasionally to distribute marinade.
Drain. Skewer the chicken neck skin to back.
Tie legs securely to tail; twist wing tips under back.
Place the chicken, breast side up, on a rack in a shallow roasting pan.
Roast in a 375° oven 1 1/2 hours or until drumstick moves easily in the socket.
Meanwhile, combine honey and the 2 tablespoons soy sauce.
Baste chicken with honey soy mixture during the last 15 minutes of roasting time.
Makes 6 servings.

title: neptune pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions; rinse and drain. In a large bowl, combine tuna, salad dressing and Salad Supreme. Add pasta; toss to evenly coat.
Stir in tomatoes and onions. Cover; refrigerate at least 3 hours.
Stir before serving.

title: baked bean casserole
directions: Cook chopped onion in bacon drippings until clear.
Add next 6 ingredients and stir.
Add beans; stir well.
Put in casserole; bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: escalloped corn
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Sprinkle with toasted crumbs. Bake 30 minutes until brown on top.

title: swiss chicken
directions: Place chicken breasts in baking dish.
Spread with the mustard.
Place a slice of cheese on each breast.
Sprinkle with onion and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients until boiling, remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Drop on wax paper.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.

title: pink pineapple topping
directions: Simmer over medium heat, stirring constantly until candies dissolve.
Chill.
Serve as a sundae topping or on puddings or between sponge cake wedges.

title: quick apple cake
directions: Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spread apples over bottom of pan. Pour over beaten eggs; mix.
Add sugar, oil, nuts and vanilla, turning with fork.
Add flour, cinnamon, soda and salt.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes at 325°.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: old-fashioned coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients in	order and pour into an uncooked pie shell.
Dust with
remaining
nutmeg
if desired.
Bake at 350° until set (about 30 minutes).

title: pizza burgers
directions: Brown hamburger or sausage. Drain. Split English muffins in halves. Spread pizza sauce on each half.
Mix onion and green pepper with meat. Spread meat mixture on each half of muffin. Top with cheese. Bake at 350° until cheese is melted.
Serve immediately.

title: banana split salad
directions: Combine graham crackers and melted butter; press into long baking dish.
Beat oleo, vanilla, eggs (one at a time) and powdered sugar until thick and smooth like icing.
Pour into crust.
Slice bananas over filling.
Press into filling.
Add pineapple and spread over bananas.
Spread large container Cool Whip over pineapple.
Cover with chopped nuts and maraschino cherries; refrigerate.

title: creamy baked chicken
directions: Place cooked chicken in baking pan.
Pour soup over and sprinkle crushed cubes over top.
