Lay slices of cheese on top and bake for 1/2 hour at 325°.

title: mama dixon's pound cake
directions: Beat egg whites with 3 tablespoons sugar until stiff.
Cover and place in refrigerator.
Cream Crisco and 2 2/3 cups sugar until light.
Add egg yolks, 2 at a time.
Add flour and whipping cream alternately to mixture.
Fold in egg whites.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 25 minutes.

title: homemade kraut
directions: You will need a stone churn or large jar.

title: pineapple apricot bread
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients; set aside.
Combine sugar, butter and egg; beat well.
Add milk, pineapple, apricots and raisins; beat well.
Stir in flour mixture and pecans.
Pour mixture into a greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes in a pan on a wire rack.
Remove from pan.
Yield: 1 loaf.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix sugar, oleo and milk.
Cook 20 minutes and bring to boil on medium; stir occasionally.
Remove from burner.
Beat peanut butter and Marshmallow Creme into mixture.
Pour into buttered pan.
Let harden.

title: ghostbuster cake
directions: Follow directions on cake mix and bake in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Just before cake is done, mix rest of ingredients.
Cook in a pan on low heat until chocolate and marshmallows are melted; let come to a boil.
When cake is done, punch holes in it with a wooden spoon handle and pour icing over it while hot.

title: chuck's chili
directions: Cut steak into cubes and small strips.
Cube onion and green pepper.
In a large frying pan, brown all the meat with 1/2 of the onion and green pepper over low heat.
As the meat is browning, add chili powder, basil, celery seed and 1/2 of the garlic.
Add salt, pepper and Texas Pete to taste.
Also add cumin and cayenne pepper.
Cut jalapeno into rings and add to meat as it cooks.

title: reese cups
directions: Mix and spread in buttered pan.
Melt chocolate chips and wax; spread on top.

title: triple layer chocolate bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine crumbs, 1/4 cup cocoa, sugar and butter; press firmly on bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking pan.

title: alma's pecan pie
directions: Line pie shell with pecans.
Beat eggs well.
Add syrup, sugar, salt and butter; mix and pour slowly into shell.
Bake in moderately hot oven at 375° on lower shelf for about 40 minutes. Cool.
Serve topped with spoonfuls of whipped cream.
Makes one (8-inch) pie.
Makes 6 servings.

title: browned beef stew
directions: Heat
vegetable
oil
in
heavy
skillet or Dutch oven. Place flour,
salt and pepper in bag.
Shake to mix, then add meat
and shake to coat meat.
Empty all including extra flour into hot oil and add onion and brown well.
Add chopped carrot and
next
4 ingredients.
Cover and cook over low heat 1 1/2 hours,
stirring as	needed.
Add diced potatoes, carrots and onions;
cook	1/2 hour longer.
Add peas and continue cooking about
minutes. (You may use a can of English peas if you prefer.)

title: bran muffins
directions: Mix wet ingredients.
Mix in dry ingredients, except flakes and nuts.
Stir in flakes and nuts.
Stores in refrigerator several days.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: pizza pop-up pie
directions: Brown and simmer the first 7 ingredients.
Pour meat mixture into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cover with Mozzarella cheese.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix and pour into dish.
Cover with bacon strips.
Bake in 300° oven 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: blueberry delight
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients thoroughly.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 325°.
Blend the cream cheese, sugar, Cool Whip and vanilla well; spread over.
Slice the bananas and place over Cool Whip mixture.
Spoon blueberry pie filling over bananas.

title: festive rice
directions: 1. In a medium (2 qt.) saucepan bring broth to a boil.
Add rice. reduce heat to medium-low; cover and simmer for 10 minutes. 2. Stir in butter-flavor sprinkles and all vegetables.
Cover. Continue simmering 10 minutes. 3. Remove from heat and let stand 5 minutes or until all water is absorbed.
Sprinkle top with butter sprinkles and black pepper. 4. Fluff with a fork before serving. Makes 8 servings.

title: kraut
directions: Fill a quart jar with chopped cabbage.
Stick a banana pepper pod in the center of the jar.
Add a whole garlic and the vinegar, sugar, salt and alum.
Fill each jar with hot water.

title: chinese green salad
directions: Combine salad dressing and ginger root in a small bowl.
Stir well and let stand 30 minutes.
Combine Chinese cabbage and next 3 ingredients.
Toss gently.
Pour dressing mixture over.
Serve. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cover with bread crumbs.
Dot with butter.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: stuffed pasta bake
directions: Combine Ricotta cheese, 1/4 cup Romano cheese, bread crumbs, garlic and parsley flakes; mix well.
Spread 1 cup sauce onto 10 x 6-inch baking dish.
Fill each shell with approximately 2 tablespoons cheese mixture; place shells on top of sauce.
Spoon remaining sauce over shells.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese and remaining Romano cheese.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix together thoroughly and pour into crusts.
Let set in refrigerator until chilled and firm, minimum 4 hours.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Layer as follows in a casserole dish: cooked noodles, cooked sausage, sauce, peppers, mushrooms, pepperoni and cheese.
Cook at 350° until hot and bubbly.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Beat shortening at medium speed with an electric mixer until fluffy.
Gradually add sugars, beating well.
Add egg and vanilla, beating until blended.

title: peek-a-boo squares
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition. Add vanilla and almond. Add flour, mixing well.

title: honey pecan cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Coat peeled and sliced apples (1/8-inch thick) with cinnamon and sugar.
Sift together dry ingredients and set aside in medium size bowl.
In large bowl, mix together remaining ingredients at medium speed until smooth and gradually add dry ingredients, mixing until smooth.

title: sweet pea soup
directions: Add peas and water or vegetable cooking water according to directions on package (or 3 cups water for every 1 cup peas) to a large stock pot.
Bring to boil, reduce heat and simmer 1/2 hour. Add vegetables and seasoning and cook until peas have disintegrated to creamy consistency and vegetables mash easily against side of pot.

title: apple fritters
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Combine rest of ingredients together and add to the dry mixture.
Use right amount of milk to make right consistency batter.
Fry in deep hot fat (305° to 375°) until done, which will take about 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Toss together cornbread crumbs and muffin crumbs in an 8-inch baking dish.
Add sage, celery, salt, pepper, poultry seasoning. Mix well.
In butter, add onion.
Cook
just until tender and clear.
Add entire mixture to crumb and seasoning mixture.	Beat two eggs slightly.	Add to mixture.
Add chicken broth.
Stir until well combined.
Bake in a 350 degree oven for 30 - 45 minutes.

title: barbecue meat loaf with sauce
directions: Heat to boil.
Pour over loaf and bake at 325° for about 1 hour, basting occasionally.
This is better the second day.

title: big peach pie
directions: Peel and slice peaches; grate 2 teaspoons lemon peel and squeeze 2 tablespoons lemon juice.
Toss peaches with sugar, lemon and 2 tablespoons flour.
In another bowl, mix flour, corn meal, salt and shortening; work to consistency of coarse crumbs. Add 8 to 9 tablespoons cold water.
Divide into 2 balls, one larger for bottom.
Roll larger ball out to fit a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Spoon peach mixture over bottom crust.
Add second crust.
Make slits in it.
Brush with milk and sprinkle with sugar.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and bacon.
Drain kidney beans and butter beans.
Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° until warm (approximately 1/2 hour), covered.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Add 1 large sliced mild onion and lots of chopped celery.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat together all ingredients.
Pour in a 9-inch pie shell. Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes or until brown and set.
Insert knife in center, should come out clean.

title: oatmeal apple raisin muffins #2
directions: Baking Temperature: 400°.
Baking Time: 15 to 20 minutes.

title: stuffed chicken breast
directions: Mix all ingredients together except chicken.
Put 1/4 of stuffing mix on half of chicken breasts.
Fold other half over and secure with toothpicks.
Put in lightly greased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: eggplant stacks
directions: Pare as many Russet (Idaho) potatoes as desired.
Cut lengthwise into 3/8-inch thick slices, then cut slices into strips, 3/8-inch wide.
Rinse in cold water; drain thoroughly on paper towels.

title: barbecue chicken breasts in marinade
directions: In bowl large enough to hold all the chicken pieces, combine all of the ingredients, except chicken breasts and branch of fresh rosemary.
Mix well.
Place chicken breasts into mixture and allow to marinate a minimum of 2 hours.
The longer the chicken is allowed to sit in marinade, the better; can be left overnight.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Boil potatoes in large slices until almost done. Saute (brown) pork chops in 2 tablespoons butter. Coat bottom of casserole dish with soup. Put in pork chops. Drain potatoes and put over pork chops. Pour remainder of soup over chops and potatoes. Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: overnight ham
directions: Place ham (fat side up) in a covered roasting pan or you can use foil to cover.
Add water.
Put ham in a cold oven and preheat to 500°.
When it has preheated for 15 mintues, turn oven off. Don't open door, but time it for 3 hours.
Preheat oven again and then cook for 15 minutes.
Turn oven off and don't open oven for 7 hours or overnight.
Yum!

title: zucchini squares
directions: Mix all ingredients well and pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan; bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: party pinwheels
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Spread on tortillas.
Sprinkle on remaining ingredients.
Then roll and wrap tightly.
Chill 2 hours. Cut off ends.
Cut diagonally into 1-inch slices.
I add ham slices to the mixture.

title: chocolate eclair dessert(lighter eating - 4 points)
directions: Evenly arrange 12 graham cracker in a 9 x 13 cake pan. In a large bowl, combine dry vanilla pudding mixes, 1 1/3 c. dry milk powder, and 3 c. water. Mix well using a wire whisk. Blend in 1/2 c. cool whip and 1 tsp. vanilla. Mix gently to combine. Spread half of mixture evenly over graham crackers. Layer another 12 graham crackers over top. Evenly spread remaining pudding mixture over graham crackers. Top with remaining 12 crackers. In a medium bowl, combine dry chocolate pudding mix, remaining 2/3 c. dry milk powder, 1 tsp vanilla and

1 1/4 c. water. Mix well using a wire whisk. Spread chocolate mixture evenly over top of graham crackers. Cover and refrigerate at least 1 hour. Just before serving spread remaining cool whip evenly over top. Drizzle chocolate syrup evenly over cool whip. Refrigerate at least 1 hour.

title: turkey casserole
directions: Combine butter and water.
Stir until butter melts.
Pour over stuffing and toss.
Stir in 1/2 can onions.
Spoon stuffing mix into 9-inch dish (spray the dish).

title: grits casserole
directions: Bring milk to a boil, add butter then gradually stir in grits. Be sure to not use quick cooking grits.
Resume boil and continue cooking.
Stir all the while until mixture takes on appearance of cooked farina.
Remove from heat, season with salt, pepper and beat hard with electric mixer for 5 minutes.
Mixture will take on a creamy appearance.
Pour into 13 x 9 x 2-inch casserole and allow to sit.

title: hot fruit compote
directions: Combine all fruit in baking dish (13 x 9-inch).
Combine brown sugar, butter and applesauce in saucepan; heat and stir.
Spoon over fruit and sprinkle with 3 tablespoons of brown sugar and pecans.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Seal with aluminum foil.

title: spinach pie
directions: Hold yolk of 1 egg for top of pie.
Mix with 1 tablespoon water.
Stir all other ingredients.
Put in pie crusts and bake for 1 hour.
Check pie and bake for 30 minutes longer.

title: no bake banana pudding
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients until thickened.
Layer with vanilla wafers and bananas in large Pyrex dish.
Top with Cool Whip and refrigerate.

title: chocolate chip butter balls
directions: Mix together the flour, chopped pecans and chips; set aside. Cream the butter; add the salt and icing sugar.
Cream.
Add rum extract and cold water.
Gradually add flour mixture and blend. Mold dough into balls.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 325° for 25 minutes.
While warm, roll in icing sugar.
When cool, sprinkle with additional icing sugar.

title: fluffy tapioca dessert
directions: Bring 2 cups of water to a boil in saucepan.
Add jello and pudding mixes one at a time and stir well until dissolved.
Bring to a boil, turn off heat and cool.
Pour cooled mixture into 2-quart bowl.
Add carton of Cool Whip and drained oranges.
Stir slowly until blended.
Refrigerate.

title: chocolate silk pie
directions: Whip the butter
and sugar until light.
Add the chocolate and vanilla.
Beat until blended. Add 1 egg and beat 5 minutes. Add the other egg and beat 5 more minutes. Fill baked pie shell. Chill.

title: extra good cornbread(makes 1 large cake)
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Put butter in pan and place in oven to melt.
Mix all other ingredients and beat until smooth.
Remove pan from oven.
Pour batter into pan and bake 20 to 30 minutes.

title: lime cheese salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in the boiling water and let sit until partially set.
Whip
the gelatin and then add the rest of the ingredients (except
oil)
in
the	order given in the list of ingredients.
Pour	into 9 x 13-inch dish which has been oiled and let
set
until
firm.
Cut into squares to serve.	Serves 12.

title: cranberry mousse(jello salad)
directions: In a large bowl, dissolve gelatin in boiling water. Drain pineapple, setting the pineapple aside and adding juice to gelatin. Stir in cranberry sauce, lemon juice, peel, and nutmeg. Chill until mixture thickens. Fold in sour cream, reserved pineapple and pecans. Pour into glass serving bowl or an oiled 9-cup mold. Chill until set, at least 2 hours.

title: sausage balls
directions: Have sausage and cheese at room temperature.
Mix uncooked sausage with cheese and Bisquick.
Roll into 1-inch balls and place on a cookie sheet.
(You can freeze now on the sheet.
When frozen, they can be bagged.)
Bake at 400° about 15 to 20 minutes. You can bake and freeze them, too.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Oil and flour tube pan.
Mix ingredients 2 minutes.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 325°.

title: potato candy
directions: Boil potato until done. Peel and mash well. Mix powdered sugar with potato until it is thick enough to roll out (takes about one pound). Sprinkle dough board with powdered sugar or on long piece of wax paper. Roll dough out thin and spread peanut butter. Roll up, wrap in wax paper and refrigerate until cool enough to slice.

title: pasta salad
directions: Boil vermicelli; drain and cool.
Sprinkle Salad Supreme seasoning on vermicelli.
Mix vegetables with vermicelli.
Add Italian dressing.
Mix well.
Marinate in refrigerator at least one hour before serving.

title: barbecued beef
directions: Brown meat until crumbly.
Drain off grease and add onion, green peppers, sugar, mustard, vinegar, salt and catsup.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Serve on hamburger bun.

title: okra gumbo
directions: Clean okra and cut into big pieces.
Chop the onions.
Put fresh tomatoes in boiling water; let stand for about 10 seconds. Peel tomatoes and cut up.
Heat oil or Pam in a deep cast-iron skillet.
Add vegetables and enough water to boil okra.
Add the oregano, bay leaf and salt.
Cook over medium heat until okra is done.

title: 20 minute cake
directions: Simmer to boiling the margarine, cocoa and water.
Blend together in a large bowl the flour, sugar, soda, sour milk and eggs.
Add chocolate mixture to flour mixture.
Bake cake in a 17 x 11-inch jelly roll pan (any smaller and cake will run over). Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.
Bake 5 minutes more while you make frosting.
Frost the cake immediately after removing from oven.

title: cherry delight
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients together and spread in 9 x 9-inch pan. Mix together the confectioners sugar, cream cheese and Cool Whip. Spread this mixture over graham cracker crust. Spread the pie filling on top of Cool Whip mixture. Refrigerate before serving.

title: beef and green onion quiche(microwave)
directions: In a large mixing bowl, beat 1 egg slightly.
Add 1/2 cup evaporated milk and stuffing mix.
Toss lightly.
Let stand a few minutes until most of the liquid is absorbed.

title: cameo shrimp
directions: Heat oil in skillet.
Saute shrimp with garlic, onion, oregano, salt and pepper until shrimp are red and onions are brown.
Add wine and tomato sauce; cook for 5 minutes.
Serve over hot, buttered angel hair or spaghetti.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cream cheese ball
directions: Blend cream cheese with seasoning.
Pat into round or square flat shape.
Roll on all sides in lemon pepper.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Chop up in bite size pieces broccoli and celery.
Cover with water and cook until crisp and tender (do not drain).
In large saucepan, combine oleo, flour, salt and pepper.
Cook and stir until flour is slightly browned.
Add milk 1 cup at a time.
When sauce starts to thicken, add Velveeta.
Stir and cook over medium heat until cheese is completely melted and sauce is fairly thick. Add cheese sauce to vegetables.
Let set for 15 minutes before serving.

title: mostaccioli
directions: Mix it all together except for noodles and cheese.
Cook for 3 hours.
Cook mostaccioli noodles.
Serve noodles with sauce over them and cheese on top.

title: beef stew
directions: Put first four ingredients in pan which oil has been added; brown meat.
Add water, bouillon cubes, cover and simmer one hour. Stir in Worcestershire sauce, celery, potatoes, onions and carrots.
Cover and simmer one hour or until vegetables are tender.
Thicken with flour, water mixture.

title: blackberry jam cake
directions: Sift flour, salt and spices together; cream sugar and margarine and add eggs one at a time.
Beat well after each addition.
Dissolve soda in buttermilk and add to creamed mixture. Mix well.
Fold in jam, raisins and nuts.
Bake in greased and floured loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Serves 8 or 10.

title: crab spread
directions: Combine sour cream, cream cheese, lemon juice, horseradish and Old Bay.
Stir over low heat until bubbly.
Add green pepper and flaked crab meat.
Continue to heat until crab is heated through. Serve with variety of crackers, chunks of bread or fresh vegetables.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Place in lasagne pan. Drizzle melted butter over top.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Easy and good for lots of people.
Serves 12.

title: candied apples
directions: Cook water and sugar to a thick syrup.
Peel and quarter apples and put in pan.
Add pinch of salt; pour syrup over apples.
Slice margarine or butter over apples.
Add 1/4 cup of red cinnamon candy hearts before cooking.
This makes apples a pretty red color and adds flavor.
Cook on top of stove on medium-low until clear (20 to 35 minutes).
(Apples may be baked in a 350° oven about 45 minutes, but tend to be slightly watery.)
Make in a 9 1/2-inch round pan. Serves 8.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: In large bowl, mix sauerkraut, carrots, celery, green pepper, onion and pimentos.
In small bowl, mix sugar and oil; pour over vegetables and mix well.
Cover and refrigerate at least 8 hours.

title: easy ham salad
directions: Alternating ham and salad olives, press through a meat grinder.
Add enough mayonnaise to moisten.
(Needs to be easy spreading consistency.)
Do not add salt.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread crescent rolls in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan to make crust.
Bake as directed on package, 7 to 8 minutes (don't overbake).
Cool, then top with the following:
Cream the mayonnaise, cream cheese and spices together, then spread over cool crust.
Top with finely chopped raw vegetables.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese on top.
Chill before serving.

title: down home potato salad
directions: Boil peeled potatoes and eggs.
When potatoes are tender, place in large bowl, making sure not to retain any excess water. While potatoes cool, peel eggs.
Separate egg whites, placing yellows in small bowl.
With fork, mash yellows, adding mustard to make a creamy texture.
Cut up egg whites and add to cooled potatoes.
With a large spoon, chop potatoes to desired texture. Add 2 teaspoons relish and desired mayonnaise and mustard to potatoes.
Stir well.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: taco burgers
directions: In skillet, brown meat; drain off excess fat.
Add tomatoes, chili powder, Worcestershire sauce, garlic salt, sugar and dry mustard.
Stir well, breaking up large pieces of tomato.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat.
Simmer gently, uncovered, for 15 to 20 minutes, or until thick.
Spoon into toasted buns.
Sprinkle with lettuce and shredded cheese.
Makes 8 servings.

title: bran muffins
directions: Place sugar, flour, soda, salt and cinnamon in a large bowl; blend.

Stir in Raisin Bran. Stir in by hand the oil, eggs and buttermilk. Fill muffin cups 2/3 full. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes. Bake what you need and keep the rest in covered bowl in refrigerator. Spoon out as needed. Do not stir batter if you refrigerate it.
Keeps 6 weeks.

title: grandma bea's flan
directions: Preheat oven to 225°.
Mix all ingredients except sugar in blender and whip for 5 minutes. Dissolve sugar in saucepan and cook until caramelized.
Pour sugar into 9-inch cake pan and pour custard on top.
Place a low roasting pan half filled with water in oven.
Set cake pan with flan mixture in the middle of roasting pan and bake for 2 hours and 5 minutes.

title: bacon-wrapped shrimp
directions: You can play with this recipe depending on the shrimp count. Depending on the size of the shrimp will depend on how many appetizers you will get.
I usually cut the bacon in half and wrap around medium size shrimp (30 count).
You can prepare this the day before and let marinate.
Put the bacon wrapped shrimp on a cookie sheet, making sure each is covered in the teriyaki baste.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
They are excellent!

title: summer sausage
directions: Mix well and put in refrigerator for 3 days. Mix each day and on day 4 roll into logs. Bake 8 hours at 175°, turning once. Put over pan for grease to drip.

title: taco pockets
directions: You also need a dough press.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place sliced apples in baking dish.
Mix remaining ingredients and sprinkle over apples.
Bake in oven at 325° for 1 hour.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Beat egg; add milk, salmon and crackers until you can make a loaf.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: bundt cake
directions: Put all ingredients except pecans in mixing bowl and beat at high speed.
Pour half the batter into well-greased Bundt pan. Sprinkle pecans over and add rest of batter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cracklin' bread
directions: Sift first 4 ingredients together into bowl.
Stir in mixture of egg and milk.
Add cracklings; mix well.
Pour into greased 8-inch baking pan or 10-inch iron skillet.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes or until browned.

title: squaw corn
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Remove bacon from pan.
Add onions, chopped, and cook 3 minutes.
Add corn with liquid and heat through.
Add eggs, unbeaten, one at a time and stir gently over moderate heat.
Add bacon, crumbled.
Continue cooking until eggs are set.
Remove from heat and serve hot.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cook the chicken breasts and cut into bite size pieces.
Mix chicken, vegetables, potatoes, and soup in a 2 qt. casserole dish. In another bowl, mix Bisquick, milk, and egg until blended.
Pour this mixture over the chicken mixture.
Bake at 425 for about 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush Oreos; mix butter, cheese and sugar, then mix milk, dry pudding and Cool Whip together.
Then put both mixtures together. Layer cookies and mixture.

title: gingerbread men
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Stir in water.
Mix together last 6 ingredients.
Add flour mixture to liquid mixture, 1/3 at a time. Knead.
Cut into balls, size of golf balls.
Mold into shape of gingerbread man and decorate.

title: squash casserole
directions: Drain cooked squash.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into buttered casserole.
Cover with cracker crumbs. Bake 25 minutes at 300°.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: In a saucepan, cook the onion in the butter until straw colored.
Put the bread cubes in a large bowl.
Pour in the milk and the onion. Set aside until milk has been absorbed.
Add the chopped round steak, chopped veal, chopped pork, salt, pepper, allspice, nutmeg and eggs.
With hands, mix all the ingredients together thoroughly and shape into balls (1-inch).
Roll balls in flour.

title: chinese chicken salad
directions: Blend soy sauce, oil, sherry, honey and sugar.
Pour 1/2 over chicken and let set 2 hours.
Cook pasta (al dente), parcook (not all the way) the snow peas (you want them crunchy).
Mix everything else together.
Add cashews right before serving, they may get soggy.

title: broccoli quiche
directions: Chop broccoli into small pieces and steam until slightly crisp.
Beat eggs and milk until frothy.
Mix flour, powder and salt. Stir into egg mixture.
Mix well.
Fold in broccoli, cheese and onion.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased baking pan.
Sprinkle with seasoned salt. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes.
May be refrigerated and reheated in microwave.
Cut into squares.

title: black bean soup
directions: Soak beans overnight.
Drain and cook with 6 cups stock until tender, about 2 hours.
In large pot, heat oil; saute celery, onion and garlic until soft.
Add rice and saute 2 to 3 minutes longer. Stir in 1 cup stock from beans.
Add beans and rest of liquid in which they were cooked.
Add remaining ingredients except milk. Cook 1 to 2 hours.
Blend milk with 1/2 cup soup broth, add mixture to soup.
Serve garnished with chopped green onions and a drop of sour cream.

title: bird seed
directions: Mix all ingredients together and serve.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken and save the broth; brown the chicken pieces in butter and add the onion, bell pepper, pimentos and mushrooms.
In another pan, stir the cream of chicken soup and Velveeta until cheesy.
Cook spaghetti in chicken broth.
Spread spaghetti in baking dish and top with chicken, adding cream mixture on top of chicken.
Top layer with cheese mixture and bake until all cheese is melted.

title: middle eastern style dip
directions: In covered blender or food processor, combine all ingredients. Blend until smooth.
Serve at room temperature or chilled with pita bread.
Cut up fresh vegetables or use crackers for dipping.
Makes 2 1/4 cups.

title: chili rellenos casserole
directions: In large bowl, whisk eggs, sour cream and green onions. Sprinkle bottom of 13 x 9-inch dish with 3/4 cup Monterey Jack cheese.
Cover cheese with 1/2 the egg mixture, then, in equal portions, layer as follows: chilies, jalapenos, egg mixture, chilies, jalapenos and egg mixture.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: jello pudding dirt cups
directions: You will need 8 to 10 (7 ounce) plastic cups.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables as directed.
Put in baking dish.
Pour cream of mushroom soup (undiluted) over vegetables.
Cover with American cheese slices.
Crumble bread over cheese.
Melt oleo and pour over bread.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bread is lightly browned.

title: pan-broiled shrimp
directions: Use fresh or frozen uncooked shrimp.
Remove shell, leaving tail.
Remove black vein in back.
Melt butter in pan; add seasonings.
Stir-fry shrimp about 3 to 5 minutes.

title: rhubarb crunch
directions: Mix rhubarb, 3 tablespoons flour and sugar.
Pour into a greased 9 x 12-inch pan.
Mix brown sugar, 1 1/2 cups flour, butter and shortening with a fork.
Crumble mixture over rhubarb mixture.
Bake at 375° until brown (30 to 40 minutes).

title: sour cream chicken enchiladas
directions: Cook, cool, skin and debone chicken.
Cut or shred into small pieces.
Saute onion, pepper and celery.
Heat soup.
Add sour cream and chopped chiles to soup.
Add all ingredients thus far together.
Mix to blend well.

title: very good marshmallow salad
directions: Put small marshmallows in bowl. Add pineapple chunks. Add nuts and grapes. Let stand overnight in refrigerator.

title: mother's golden coconut custard
directions: Beat egg yolks.
Add cream or rich milk, sugar, vanilla, butter and coconut.
Mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes, and 325° for about 30 minutes or until set and light brown.
Top with meringue or just before serving, decorate with whipped cream.

title: best pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Pour into pie shell.
Bake 15 minutes at 425°, then reduce heat to 350°. Bake about 45 minutes longer or until inserted knife comes out clean.
Serve topped with whipped cream.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown beef; drain and add onions.
Add everything except cheese.
Simmer for 15 minutes, top with cheese and serve.

title: coffee tortoni
directions: Toast almonds and coconut until light brown.
Fold 4 tablespoons sugar, instant coffee and flavorings into whipped cream.
Beat egg whites until white.
Add 2 tablespoons sugar. Mix all together and put into cupcake liners and freeze.

title: porcupine meat balls
directions: Mix beef, rice and spices.
Roll into balls.
Place in casserole dish.
Mix soup and water.
Pour over meat balls. Cook, covered, in a 350° oven for about 45 minutes.

title: pistachio orange asparagus
directions: In a saucepan, bring 1 inch of water to a boil.
Place asparagus in a steamer basket over water.
Cover and steam for 5 minutes or until crisp-tender; drain.
Place asparagus on a serving platter and keep warm.

title: hawaiian bread
directions: In large bowl, combine 2 cups flour, yeast, salt, sugar, dry milk and 1 1/2 cups water to make thick batter.
Drop in eggs, one at a time; blend.
Work in 2 more cups flour.
Break butter into several pieces; drop into mixture.
Blend with 25 strong strokes with wooden spoon.
Work in coconut and nuts.
Add remaining flour, 1/2 cup at a time, to form a shaggy mass.
Sprinkle board with flour; turn out dough.
With rhythm of push, turn and fold, knead dough for about 7 minutes.
Return dough to bowl, cover with plastic wrap and leave at room temperature until double in size, about 1 hour.

title: custard
directions: Mix sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Add to milk when scalding.
Stir constantly until coats spoon.
Strain in jar.
Chill.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Cream together until smooth.
Spread on cooled Apple Nut Cake.

title: the best sugar cookie you ever ate or snitched!
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add next four ingredients together. Mix well.
Add dry ingredients.
Mix. Roll into balls.
Smoosh down with warm glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes until lightly browned on edges.
Frost with favorite icing.
Yields 5 to 6 dozen.

title: heavenly waffles
directions: Mix all together and bake in a preheated waffle iron.
These are delicious and so light and crisp.
Easy to stir up.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Cover pepperoni with water and boil 5 minutes; drain. Saute onions in 1 1/2 tablespoons butter. Pour remaining butter in 11 x 7 1/2-inch casserole dish. Toss spaghetti in butter. Cover with 8 ounces tomato sauce, 1/2 cup of Swiss cheese, 1/2 of the pepperoni, 1/2 of the sausage, 1/2 of Mozzarella cheese and all of mushrooms and onions. Sprinkle oregano and basil over mixture. Top with remaining Swiss cheese, pepperoni, sausage, tomato sauce and Mozzarella cheese. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: rum cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour 10-inch tube or 12-cup Bundt pan.
Sprinkle nuts over bottom of pan.
Mix all cake ingredients together.
Pour batter over nuts.
Bake 1 hour; cool. Invert on serving plate. Prick top to allow cake to absorb glaze. Repeat until glaze is used up.

title: baked barbecued shrimp
directions: Leave shells on shrimp, but slit down the back with a pear of scissors and remove vein.
Wash shrimp well; pat dry and spread in shallow pan.
Combine remaining ingredients except bread in small saucepan and let simmer for 10 minutes.
Cool to room temperature. Pour over shrimp and mix thoroughly.
Cover and refrigerate 2-3 hours, stirring every 30 minutes.
Preheat oven to 300 degrees. Bake shrimp, turning frequently, until they just turn pink, about 15-20 minutes; DO NOT OVERBAKE.
Adjust seasoning.
Serve in soup bowls with chunks of French bread to soak up the sauce and plenty of napkins.

title: mint juleps(20 servings)
directions: Combine first four ingredients in a glass container; stir until sugar is dissolved.
Cover; let stand overnight.
Strain mixture in large pitcher, discarding mint.
To serve, fill chilled glasses with shaved ice; add julep mixture and garnish with fresh mint sprigs.

title: italian meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 375° and lightly spray baking dish (shallow) with cooking oil.
Soak breads in 1 cup water.
Mash soaked bread with a fork.
Put ground beef in a mixing bowl.
Add bread, onion, parsley, cheese, egg, salt and pepper.
Mix well and dump into baking dish.
Shape into a loaf.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Pour tomato sauce over meat; sprinkle with oregano.
Bake for 20 minutes longer.
Serves 4 to 6.
Delicious served hot or cold.

title: sandwich spread
directions: Add tomatoes, onions, peppers, salt and water together.
Boil for 10 minutes.
Add to that mixture the vinegar, sugar and mustard.
Boil for 10 minutes more.
Add cornstarch and boil 10 minutes longer.
Makes about 8 pints.
Can and seal.

title: pumpkin pie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Remove 1 cup of the cake mix; reserve.
In small bowl, lightly beat 1 egg.
In large bowl, stir together remaining cake mix, melted butter and the beaten egg.
Press into prepared pan. In large bowl, lightly beat remaining 3 eggs.
Stir in pumpkin, 1/2 cup of the sugar, brown sugar, evaporated milk and cinnamon. Pour over cake mixture in pan.
To the 1 cup reserved cake mix, add remaining 1/2 cup sugar, walnuts and softened butter; mix until crumbly.
Sprinkle over pumpkin mixture.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes.
Serve warm or cool.
Preparation:
15 minutes; total time, 1 hour 40 minutes.

title: lemon cheese cake
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup boiling water until syrupy, set in refrigerator.
Let cream cheese soften to room temperature.
Stir together sugar, vanilla, lemon juice and cream cheese; stir until smooth.
Add jello.
Whip chilled Milnot with mixer until fluffy. Stir in cream cheese mixture, mix well.

title: english walnut pie
directions: Bake in a 9-inch unbaked pie shell.

title: chicken-bacon bites
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Trim crusts from bread and discard. Flatten bread slightly with a rolling pin.
Combine chicken spread and Worcestershire sauce and spread on bread slices.
Cut each slice into four squares.
Fold each square in half, spread side in,and wrap with piece of bacon.
Place bites on a broiler pan. Bake 40 minutes, turning halfway through.
Drain on paper towels. Serve warm.
Makes 2 dozen appetizers.

title: sausage dip
directions: Brown sausage and onion; drain.
Add other ingredients. Simmer until heated through, but do not boil.
Put in crock-pot on low to keep warm.
Serve with warm tortilla chips.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook hen in salt water (little onion and celery to taste). Make cream sauce of oleo, flour and milk.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Saute green pepper in mushroom juice.
Bone chicken and cut in cubes.
Add cheese, mushrooms, onion, green pepper, cooked spaghetti and cream sauce.
Mix well and bake in buttered baking dish for 30 minutes at 350° (or a little longer until brown).

title: marinade(good for all types of meat from venison to chicken)
directions: Mix ingredients in bowl and place meat in bowl.
Cover and marinate several hours or overnight.

title: fridgerated lemon cheese cake
directions: Put crumbs and butter together.
Press into oblong pan. Sprinkle 1/3 cup crumbs on top of cake.
Refrigerate.

title: grandma's swedish baked beans
directions: Mix all together in large roaster or crock-pot.
Cover and bake 1 hour at 325° or in crock-pot on medium or high for 1 to 2 hours.

title: beef brisket
directions: Place meat on heavy-duty foil.
Add all other ingredients. Marinate overnight in the refrigerator or for at least 6 hours. Cook in crock-pot on low heat for 10 hours.

title: no bake cookies
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan, bring first 4 ingredients to a boil for 1 minute and remove from heat.
Then add the remaining ingredients.
Drop from teaspoon onto waxed paper.

title: egg custard
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Beat eggs lightly.
Add sugar and salt. Blend well.
Add milk and vanilla.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Then reduce heat to 350° and bake 25 to 30 minutes.

title: sweet and sour balls
directions: Form meat into 1/2-inch balls; do not season.
Place in shallow pan; microwave for 2 minutes.
Turn occasionally until meat is firm; don't overcook.
Drain.
Melt jelly and catsup in electric skillet.
Place meat in mixture; simmer slowly for 1 1/2 hours.
Have toothpicks available for guests.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: hot chicken and rice salad
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Stir until mixed well.
Add next 6 ingredients.
Mix well.
Spoon into lightly greased dish. Combine corn flakes, almonds and butter and sprinkle on top.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: italian vegetable soup
directions: Brown beef in large pan; drain.
Add all the ingredients except cabbage, green beans and macaroni.
Bring to a boil. Lower heat; cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Add cabbage, green beans and macaroni.
Bring to a boil; simmer until vegetables are tender.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese before serving.

title: slum gullion
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in 2 tablespoons oil; add meat and brown.
Drain off oil and add salt and pepper, tomatoes and catsup. Simmer 15 minutes.
Cook macaroni; add and stir to mix. Simmer until served.
Serve with tossed salad and French bread. Serves 4 to 5.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown steak chunks in oil.
When done, stir in remaining ingredients.
Simmer for 15 minutes or microwave 10 minutes. Serve over rice or noodles.

title: arroz con pollo nuevo mexicano(chicken with rice, new mexican style)
directions: Heat 1/2 cup oil in a skillet; brown chicken pieces on all sides.
Drain chicken and reserve.
Add remaining oil to skillet. Add the rice.
Cook, stirring, until rice is transparent and golden.
Stir in garlic.
Set chicken on top of rice.
Pour in the broth or water and beer.
Stir in cumin, saffron, salt and pepper. Bring to a boil; simmer, covered, until rice is tender and liquid absorbed.
Stir in peas and reheat.
Serves 6.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Combine sugar, water and cinnamon.
Bring to boil and boil for about 3 minutes.
Remove from heat and add oleo.
Set aside.
Sift the remaining dry ingredients together.
Cut in shortening until mixture crumbles.
Add milk all at once and stir just until flour is moistened.
On lightly floured surface, roll dough and cut into rectangles.
Place apple on rectangle, add some cinnamon and dot with oleo.
Bring dough up around apple.
Place in ungreased baking pan.
Pour syrup over dumplings.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: buttermilk pancakes(for a large quantity)
directions: Can do both recipes on an electric grill set at 400°.
Turn pancakes when bubbles appear on top.
Enjoy!!

title: no bake cookies
directions: Combine sugar, butter and milk in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil for 2 minutes.
Bake off heat.
Add peanut butter, oats and vanilla.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper.

title: christmas fruit cake
directions: Mix spice cake as directed on the back of the box, then add blackberry preserves and then the remaining ingredients and mix well.

Grease and flour a tube pan and pour cake mix evenly in pan. Top with walnut and pecan halves and bake at 350° for 1 hour or using a toothpick and place in the cake and if it comes out clean, the cake is done.

title: souper tuna noodle bake
directions: In pan, cook onion in butter until tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into 2-quart baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until hot.
Stir. Top with sliced cheese and croutons. Bake until cheese melts.
Serves 6.

title: black bean salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and let sit a few hours.
Serve chilled.

title: custard pie
directions: Heat milk over low heat.
In bowl mix sugar, flour and eggs. Beat well.
Pour into heated milk.
Cook over medium heat until mixture boils.
Remove from heat; add vanilla.
Pour custard into prepared crust.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Yield:
8 servings (each with 295 calories).

title: company casserole
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions (do not overcook). Drain and rinse.
Cook meat until done; drain.
Return to skillet. Add salt, pepper, garlic and tomato sauce.
Simmer about 5 minutes. Combine cottage cheese, sour cream, onions, noodles and meat sauce in 2-quart casserole.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: creamy italian dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients, stir until smooth. Cover, chill. Makes 1 1/4 Cups.

title: hot pepper jelly
directions: Mix vinegar, peppers, sugar and salt.
Boil 1 minute and take off heat for 10 minutes.
Add coloring and Certo.
Let stand 10 more minutes, then skim.
Put in sterile jars and seal.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Bring tomato soup, sugar, vinegar, oil and Worcestershire sauce to a boil.
Pour boiled mixture over carrots, onion and green pepper.
Marinate overnight in refrigerator.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix together all ingredients and refrigerate for 24 hours before serving.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken; take off bone and tear pieces apart.
Boil noodles in chicken broth (save about 1 cup broth).
Mix everything including the extra broth and pour into Pyrex dish.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all together; bake at 375° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: cheesecake
directions: Beat cream cheese until fluffy, gradually add sugar.
Beat in sour cream and vanilla flavor (medium speed) until smooth.
Fold in Cool Whip (do not beat). Pour in crust and chill 2 hours.

title: corned beef sandwich
directions: Makes 6 nice sandwiches.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Mix milk, egg yolks and lemon juice together.
Pour in pie shell.
Top with meringue.
Bake.
Cool.
Place in refrigerator until cold before cutting.

title: onion blossom
directions: Take onion and cut in sections, but not all the way through. Take butter and put between wedges.
Sprinkle Cavender's and garlic salt on onion.
Put in bowl and put waxed paper over onion. Cook in microwave on High for 5 minutes.

title: grated sweet potato pone
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Pour mixture into lightly greased 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until slightly firm.
Stir twice during cooking.

title: chicken pie
directions: Cook chicken until tender.
Separate from bone in small pieces.
Place
in	12
x 9 x 2-inch pan.
In a saucepan, boil broth
and	cream of chicken soup.	Combine margarine, pepper, flour
and	buttermilk.
Pour broth mixture over chicken, then spoon batter
over	top.
Bake at 425° for 25 minutes or until brown.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Mix sugar and flour together.
Pour in milk; stir until smooth.
Melt butter in a 2-quart dish (tall sides) in oven.
Pour batter into dish.
Pour peaches onto batter.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: potato soup
directions: Fry
bacon
until
very crisp, then add onion and saute with a
little
water.
Set
aside and cook potatoes in large pan. When
potatoes
begin
to get soft add the bacon, onion, salt
and pepper.
Cook until the potatoes begin to get soupy. You may add a little milk if desired.

title: chocolate wacky cake
directions: No eggs, no milk cake.

title: cherry crunch
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into cake pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook, rinse and drain macaroni.
Mix all ingredients in order given, except mayonnaise and sour cream.
Mix these in small bowl and pour over all.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight before serving.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Melt oleo; add celery and onion.
Cook until almost tender. Add seasonings, Cheez Whiz and mushroom soup.
Beat slightly. Combine with drained broccoli and rice.
Bake in a greased casserole dish at 350° until it bubbles.
Add topping of bread crumbs and cheese and brown.

title: zucchini supper
directions: Beat eggs, milk and Bisquick; mix until smooth.
Add zucchini, onion, pepper and cheese.
Mix well.
Pour into greased 15-inch cookie sheet and bake, uncovered, in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate "frosty" ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients well in electric ice cream churn.
Churn will cut off when ice cream is made (about 20 to 30 minutes). Simple, easy and tastes just like a "frosty."

title: aunt liz's chocolate cake
directions: Blend together margarine, flour and nuts.
Spread into cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes; cool.
Blend cream cheese and powdered sugar together.
Fold in 2 cups Cool Whip.
Spread on cooled crust.
Mix chocolate pudding and milk.
Mix according to directions on package.
Spread on cream cheese layer.
Spread Cool Whip on top.
Sprinkle with chocolate curls.

title: uncooked cookies
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, margarine and milk.
Heat to boiling point in a large saucepan, stirring constantly.
Boil 1 1/2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add oats; beat well.
Add vanilla and peanut butter; beat well.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.

title: broccoli carrot cuts
directions: Mix cream cheese, dressing mix and mayonnaise.
Spread out crescent rolls on cookie sheet and bake; cool.
Spread mix over crescent sheet.
Sprinkle with diced vegetables.
Serve immediately.

title: company casserole
directions: Cook noodles.
Cook meat in skillet (drain off fat).
Add salt, pepper, butter, garlic salt and tomato sauce.
Simmer about 5 minutes; alternate layers of noodles and meat.
Top with cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: crispy caramel popcorn
directions: Heat oven to 250°.
Place popped corn in a large baking pan. Bring to a boil the sugar, syrup and oleo in a saucepan.
Cook 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add soda and extracts.
Pour over popcorn.
Stir.
Place in oven and bake for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: frozen slaw
directions: Cut the cabbage and mix with the salt.
Let stand for 1 hour, then add cut up celery and pepper.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding as directed.
Mix pudding, milk and Cool Whip. Layer: pudding mix, bananas and wafers, ending with wafers. Refrigerate.

title: cajun pasta and chicken
directions: Cook macaroni; brown chicken in 2 tablespoons oil.
Remove and add peppers and onions.
Remove and add remaining oil.
Stir in flour.
Stir until dark brown; add tomato to make thick sauce. Add chicken, onion and pepper to sauce.
Serve over macaroni.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients; mix well.
Combine eggs, oil and strawberries.
Add to dry ingredients, mixing well.
Pour batter into 2 greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: mom's baked crab salad in seashells
directions: Combine all ingredients, except buttered crumbs.
Place in greased shells and sprinkle with buttered crumbs.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° until crumbs are golden brown.
Serves 8.

title: bread pudding
directions: Cut buttered bread into finger-width pieces.
Arrange in layers in buttered baking dish.
Beat eggs slightly.
Add sugar, salt, vanilla and milk.
Sprinkle with cinnamon (optional) and 1/4 cup cooked, drained raisins (optional).
Bake at 325° for 1 hour. Serves 6.

title: special meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: hazel's bread pudding
directions: Place bread in baking dish.
Beat eggs, milk, sugar and salt together.
Pour over bread.
Add vanilla and mix in raisins. Place dish in a pan of hot water.
Bake at
350° for 40 minutes. Center of pudding should be firm.
Insert knife in middle, knife should come out clean, if not, cook longer.
Serves 4.

title: zucchini italiano
directions: Saute zucchini in butter 5 minutes; add remaining ingredients, stirring gently. Cover and simmer 5 to 7 minutes. Yields 2 servings.

title: deluxe lentil soup
directions: Saute onions and garlic in butter.
Add chopped bacon for extra flavor.

title: egg noodles
directions: For each egg, add next 4 ingredients.
Mix well.
Add enough flour to make stiff dough.
Roll dough out flat, then cover with thin layer of flour; roll like jelly roll.
Cut 1/2 way through lengthwise, then make thin slices across.
Drop into boiling chicken or beef broth, then simmer 30 minutes.

title: cheesy scalloped potatoes and ham
directions: Place potatoes and ham in 2-quart casserole.
Mix together soup, milk and cheese, heating until cheese is melted.
Pour over potatoes and ham in dish.
Place covered dish in 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes or until potatoes are tender.

title: green bean casserole
directions: In a large nonstick skillet, saute onion and ground beef.
Add mushrooms and seasoning.
Cook a few minutes.
Add broth and tomato juice, then add beans.
Simmer in skillet or put in a 2-quart casserole dish and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: tasty crescent hamburgers
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Add sour cream, celery soup and crumbled onion rings to drained hamburger; mix well.
Flatten crescent rolls out on flat surface 1 at a time.
Place large spoonful of meat mixture in center of roll.
Bring edges up over meat mixture.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake until brown; don't overcook.

title: lentil and barley stew
directions: Saute in oil, celery, onion, cumin and garlic.
Add water and lentils; cook 20 minutes.
Add tomatoes, barley, salt, pepper and herbs.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Add carrots and simmer another 20 to 30 minutes.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: *Add 1 at a time.

title: creole icing
directions: Combine butter, coffee, cocoa and cinnamon.
Gradually add sugar, beating to spreading consistency.
Makes 1 1/2 cups icing or enough for an 8 or 9-inch layer cake.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Combine yeast and water; let stand 5 minutes or until bubbly. Add buttermilk to yeast mixture and set aside.
Combine dry ingredients in a large bowl.
Cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Add buttermilk mixture, mixing with fork until dry ingredients are moistened.
Turn dough out on a floured surface and knead lightly about 3 or 4 times.
Roll dough in 1/2-inch thickness; cut into rounds with a 2-inch cutter and place on lightly greased baking sheets.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Yield:
About 3 dozen.

title: cucumber cottage cheese salad
directions: Dissolve jello, sugar and lemon juice in hot water.
Add cottage cheese, salad dressing, onion, cucumber and ground nuts. Thoroughly mix all ingredients and place in mold.
Chill several hours.
Unmold before serving.

title: pecan cheese treats(serves 20)
directions: Sift flour and pepper together.
Soften margarine and combine with cheese; stir in flour and pepper.
Mix until dough is smooth. Roll by hand into 35 to 36 small balls.
Cut each ball in half to add pecan; shape dough around pecans.
Put on ungreased cookie sheet and chill in refrigerator 15 minutes.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, using 3/4 dressing mix.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle remaining dressing mix on top. Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: marble squares
directions: Combine margarine, water and chocolate in saucepan; bring to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Stir in flour, sugar, soda and salt. Add eggs and sour cream; mix well.
Pour into greased 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan.

title: country steak
directions: Cut steak into strips and roll in flour; brown all sides.
Add onion and green pepper.
Salt and pepper.
Add water and simmer on medium heat until tender, about 1 hour.
Take 2 to 3 tablespoons of cornstarch and water and make slightly thick paste.
Add to steak to make gravy.
Add water if necessary.

title: orange sticky buns
directions: Add grated rind of oranges to sugar.
Melt butter and add to orange juice.
Spray inside of Bundt pan with vegetable spray. Separate biscuits and dip in melted butter.
Mix and then add sugar and rind mix.
Place in pan in layers, pouring any remaining juice and sugar over buns.
Bake at 385° for 35 minutes.
Turn upside-down on serving dish.
Be careful to avoid splashing of hot syrup.

title: artichoke parmesan quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 450 degrees.
Line a 9 inch deep dish pie plate with pastry.
Prick bottom & sides several times with fork. Bake 7 to 8 minutes until it begins to brown; set aside.
Decrease oven temperature to 400 degrees.

title: lemon glaze
directions: Heat milk and butter.
Pour over sugar.
Stir and add lemon juice. Pour on cake while hot.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Cut stems from green peppers and remove seeds.
Cook in boiling water for 5 minutes.
Mix ground meat with bread crumbs, onions, milk, salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Fill peppers and bake, covered, for 45 minutes, uncovered for 15 minutes.

title: cream cheese cake
directions: Mix butter, cream cheese and water. Add sugar oil and eggs. Mix well with electric mixer. Add cake mix and mix thoroughly. Pour in bundt pan and bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, soda and salt. Add sugar to shortening; mix well. Blend in eggs and vanilla. Add flour mixture gradually. Mix well. Spread in 13 x 9 pan. Sprinkle with chips and nuts. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Cool in pan. Cut into bars. Makes 48.

title: persimmon cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees.

title: raspberry pretzel dessert
directions: Mix above together as first layer.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes and cool.

title: one dish supper
directions: Brown the ground beef, add onions and bell pepeer, pour off the excess grease.
Add the cooked rice, one can of the tomato soup.
Cut the cabbage into about 4 inch pieces.

Butter the bottom and sides of the pan, cover the bottom with a layer of cabbage, then rice and ground beef mixture, then top with remaining cabbage and spread the second can of soup over the cabbage.

title: icebox rolls
directions: Pour boiling water over shortening, sugar and salt.
Blend by cutting up shortening.
Dissolve yeast in cup of warm water.
Add to eggs and mixture.
Add flour and blend well.
Cover with foil and place in refrigerator at least 4 hours before rolling.
Roll out as needed; cut rolls with biscuit cutter, then fold in half. Let rise in pan 2 hours before baking.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Thaw broccoli.
Heat butter, onion, mushroom soup and cheese until bubbly.
Add rice and broccoli and mix well.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish and bake for 30 to 40 minutes at 325°.

title: dirt
directions: Crush Oreo cookies. Mix together cream cheese, butter and confectioners sugar. Combine milk, pudding mix and vanilla until thick. Mix together pudding and cream cheese mixture, then mix in Cool Whip. Layer Cool Whip mixture alternately with crushed Oreo cookies, beginning with Cool Whip mixture. Chill.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix dry ingredients, then add liquid.
Mix.
Add salad oil very little at a time.
Pour over apples, bananas, canned pineapple, grapes, oranges, peaches and strawberries.

title: baked ham in paper bag
directions: You will also need 2 brown paper grocery bags.

title: chocolate or coconut cream pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and salt.
Scald milk.
Add to sugar mixture a little at a time.
Beat egg yolks, stir in some of the hot mixture then add both mixtures together.
Cook on low heat until real thick.
Remove from heat and add butter and vanilla.
Add coconut. Beat egg whites until fluffy.
Add 6 tablespoons sugar and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Fold in 1/4 egg white mixture into pie and pour into baked pie shell.
Top with remaining egg whites and bake until brown.

title: carrot cake
directions: Combine all ingredients except carrots.
Beat until smooth, then add carrots.
Pour batter into 2 greased and floured 9-inch round cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool in pans 10 minutes, then remove from pans and let cool before icing.

title: indiana date pudding
directions: Boil the brown sugar and water for 3 minutes.
Pour into a 9 x 13 pan.
Mix together the sugar and oleo, then add milk, flour, baking powder, chopped nuts and diced dates.
Spoon batter mixture by spoonfuls into water/brown sugar mixture.
Bake at 350° until brown on top.

title: rice casserole
directions: Put all in casserole dish and bake covered at 350° for 30 minutes.
Stir.
Continue baking covered for 30 more minutes.

title: pineapple and squash
directions: Do not peel young, tender squash.
Combine with water, sugar and vinegar.
Cook until tender (do not overcook).
Add pineapple and bring back to a boil.
Spoon into sterilized jars and seal. Makes 3 or 4 pints.
Serve chilled.
(Something different.)

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Melt butter.
Add remaining ingredients. Mix well.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Serve as soon as removed from oven, preferably with ice cream or Cool Whip.

title: prune cake
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add oil and prunes.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Add nuts.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool in pan.
When cold, turn out and sift powdered sugar over top.

title: cheesy grits and vegetables
directions: Prepare grits as directed on the package. Add cheese and margarine, stirring until melted. Beat eggs in a small bowl. Stir a small amount of the hot mixture into eggs, then combine eggs with hot mixture, mixing well. Fold in thawed mixed vegetables. Pour mixture into a lightly greased 2-quart casserole. Microwave on High power for 12 to 15 minutes or until thoroughly heated, turning dish twice during cooking if not using a rotation table. Let stand for 5 minutes before serving.

title: shrimp fettucini
directions: Saute onion, bell pepper, celery and garlic in large pot.
Add parsley and shrimp; cook 10 minutes.
Add flour, half and half cream and cheese, stirring until cheese is melted, over medium-low heat. Cover and simmer 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Boil, drain and rinse noodles.
Stir into shrimp mixture.
Pour into buttered 13 x 9-inch glass casserole dish; top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until cheese is melted. (Crawfish can be used.)

title: christmas eve she crab soup
directions: In top of double boiler heat milk, mace and lemon peel.
Let simmer 7 minutes.
Add crab, butter and cream.
Heat over boiling water.
Remove peel.
Add cracker crumbs and seasonings and let stand.
Add sherry and crumbled egg yolks to bottom of soup cup before serving.
Serves 6.

title: goulash
directions: Cook onion, garlic and bell peppers in oil. Add meat, salt and pepper. Cook until done. Drain. Add tomato sauce, tomatoes, worcestershire. Simmer about 1 hour. Cook elbow macaroni. Mix with meat sauce. Cover, turn heat off and let set. It if gets to dry just add a little water. Sprinkle cheese on each serving. Serve with salad and garlic toast.

title: preacher's casserole
directions: Brown hamburger.
Grease casserole pan (9 x 13-inch).
Sliver onion on bottom of pan.
Press hamburger over onion.
Salt and pepper.
Pour mushroom soup over hamburger.
Add tomato soup over mushroom soup.
Layer frozen Tater Tots over top.
Sprinkle salt on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: oleta cherry cheese pie
directions: Whip softened cream cheese.
Add sugar and beat until smooth. Add Cool Whip and flavorings.
Mix well until fluffy but do not overbeat.
Will be runny if overbeaten.
Put in graham cracker shell and add cherry pie filling ring for decoration.
Makes 2 pies.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash, onions and bell pepper with salt and pepper in small amount of water until tender; drain.
Mix soup, milk, egg, cheese and cracker crumbs.
Layer with squash mixture in a casserole.
Top with bacon and more cheese.
Bake at 375° until done.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake in 2 layers as directed on box; let cool.
Mix vanilla pudding as directed and set aside.
Crumble 1 layer of cake in bottom of punch bowl, then layer 1/2 pineapple, 1/2 pudding mix, 1/2 strawberries, 1/2 nuts, 1/2 coconut, 1/2 Cool Whip and 1/2 of cherries.
Repeat layers, leaving enough Cool Whip, nuts and cherries to sprinkle on top.

title: burnt sugar pie
directions: Brown 1 cups sugar until golden and add enough hot water to make a syrup.
Then add to warm milk.
Then add these ingredients mixed together in a small bowl.
1/3 cup sugar, 1/4 tsp. salt, 4 eggs separated, (save the whites for the meringue), 1/2 cup or 6 Tbsp. cornstarch, and 1/3 cup milk.
Mix well and add to milk and cook until thickened.
Pour into pie shells.
Cover with meringue and brown in oven.

title: meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together thoroughly hamburger, crackers and tomato sauce in a large bowl.
Combine and mix together well egg, salt, pepper and onion or onion salt.
Add egg mixture to hamburger mixture and mix together thoroughly.
Shape in 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake for 1 hour.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: teriyaki sauce
directions: Mix. Cut steak into 1-inch cubes.
Clean fresh mushrooms.
Soak meat and mushrooms for 2 hours.
Saute meat and mushrooms.
Serve warm.

title: pasties (a meat pie)
directions: Lay 1 pie crust flat.
In center, place 3/4 cup diced potatoes.
Layer about 1/2 cup diced meat on top, followed by 1/4 cup diced onions.
Sprinkle with about 1 teaspoon salt and 1/2 teaspoon pepper (more or less, to taste).
Bring edges of dough up over filling.
Moisten with water and crimp to seal tightly.
Poke 2 holes on each side of crimp to vent steam.
Carefully pour 1/4 cup water into one of the holes.
Place on cookie sheet and bake 50 minutes at 350°.

title: perfect pizza
directions: Combine water, oil, sugar and salt in a large mixing bowl. Sprinkle yeast over water mixture until dissolved.
Add flour gradually.
Mix well after each addition.

title: cherries jubilee
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Spread pineapple in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add cherry pie filling.
Spread dry cake mix over top.
Melt butter and pour over this.
Place in oven for 30 minutes.
Take out and sprinkle nuts over top.
Put back in oven for 30 minutes longer.

title: whiskey sours
directions: Mix well, chill and Enjoy!!

title: peach cobbler
directions: Put 1 stick or 1/2 cup margarine in a deep baking dish and set in oven to melt.

title: sayyadiyyi(fish with rice)
directions: Wash fish; salt inside and out.
Let stand for 1 hour.
Fry fish in olive oil.
Set in platter.
Remove heads from fried fish and boil in 2 cups water on medium heat about 1/2 hour.
Strain liquid.
Brown onions until golden brown in fish residue, adding more olive oil if needed.
Add rice, cumin, salt and pepper. Saute rice with onions for a few minutes.
Add strained liquid to measure 4 cups.
Add water if additional liquid is needed.
Cover and cook over medium heat for 20 minutes.
Then simmer for 10 additional minutes until rice is done.
Place rice on platter. Debone fish and put over rice.
Garnish with lemon wedges.

title: goop
directions: Mix everything and put into crock-pot and cook on high for two hours.

title: soft taco shells
directions: Combine ingredients in bowl; beat with rotary beater until smooth.
Use 1/4 cup or 1/2 cup measuring cup of batter.
Pour on hot griddle.
Quickly smooth out batter in thin circle, using the bottom of the measuring cup.
If a hole appears, just drop more batter in, then smooth out.
Bake until done.

title: fried plantain
directions: Peel and slice plantain.
Using large frying pan, fry plantain until brown.
(Be careful not to have frying pan too hot).
Serve hot or warm.
Can be served with rice and any type of meat.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place in greased dish.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Top with slightly crumbled potato chips and shredded cheese.
Bake 15 minutes longer.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown ground beef and onion together and drain excess fat (if onion salt is used, add after draining).
Add salt (unless onion salt is used) and pepper to taste.
Combine ground beef mixture, tomato sauce, oregano, garlic salt, Italian seasoning.
Cook in slow cooker on low heat for 3 to 5 hours.

title: chicken and wine with rice
directions: Put chicken and water in roaster (no cover).
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Add both cans of soup and wine.
(Mix soups together before adding to roaster.)
Put soups and wine in roaster.
Cook another 30 to 40 minutes.
Serve chicken and sauce over bed of rice.
Sauce also tastes great over green beans.

title: meat loaf
directions: Beat eggs lightly; add to meat, oatmeal and chopped onion. Combine white horseradish, salt, dry mustard, milk and ketchup. Add to meat mixture and shape into loaf.
Place on flat baking pan and spread 1/2 cup ketchup on top.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 minutes.

title: old fashioned molasses cookies
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add one egg and mix well.
Stir in molasses.
Stir soda into hot water and mix with molasses mixture. Add flour gradually to make a stiff enough dough to roll.
Roll on floured board and cut out shapes with a cookie cutter.
Put on greased cookie sheet and bake in a 350° oven for 12 minutes.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt the first 3 ingredients together in the microwave or in the top of a double boiler.
Pour over the cereal in a large bowl. Mix well.
Put the powdered sugar and cereal in a grocery bag and shake well.

title: curry-cajun spiced chicken
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, combine honey, water, mustard, melted oleo, Cajun seasoning, curry powder, lemon juice and garlic; mix well.
Add chicken, turning to coat.
Arrange in single layer. Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 30 minutes, or until chicken is tender and no longer pink.

title: southern scripture cake
directions: Mix all together.
Bake in 300° oven about 2 1/2 hours.

title: chicken wiggle
directions: Boil chicken in water (salted).
Pick off bone.
Mix Parkay, pimentos, peppers, onions and mushrooms; cook tender.
Add English peas and chicken.
Cook noodles (curly noodles are best) in chicken broth.
Mix all together.
Add both sauces last.
Simmer until well seasoned.

title: scurry supper casserole
directions: Brown and drain hamburger; place in large casserole dish for first layer.
Layer 1 can drained corn, then 1 can mushrooms and onions.
Then layer drained green beans.
Next place frozen Tater Tots side by side, covering top of casserole.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve with hot bread and butter.

title: low-fat hunter-style chicken
directions: Saute bacon, cut into 1-inch pieces, in a large skillet until partially cooked, then add onion and continue to cook until onion is tender.
Remove bacon and onion and brown chicken breasts in drippings (there will be hardly any if you use turkey bacon). Sprinkle lightly with salt and pepper.
Drain any fat from pan and combine cooked bacon and onion with tomatoes, Heinz 57 sauce and sugar and add to chicken.
Cover and simmer 45 minutes, basting occasionally.
Great
with hot rice.

title: favorite pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 10-inch tube or Bundt pan.
Cream
butter and shortening.
Gradually add sugar until light and
fluffy.	Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine flour and baking powder.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk and extracts.
Beat well after each addition.
Pour
into
prepared pan and bake 1 1/2 hours or until cake tests done.
Cool in pan 5 minutes before removing to rack to cool completely.
Freezes well.
Yields 16 servings.

title: english muffin loaves
directions: In a large bowl, combine 3 cups flour, yeast, sugar, salt and soda.
Set aside.

title: corn cakes
directions: Add cornmeal to
water
in
saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until thick and bubbly.
Sift together flour, sugar, salt and baking powder.
Add to cornmeal mixture alternating sifted dry ingredients
and
milk;
stir
with large spoon.
Stir in oil, then
add
eggs.
Stir
well and fry like you would pancakes.
I use
a
ladle to dip batter out.
Serve with butter and your favorite syrup.

title: no-crust brownie pie
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Slowly add sugar and salt.
Fold in cookie crumbs.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Pour into buttered 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.
Cool.
Cover with Cool Whip and few cookie crumbs or grated chocolate.

title: artichoke spread
directions: Chop artichokes.
Add other ingredients.
Bake in pie plate or small casserole 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: blueberry bread
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and milk.
Add melted butter, flour, salt and baking powder.
Flour 2 cups blueberries and fold into batter. Pour into 2 greased loaf pans, 9 x 5 x 3-inches.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Combine sugar, syrup, peanuts and water in heavy saucepan. Cook until peanuts turn brown and quits popping.
Add soda and pour onto buttered platter, spreading thin; allow to cool.
Remove from dish and break.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Cream oil, margarine, sugar and add eggs and raw zucchini and mix well; add vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients together and add alternately with milk.
Place batter in greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: apple-walnut cake
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients; mix well. Add flour, soda and cinnamon; mix well. Fold in apple, walnuts and coconut.
Spoon into greased and floured tube pan. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours. Cool on rack 15 minutes. Turn into cake plate.
Drizzle Buttermilk Glaze over warm cake.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine broccoli, raisins and onion.
In small bowl, combine sugar, vinegar and mayonnaise.
Pour over broccoli mixture.
Toss to coat.
Refrigerate.
Sprinkle with bacon and seeds before serving.

title: rice and sausage casserole
directions: Fry sausage and drain grease. Mix all ingredients. Bake 350° oven covered for 1 1/4 hour, then 15 minutes uncovered.

title: crock-pot potato soup
directions: Put all ingredients, except evaporated milk and ham in crock-pot.
Cover and cook on low for 8 to 9 hours.
Stir in evaporated milk and ham during the last hour.

title: waikiki meatballs
directions: Mix meat, crumbs, onion, egg, salt, ginger and milk. Shape mixture by rounded tablespoonfuls.
Brown meat and remove.
Keep warm.
Pour out fat from pan.
Mix cornstarch, sugar, reserved pineapple juice, vinegar and soy sauce until thick.
Pour into pan.
Cook over medium heat.
Stir until it thickens and boils. Boil and stir 1 minute. Add meatballs, pineapple and green pepper. Heat and serve.

title: white acre peas or field peas
directions: Brown sausage in a little grease.
Add peas, salt, pepper and liquid smoke.
Boil for 1 1/2 hours on medium-high.
Pour water until is about 1-inch above peas.
Add water, as needed.
Let cook down last 15 minutes.

title: apple dapple cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients; add next 3 ingredients, blending well. Add remaining ingredients. Bake in tube pan 1 1/2 hours at 325°. Be sure to grease and flour pan.

title: cheesy hash browns
directions: Mix together and place in a 9x13 inch pan.
Add topping (below) and bake.

title: bandito buffalo wings(makes 2 dozen appetizers)
directions: Place seasoning mix in heavy plastic bag. Add a few chicken pieces.
Shake until well coated.
Repeat to coat all pieces. Place in lightly greased baking pan.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes or until done.
Serve hot with salsa for dipping.

title: my mother-in-law's german chocolate icing
directions: Beat egg yolks; add milk, sugar and butter.
Cook until thick (about 12 minutes).
Take off heat; add remaining ingredients. Cool before putting on cake.
(This is delicious on Duncan Hines German chocolate cake mix.)

title: jerky
directions: Cut all fat off meat.
Cut into 1/8 to 1/4-inch strips. Combine above ingredients in bowl and stir until dissolved.
Add meat strips and mix to coat all pieces.
Let stand or cover and refrigerate overnight.
Place meat strips (not overlapping) on cake racks in shallow rimmed baking pans.
Dry meat at lowest temperature (160° to 200°) until it has turned brown and feels dry and hard to the touch.
Let cool.
Store in airtight bags or in jar with a tight fitted lid.
Chicken and turkey, 4 to 5 hours. Beef and deer, 4 to 7 hours.

title: baked bean casserole
directions: Saute onion in oil.
Combine all remaining ingredients in large bowl; add onion and mix thoroughly.
Put into a 2-quart casserole and bake, uncovered, in preheated 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: peanut butter oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, butter and milk in a saucepan; bring to a boil.
Boil for one minute.
Remove from heat; add peanut butter, oatmeal, vanilla and salt.
Stir to mix well.
Drop from a spoon onto wax paper.
Let cool thoroughly; then they are ready to eat.
Makes approximately 20 cookies.

title: fried rice
directions: In large skillet over medium heat saute veggies.
Add everything to veggies, season with garlic and pepper to taste. Add soy sauce to make it your favorite soy taste.
Serve with good French or Italian bread.
A great way to make a good meal, use up leftovers and stretch that before pay day meal.

title: sauerkraut balls
directions: Brown sausage and add onion.
Add remaining ingredients except eggs & milk.
Chill mixture.
Roll in 3/4 inch balls.
Dip in flour, then egg and milk mixture, then roll in additional bread crumbs.
Deep fry.
Drain and cool.
May be frozen.

title: lima beans new orleans
directions: Cook lima beans following package directions.
Drain if necessary.
Add vinegar, olive oil, salt, pepper, parsley and garlic to limas in saucepan.
Heat thoroughly and then mix in lemon juice.
Serve immediately.
Serves 4.

title: bobbie's fruit compote
directions: Pour pineapple and juice over all fruit in baking pan.
Seal with double foil tightly.
Bake at 325° for one hour.

title: minute rice meatballs
directions: Mix soup with water.
Combine remaining ingredients with 1/2 cup of soup mixture; mix just to blend.
Shape into balls.
Place in skillet and brown.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Blend sugar, mayonnaise and vinegar.
Beat until creamy.
Pour over other ingredients.
Chill.
Best if made several hours ahead.

title: nut strips
directions: Mix syrup and milk.
Cut crust from bread and slice each in 3 or 4 slices.
(Freezing bread or using old bread is good.) Dip each
strip
in
syrup mixture, then in nuts.
Bake in 325° oven for about 15 minutes.

title: pork chop neapolitan
directions: Wipe chops with damp paper towel.
In hot oil in large skillet, brown chops well on both sides.
Remove from skillet.
Drain all but 1 tablespoon drippings from skillet.
Add onion and garlic; saute until tender (about 5 minutes).
Add tomatoes, salt, oregano, basil and pepper; mix well, mashing tomatoes with fork.
Place pork chops in skillet.
Arrange green pepper and mushrooms between chops.
Simmer, covered, for 1 1/4 hours or until chops are tender. Makes 6 servings.

title: miniature shrimp quiches
directions: Brush tart shells with a mixture of beaten egg and a little milk for a brown glaze.
Divide the Parmesan cheese, chopped shrimp and Swiss cheese among the tart shells.
Mix egg yolks, cream, Tabasco and salt; fill shells with mixture.
Bake in 325° oven for 15 minutes.

title: veggie dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and cut desired vegetables, etc.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Cut up fryer into pieces of desired size. Sprinkle liberally with salt and lemon pepper. Add 1/2 teaspoon each of salt and pepper to 1 cup of flour in a paper bag; coat the chicken with the flour mixture. The true secret of taste is to give the seasoning time to take effect, so place the covered chicken pieces in the refrigerator for a couple of hours or more. Cook in a deep fat fryer in oil at 375°. Remove when golden brown and watch closely as small pieces will be ready earlier.
tags: cream of chicken and mushroom soup

title: italian meat loaf
directions: Combine eggs, bread crumbs, tomato sauce, parsley, oregano, salt, pepper, garlic and ground beef; mix well.
Take 1/2 of the meat mixture and put in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Lay pepperoni and cheese on top.
Add the rest of the ground beef, sealing edges so cheese will not run out.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: aurel's 4-layer dessert
directions: Mix together flour, margarine and nuts; press into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 375°; set aside to cool.

title: fajitas
directions: Trim excess fat from beef steak.
Prick beef with fork in several places.
Mix 1/4 cup oil, the vinegar, sugar, oregano, chili powder, garlic powder, salt and pepper in ungreased square baking dish (8 x 8 x 2-inches).
Place beef in dish, turning once, to coat both sides.
Cover and refrigerate at least 8 hours, turning meat occasionally.
Broil beef with top about 3 inches from heat about 8 minutes or until brown.
Turn.
Brush beef with marinade.
Broil until done.
Saute onions and peppers in oil. Cut beef diagonally into very thin slices.

title: eldorado toll house pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Rub with butter a 9-inch pie plate. Beat eggs until foamy.
Add flour and sugars; beat until well blended.
Blend in melted butter.
Stir in chocolate chips and walnuts.
Bake for 25 minutes or until set and light golden. Serve in wedges with ice cream.
Makes 8 servings.

title: pennsylvania dutch amish cheese pie
directions: While pie cools, mix ingredients in blender, then pour on top of pie.
Put in 350° oven for 10 minutes.
Remove and refrigerate until cold.
Sprinkle top with almond slivers.

title: spinach salad
directions: Wash spinach and drain well on paper towels.
Break into smaller pieces in a large salad bowl.
Add other ingredients.

title: preacher cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients and mix by hand.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: baby tea(ground ivey,  for hives)
directions: Gather.
Trim off bad leaves.
Wash.
Place in cooker.
Add water enough to cover.
Bring to a boil; drain off tea from leaves (run through fine strainer).
Add sugar.
Give to baby about 2 ounces at a time.
Twice a day or 3 times if needed to make baby break out good.
Baby will look a lot like having measles.
