title: easy lasagna
directions: Saute beef until brown and crumbly.
Drain excess fat; season with salt, pepper, garlic powder and Italian seasoning.
Cook; drain and separate noodles.
In a large baking pan, spread a thin layer of sauce.
Top with 1/3 noodles, 1/3 cottage cheese, 1/3 Mozzarella cheese, 1/3 meat sauce and 1/3 Parmesan cheese.
Repeat layering 2 more times, ending with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; drain.
Add Prego spaghetti sauce and sugar, cook until done.
Beat egg and add to cottage cheese. Shred cheese.

title: garlic dip
directions: Place cottage cheese in a blender with yogurt; process on medium speed until smooth.
Combine with remaining ingredients and chill.
Serve with raw vegetables.

title: rice pudding
directions: Combine milk, rice, pudding mix, raisins and egg in saucepan. Stir over medium heat until mixture comes to boil.
Cool 5 minutes stirring twice.
Pour into dessert dishes and sprinkle with cinnamon and nutmeg.

title: ortega chili casserole
directions: Grease an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Layer Ortega chilies, zucchini and cheese.
Repeat 3 times.
Beat eggs, milk, salt and pepper to taste.
Add Bisquick to egg mix.
Mix well.
Pour over zucchini. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Place in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda and cinnamon together.
Add oil, eggs and salt.
Beat for 2 minutes.
Add carrots.
Grease and flour 2 (9-inch) cake pans.
Pour in batter and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour; add milk and egg yolks.
Add butter. Cook until thickens, stirring always.
Take off; add vanilla. Pour into unbaked shell and bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: picnic pecan pie
directions: Place sugar, butter or margarine, corn syrup and vanilla in a large bowl.
Mix well.
Stir in eggs; mix well.
Add pecans; mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake in a preheated 375° oven for 1 hour or until firm.
After it is cool, slice and serve.

title: applesauce
directions: Peel apples.
Slice into large pot (no cores, stems or seeds) on medium heat.
Add water while cooking as needed.
Stir often. Keep some chunks in it if you like, as apples melt down, add cinnamon to taste.
Turn on low.
Put cover on and cook until you like it.
Keeps pretty long in jars in refrigeration.
(Can add other fruit, if desired.)

title: dennis' all-american cornbread
directions: Important to scald cream with butter; add to thoroughly mixed dry ingredients.
Mix in eggs.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Allow to stand for several minutes before cutting.
Yields 12 servings.

title: yummy bars
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Mix cake mix, butter and evaporated milk.
Pour 1/2 of batter in pan; sprinkle with 1/2 cup walnuts.
Bake for 9 minutes at 350°.
Meanwhile microwave 1/3 cup evaporated milk with caramels.
After cake has cooled, sprinkle chocolate chips over top of cake, then drizzle melted caramel mixture over and melt together.
Pour the other half of cake batter over.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup walnuts on top.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°. Cool and cut into bars.

title: cappuccino cooler
directions: In blender, combine coffee, ice cream and chocolate syrup. Cover and blend until smooth. Serve immediately over crushed ice. Garnish with whipped cream.
Makes 3 (8 ounce) servings.

title: secret teriyaki sauce(enough for 2 lbs.  meat)
directions: Combine sugars, shoyu, water, garlic, and ginger in a 1-2 quart saucepan.
Bring to a boil and boil for 5 minutes.
Remove pot from heat and cool.
Whisk in oils to cooled marinade.
Add 2-4 lbs. sliced beef flank or other meat, thinly sliced, and marinate overnight.
Grill meat over charcoal for 3-4 minutes each side.
Serve with rice.

title: lemon nut bread
directions: Cream together the shortening and sugar.
Add eggs to sugar mixture.
Sift together the flour, baking powder and salt.
Add alternately with 1/2 cup of milk.
Mix in nuts and peel of lemon. Bake in a loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour or 2 small loaf pans and bake until done (less time).

title: french salad dressing(yields 2 cups)
directions: Chop onion and bell pepper very fine.
Set aside.
Put salad oil, sugar, ketchup, vinegar, Worcestershire sauce and salt into blender.
Mix well.
Pour into bowl with onion and bell pepper. Chill until cold.
Ready to serve.

title: chocolate chip cookies 2
directions: In a large mixing bowl beat the butter with an electric mixer on medium to high speed for 30 seconds.
Add the brown sugar, and baking soda.
Beat mixture until combined, scraping the bowl occasionally.
Beat in the eggs and vanilla until combined.
Beat in as much of the flour as you can with mixer.
Using a wooden spoon, stir in any remaining flour.
Stir in chocolate pieces and, if desired, nuts.
Drop the dough by rounded teaspoons 2 inches apart on an ungreased cookie sheet.

title: chicken hash in pancakes
directions: Mix and sift dry ingredients.
Beat egg and add to milk.
Mix rapidly with dry ingredients, beating well.
Grease an 8-inch skillet lightly.
Pour in a small quantity of batter.
Tip the skillet so that the batter covers the whole bottom thinly.
Cook over moderate heat until under side is brown.
Turn to brown other side.
Grease again and make another pancake.
This recipe will make four or five of these large, thin cakes, which are like French crepes, but unsweetened.
Spread each pancake with Chicken Hash and roll it up.
Place in large shallow ovenproof dish, sprinkle with a little cheese or buttered fine bread crumbs and brown in broiler, 5 inches below the flame.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix in canner.
Can then be stored for an all-winter drink. Use 3 or 4 teaspoons (heaping) to a cup of hot water.
Enjoy!

title: south coast hominy
directions: Melt butter in saucepan; add onion and green pepper and saute for 5 minutes.
Blend in flour and seasonings.
Add milk and cook, stirring, until mixture thickens and comes to a boil.
Add grated cheese and stir until melted.
Remove from heat; add olives and hominy.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish; sprinkle with buttered bread crumbs and bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until crumbs are brown.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: tomato and basil linguine
directions: In a large pot of boiling salted water, cook linguine and broccoli until just tender, 2 to 3 minutes; drain well.
Transfer to a large bowl.
Add all remaining ingredients except cheese and toss with linguine and broccoli.
Serve warm, at room temperature, or chilled.
Pass a bowl of grated Parmesan cheese on the side.

title: pork chops and sour cream
directions: Brown chops in oil in skillet.
Mix all remaining ingredients, except onion rings and sour cream, in bowl.
Separate onion rings and place on chops.
Pour mixture over chops.
Simmer for 1 hour and 15 minutes, covered slightly.
Add the sour cream and cook for 1/2 hour longer or until very tender.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Soften cream cheese; add chilies, olives and Cheddar cheese. Warm flour tortillas and spread with cream cheese mixture.
Roll the tortilla and chill through.
Slice in 1-inch slices and arrange on a plate.
Serve picante sauce on the side for dipping.

title: dump cake
directions: Layer pineapple, coconut, cake mix and pecans, in that order, in a 13 x 11-inch loaf pan.
Dot with oleo, sliced on top.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Dredge fruit in 1/2 cup extra flour.
Cream butter and sugar; add eggs separately.
Mix dry ingredients and add to butter and sugar.
Add nuts and fruit.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 12 to 20 minutes at 270° or 300°.

title: chicken ala king
directions: Blend flour and salt; add broth and milk. Mix well. Add remaining ingredients to sauce; heat thoroughly.

title: ham loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients thoroughly.
Bake in a loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour.
Dot top with pineapple cubes.

title: bloody cooler
directions: Combine all in a blender.
Blend until ice cubes are dissolved. Pour into large glass and garnish with a lemon wedge.

title: stuffed tomatoes with rice
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Wash, cut off top and scoop out tomatoes.
Saute in oil with onions.
Add salt, pepper and parsley.
Wash and drain rice; add to onions with inside of tomatoes.
Stir well for few minutes.
Then stuff tomatoes with this mixture.
Replace tomato tops.
Place in a small deep pan so that tomatoes fit without any extra space.
Pour 2 cups water over all.
Bake for half hour at 375°.
Baste the tomatoes with their juice and push them down in the pan since they have a tendency to rise.
Continue baking and basting, checking every 15 minutes. Tomatoes are done after there isn't any more juice for basting, about 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Cool.
Serve cold, never warm!

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Dice and cook potatoes.
Melt cheese and add mayonnaise, soup and milk.
Mix until well blended.
Drain potatoes.
Put in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Pour cheese over potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: popsicle mix
directions: Mix and stir well.
Store dry mix in 20 oz can with lid.

title: impossible pie
directions: Put all ingredients in blender and mix well.
Pour into a greased and floured 10-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until inserted knife comes out clean.

title: penny pincher punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid and freeze in a plastic milk jug.
Set Kool-Aid out of freezer about 1 hour before serving time.
Cut away plastic jug.
Place Kool-Aid in punch bowl.
Add ginger ale and stir until slushy.
Scoop in sherbet.

title: caramel candy
directions: Measure sugar into a heavy 2-quart saucepan.
Remove 2 tablespoons of the sugar and melt until amber in a small saucepan. Combine the milk and Karo with the 2 cups sugar.
Heat on medium. Add melted sugar.
Cook on medium heat until soft stage.
Remove from heat.
Add butter.
Cool slightly.
Beat on high speed until it holds its shape.
Add pecans.
Drop by spoonfuls on foil.

title: cucumber soup
directions: Simmer above 15 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Cool. Puree in electric blender.
Correct seasoning.
Can be served cold or hot.

title: rice and sausage
directions: Cook rice as you would normally (4 cups boiling water to 2 cups rice). When cooked, combine sausage, onion, bell pepper and celery in large skillet. Cook for 4 minutes. Add tomatoes, broth and seasonings. Cover and simmer 5 minutes. Pour cornstarch mixture into skillet; continue to cook for about 3 minutes and pour over rice in a casserole dish.

title: cold pasta salad
directions: Cook noodles and drain.
Rinse in cold water.
Drain liquids out of both olive jars and mushrooms.
Mix first 5 ingredients in large bowl.
Pour about 1/2 cup oil over mixture and stir.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Chill before serving.
If drys out overnight, add a little oil before serving.

title: sweet mix
directions: Preheat oven to 225°.
Mix Crispix, popcorn and peanuts and set aside.

title: yum-yum beans
directions: Fry sausage and crumble in pieces.
Mix sausage, onions and beans, then add soup, paste, mustard and sugar.
Can be done in crock-pot or casserole in oven.
Bake at 300° to 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: reese's peanut butter bars
directions: Mix together the finely crushed graham crackers and the powdered sugar.
Melt together the peanut butter and 1 1/2 sticks margarine.
Stir this into graham cracker mixture; press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt together the chocolate chips and 1/2 stick margarine.
Spread this over the mixture in pan; let harden at room temperature.
Cut into bars.

title: celery salted almonds
directions: Up to 1 week ahead:
In 13 x 9-inch baking pan, combine almonds, butter or margarine and celery salt.
Bake in 325° oven for 25 to 30 minutes until almonds are lightly browned, stirring occasionally.
Cool.
Store tightly covered.
Makes 2 cups.

title: apple pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: carrot-macaroni dish
directions: Saute ground beef and
onion in butter in skillet until brown. Add remaining ingredients	and
mix
well.
Pour
into greased casserole.	Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: low-fat cajun chicken
directions: Pound meat portions to 3/8 to 1/2 thick.
Sprinkle generously with seasoning.
Spray an iron skillet with Pam.
Brown pieces, turning frequently until juices are clear when pricked.
You may need to add a small amount of olive oil.

title: mixed vegetable salad
directions: Cook vegetables until tender.
Drain well.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour following dressing over vegetables and stir well.

title: warm potato salad
directions: Put potatoes and green onions into a large bowl.
Cook bacon in a large skillet over medium-low heat until crisp.
Remove to paper towel to drain.
Pour off all but 1 tablespoon drippings.
Add celery and bell pepper.
Cook over medium heat about 2 minutes until crisp-tender.
Add to potatoes.
Pour vinegar into skillet. Add salt and pepper.
Cook over medium heat until hot.
Pour over potato mixture.
Toss to mix well.
Crumble bacon over top.
Makes 4 servings.

title: scioto chapel bread dressing
directions: The night before, lay out bread slices to dry.
Preheat oven to 350°.
In the water, cook onions and celery with salt and pepper to taste until tender.
Tear dried bread into one-inch pieces and put in large bowl.
Pour water/onion/celery mixture and the beaten eggs into the bread pieces and mix well.
Pour in broth and mix again.
Mix in turkey or chicken pieces if desired. Spread in greased 9
x 13-inch baking pan and bake one hour, or until it begins to turn tan and pulls away from pan sides.
Serves 20.

title: baked chili
directions: Brown turkey.
Add beans, enchilada sauce, tomato sauce, Fritos and 1 cup cheese.
Put in an 8 x 11-inch pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with sour cream and 1/2 cup cheese. Bake 5 minutes.

title: artichoke heart salad
directions: Mix all together.
Put in refrigerator.
Before serving, mix 1 box mushrooms, cut in pieces, then serve.

title: the best chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix shortening, sugars, egg and vanilla thoroughly.
Measure flour and stir dry ingredients together. Blend into shortening mixture.
Mix in nuts and chocolate pieces. Drop rounded teaspoonfuls of dough about 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 8 minutes or until delicately browned (12 minutes for tablespoon and cookies).
Cool slightly before removing from baking sheet.

title: onion soup
directions: Cook onions and butter or drippings in covered saucepan, shaking pan often.
When onions are tender, add rice water or stock.
Boil 5 minutes.
Add seasonings and chopped parsley.

title: mandarin orange jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add 1 cup cold water and juice from oranges.
Stir in sherbet until melted.
Let stand until it starts to thicken, then stir in oranges.
Pour into mold (if desired) and chill.

title: blue crab stuffing
directions: Remove remaining shell and cartilage from crab meat.
Cook bacon until crisp; crumble and set aside.
Saute vegetables in bacon grease.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa together.
Add this mixture to beaten eggs; add milk, vanilla, vinegar and melted oleo.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush cookies.
Cream oleo, sugar and cream cheese.
Mix milk to pudding.
Combine cream mixture with pudding mixture.
Take mixture and fold in whip cream.
In bowl or flowerpot, layer cookies, then cream mixture until full.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions on bag only add celery and onions and cook until tender.
Add rice, soups, butter, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Now stir in jar of cheese whiz and stir well.
Pour in large greased baking dish and bake for 1 hour at 350 degrees.

title: poppy seed torte
directions: Place bowl and beater in freezer for 1/2 hour.

title: sweet potato and apple casserole
directions: Peel and slice sweet potatoes. Cook until about half done. In a large buttered baking dish, layer sweet potatoes, apples and marshmallows. Sprinkle with mixture of sugar, cinnamon, salt and pecans. Blend cornstarch and water in a small bowl and pour over layers. Dot with butter and bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: potato puff buns
directions: Scald 1
cup
of milk.
Add to it the butter, sugar and salt. Cool
to
lukewarm.
Add
1 package of yeast.
Blend in eggs, potatoes and flour.
Mix well.
Place in a greased bowl. Mixture will
be
slightly sticky.
Refrigerate until 2 hours before
it's needed.
Roll
out
to 1/2-inch thick on floured surface.
Cut and place on greased cookie sheet.
Let rise for 1 to 1 1/2 hours. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: jubilee chocolate cake
directions: Stir baking soda into buttermilk or sour milk until dissolved. Combine flour, 1 cup sugar, cocoa and salt in large mixer bowl. Add oil, buttermilk or sour milk mixture and egg yolks; beat until smooth.
Beat egg whites in small mixer bowl until foamy; gradually add 1/2 cup sugar, beating until very stiff peaks form. Gently fold egg whites into chocolate batter.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch oblong pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until cake springs back when lightly touched in center. Cool in pan on wire rack.

title: pumpkin muffins(from the american cancer society cookbook)
directions: In bowl, combine bran, flour, sugar, cinnamon, baking powder, baking soda, salt and raisins.
Toss to mix.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir just until combined.

title: cinnamon balls
directions: Cream butter; add sugar, flour and pecans.
Roll into small balls.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Roll in cinnamon and sugar mixture.
Makes 30.

title: biscuit mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together, cutting the shortening in well. Store in airtight container.
Add water to necessary amount for batch of biscuits.
Use as you would any biscuit mix.

title: low-fat shortcake
directions: Cut a piece of waxed paper to fit the bottom of a 9-inch square baking pan.
Spray Pam on paper and sides.

title: spiced oyster crackers
directions: Mix all ingredients together and spread on a cookie sheet. Bake in a preheated oven for 15 minutes at 250°.
Stir once halfway through baking time.
Remove from oven, allow to cool and store in an airtight container.

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: Slice eggplant in 1/4-inch slices.
Dip in slightly beaten egg and coat with breadcrumbs.
Brown both sides in skillet with oil, about 1 minute each side.
Place browned eggplant on paper towels to absorb oil.
In 9-inch round casserole dish, place a layer of eggplant, then spoon thin layer of sauce over and sprinkle Parmesan and Mozzarella over sauce.
Use a dash of chili powder on each slice.
Repeat layers and top with Mozzarella.
Microwave for approximately 5 to 10 minutes.
Serves 3 to 4 people.

title: spiced tea
directions: Combine and store.
Makes 20 cups.
To make 1 cup, mix 4 heaping teaspoonfuls of mix with 8 ounces boiling water.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Beat cream cheese until soft and fluffy.
Beat in sugar and peanut butter.
Slowly add milk and blend into mixture.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into crusts and freeze until firm.
Take out 10 minutes before serving.

title: chicken-rice soup
directions: Combine all ingredients except rice.
Bring to a boil.
Add rice.
Cover; let simmer until rice is tender.

title: spinach and cheese casserole
directions: Cut up cheese and butter in spinach. Mix in flour and eggs. mix together.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Place in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until browned.

title: cool banana split
directions: In saucepan, cook the vanilla pudding with milk according to pkg, until bubbly.
do not scorch.
Stir constantly.
When done put in glass bowl, let cool in ice.
Remove from refrigerator, set aside.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Cook pie ingredients over low heat until thick, stirring constantly.
Pour into baked or graham cracker shell.

title: pink party wedding punch
directions: Combine all ingredients except lemon slices in a large punch bowl.
Add ice. Garnish with lemon slices.
Makes 32 servings.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix everything; shape in loaf.
Pour catsup on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cut up cabbage, removing hard core.
Place cabbage in boiling water and parboil 5 minutes; drain.
Alternate layers of cabbage, soup and cheese in a greased casserole.
Season and sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Dot with butter and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: strawberry surprise
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix crushed pretzels, 1/3 cup sugar and margarine.
Press firmly into bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Bake 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Cook broccoli until tender.
Drain. Add onions, mushrooms, soup, mayonnaise, milk, bread crumbs and cheese to the broccoli.
Stir and blend all ingredients.
Season to taste.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: chicken, pasta and pine nuts
directions: Drain and chop tomatoes.
Reserve juices from tomatoes separately.
Add oil, onion, garlic, sun-dried tomatoes, pine nuts and chicken to a non-stick saut pan.
Cook 4 minutes over medium-high heat, until garlic starts to brown.
Add the brandy and stir well, cook for 2 minutes.
Add the chopped can tomatoes and basil.
Cook 2 more minutes while stirring well.
Add chicken stock, reserved juice form tomatoes and cream.
Bring to a boil and simmer 20 minutes.
While the sauce is simmering, prepare pasta.
Drain pasta and return to pot.
Pour sauce over pasta and stir until well combined over low heat.
Add cheese and serve. Serve 4-6 people, depending on portion size!

title: corn casserole
directions: Brown crumbs in butter.
Add corn, slightly beaten eggs, soup, onion and seasonings.
Pour into buttered casserole or ring mold. Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes or until firm and pulls away from side of pan.
If baked in ring mold, turn out on serving plate and serve with cooked Brussels sprouts in center.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Scald milk.
Cool to lukewarm in bowl.
Add yeast, sugar and 1 1/2 cups flour; mix well.
Let stand until bubbly.
Stir in salt, eggs, oil and remaining 1 1/2 cups flour to form soft dough. Knead on floured surface until smooth and elastic.
Place in greased bowl, turning to coat surface.
Let rise, covered, in warm place until doubled in bulk.
Roll 1/4-inch thick on floured surface.
Spread with 3 tablespoons softened butter.
Sprinkle with mixture of cinnamon and 1/2 cup brown sugar.
Roll as for jelly roll.
Slice 1 1/2 inches thick; place in greased baking dish.
Combine 1 tablespoon butter, 1/4 cup brown sugar and water in bowl.
Drizzle over rolls.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until golden brown.
Yield:
12 servings.

title: blueberry dessert
directions: Pour pie filling in 10 x 10-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle cake mix and nuts.
Cut margarine into 1/4-inch pats and cover the entire mix.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cool.
Then refrigerate for 1 hour.

title: rich sunshine cake
directions: Preheat oven to moderate temperature (350°).
Beat yolks, sugar, water and vanilla until thick and light.
Add flour.
Have egg whites at room temperature.
Beat egg whites and salt until foamy; add cream of tartar and continue beating until whites are stiff.
Fold whites into the yolk mixture.
Place batter in ungreased 10-inch tube pan; cover with brown paper.
Bake for 15 minutes; remove paper and bake 45 minutes longer.
Invert pan until cake is cool.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all but last 2 ingredients together and pour into large buttered casserole dish.
Top with cornflakes mixed with margarine.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: pork loin roast
directions: Place roast on a rack in a shallow roasting pan. Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours. In a skillet, saute the onion, celery and garlic in oil until tender. Stir in the remaining ingredients. Spoon 1 cup sauce over roast. Bake 45 to 55 minutes longer or until a meat thermometer reads 160°. Let stand for 10 to 25 minutes before slicing. Serve with the remaining sauce. Yield: 8 servings.

title: crisp crusted baked chicken
directions: Wash chicken pieces and pat dry.
Set aside.
Beat egg and milk in a bowl.
In another bowl, mix potato flakes, garlic powder and Parmesan cheese.
Roll chicken first in egg mix, then in the potato flakes mixture.
Melt butter in shallow baking pan.
Roll coated chicken pieces in the butter and place them skin side up in the pan.
Bake at 400° for 45 to 50 minutes, or until juice from thighs runs clear when pierced with a fork.
Transfer to serving platter.
Garnish with celery leaves and celery slices and serve.

title: cheese and broccoli dip
directions: Heat cheese until melted.
Add the cooked broccoli and sausage.
Mix by hand until well blended.

title: lemon bars
directions: Sift together flour and powdered sugar.
Cut in butter until mixture clings.
Press in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until light brown.

title: potato donuts
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, oleo and potatoes.
Add milk.
Add flour and baking powder.
Mix until firm dough (may need more flour).
Let set for 10 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream the butters.
Beat in sugars. Add other ingredients. Roll into small balls. Smash with fork dipped in flour.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned on bottom, about 7 to 8 minutes.

title: cherry surprise balls
directions: Beat butter at medium speed with an electric mixer until creamy; gradually add powdered sugar, beating well.
Gradually add flour, beating until blended.
Stir in vanilla and pecans.
Cover and chill 1 hour.
Shape dough around each cherry half to form a 3/4-inch ball.
Place balls 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar while warm.
Cool on wire racks.
Yield:
28 cookies.

title: ann bond's baked beans
directions: Brown ground meat.
Cook bacon.
Combine ingredients in casserole dish.
Cook only 1 hour at 350°.

title: macaroni casserole
directions: Cook macaroni. Combine ingredients (except shredded cheese). Put in dish. Top with shredded cheese. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Sift together cornbread mix, baking powder and salt.
Add cheese, onion, peppers, corn oil and sweet milk.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Cook at 350° until nice and brown.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and cinnamon; set aside.
Separate egg white from egg yolk and set mixer to medium speed.
Beat egg white, adding sugar 1/2 cup at a time until foamy, then add the egg yolk and oil until blended.
Next, add flour mixture and mix until smooth, then add carrots, pineapple and pecans.
Mix at low speed until well mixed.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until tester comes out clean.

title: sweet and sour dressing
directions: Mix and shake well.

title: sweet potato muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Mix together wet ingredients.
Barely mix the 2 together.
Pour into greased muffin tins and bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Yield: 2 dozen.

title: beef for sandwiches
directions: Put beef roast in roaster; cover with water.
Bake until tender.
Pour off broth and refrigerate until grease separates. Throw away grease.
As roast cools, shred with a fork, disposing of any fat or bone.
(This may be done 2 or 3 days ahead.)
To shredded beef, add clear broth, mushroom soup and dry onion soup mix and mix well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or a little longer (I use a crock-pot).

title: catnip tea
directions: Boil leaves and steep approximately 1 minute.
Add sugar. Stir and serve hot.
Good for a sleeping aid.

title: honey baked chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place breasts in baking pan.
Combine all other ingredients for sauce.
Pour sauce over chicken.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix with water as needed.
Drop by spoonful into hot oil until browned as desired.

title: breaded pork chops
directions: Mix eggs & milk together. Dip pork chops in egg mixture and then coat with cracker crumbs. Put oil in skillet. Brown chops on both sides. Place on foil lined cookie sheet and Bake at 350° for 40 - 45 minutes.

title: date nut balls
directions: Cook ingredients over low heat, stirring constantly, for 10 minutes or until thick.
Remove from heat and add 1 teaspoon vanilla and 3 cups of Rice Krispies.
Roll into bite size balls and roll in coconut.

title: amish dressing
directions: In a large bowl, put bread cubes, potatoes, celery, parsley and carrots.
Add eggs, well beaten.
Then add 1 quart liquid which may be meat stock, milk, cream or condensed milk.
Finally, add 1 pint or more cooked, diced chicken and toss lightly.

title: pasta with beans soup
directions: Brown meat in large Dutch oven or pan.
Add onion, tomatoes, beans and broth; simmer 15 minutes.
Just before serving, add macaroni, pepper, oregano and basil.
Serve immediately sprinkled with grated Romano or Parmesan cheese.
I take the fat off the broth that makes it almost fat-free.
Wayne loves this soup.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream butter, margarine and cream cheese until smooth.
Add sugar and cream until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in flour and salt.
Add vanilla.
Pour batter into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan. Place cake in cold oven and bake 2 hours at 300°.

title: stuffed jalapenos
directions: Heat a little at a time.
Turn off heat if mixture begins to cook.
Saute onions and celery in the butter.
Add chicken; stir to break chicken up into pieces.
Add 1 cup bread crumbs.
Stir until moist.
Add 2 eggs and mix well.
Add 1/2 cup bread crumbs until mixture begins to stick together forming a ball.
May need to add a few more bread crumbs if mixture is gooey.
Needs to be more dry than wet.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Pack mixture into jalapenos.
Should be enough to overstuff.

title: quick energy pick-ups
directions: Crush graham crackers with your fingers onto sheet of waxed paper.
Mix remaining ingredients thoroughly in bowl.
Shape teaspoonful of the mixture into 1 inch balls.
Roll balls in the graham cracker crumbs until coated.
Arrange the coated balls on ungreased cookie sheet and refrigerate about 20 minutes.
Makes 30 pickups.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Shred lettuce coarsely with knife.
Fill serving dish 1/2 full of lettuce.
In layers sprinkle the green pepper, onion and celery. Add peas.
Spread Miracle Whip and sour cream mixed together by hand over the peas.
Sprinkle sugar over this.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese, then bacon over top.
Cover tightly with Saran Wrap and refrigerate overnight.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: bean casserole
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Put in bacon grease the cut up onion and cook.
Add vinegar, salt, brown sugar and mustard, cover 20 minutes.
Combine all beans in casserole and pour mixture over it. Sprinkle bacon on top.
Cook 1 hour at 350°.

title: kisersmaron(breakfast dish)
directions: Stir milk and flour together until smooth.
Add yolks, sugar, butter and egg whites to mixture.
Then add in the raisins.
Add butter to skillet and cook as you would scrambled eggs.
Serve with powdered sugar or a syrup of your choice.

title: cappuccino mix
directions: In a medium-sized glass jar, combine the nondairy creamer, chocolate drink mix, instant coffee, sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg; mix well.

title: orange glazed chicken
directions: Bake chicken in butter until brown, about 30 minutes, at 350°. Add orange juice, honey, salt, mustard and paprika; mix all together.
Brush over chicken.
Bake another 10 to 15 minutes.

title: hot italian sausage over penne
directions: Put 2 Tbsp. olive oil in saucepan and add garlic and shallots. Brown and add skinless sausage, brown and drain oil.
Add paprika & chicken broth.
Let simmer until you have half of liquid left.
Add cream and simmer until you have half of liquid left.
Add remaining spices, simmer 10 minutes.
Cook penne until done, drain and stir in mixture.
Top with tomato, green onion and cheese.

title: summer corn salad
directions: Run hot water over frozen corn to thaw. Drain well. Add all finely chopped vegetables to corn, mix well.
Add sugar, vinegar, salt, pepper and celery seed.
Mix to taste. Serve very cold. Yields 8 to 10 servings.
Great with spaghetti.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Cook and drain potatoes.
Stir in butter.
Spoon half of the potatoes in casserole.
Top with half of the bacon and half of the cheese, then repeat.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: coconut marbles
directions: In large bowl, let margarine soften.
Then add sugar and coconut.
Mix with hands.
If not stiff enough to roll into marble-size balls, mix more sugar and coconut until stiff enough to hold shape.
Lay on wax paper on flat pan and stick with toothpicks.
Freeze until you melt morsels and wax in top of double boiler.
Remove balls from freezer and dip with toothpicks in chocolate mixture.
Lay back on wax paper until cool.
Enjoy eating and let the pounds take care of themselves.

title: bread pudding
directions: Melt butter.
Combine with eggs, salt, vanilla, sugar and milk. Stir until sugar is dissolved; pour over bread cubes.
Pour into a 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Serve cold with whipped cream or warm with sauce.
If bread is dry, heat in the milk slightly before adding the other ingredients.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: homemade old fashion white bread
directions: Set 2 2/3 cups of water aside.
Empty yeast, with a dash of sugar to dissolve yeast, into 2 2/3 cups water, after mixing all other ingredients, then add water slowly to make dough.
Be sure and knead dough very well.
The more you knead, the more the bread will rise, approximately 5 minutes.
Let rise 1 hour.
Let rise 1 hour after placing them in pans.
Bake.

title: cheese wheels
directions: Mix grated cheese and margarine.
Add flour; mix well.
Add cereal and mix well.
Shape in small marble size balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Flatten each ball with fork and bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: cheesy broccoli casserole
directions: Grease lightly a square baking dish, 8 x 8 x 2-inches.
Spread broccoli in dish. Beat sour cream, cottage cheese, Bisquick, margarine and eggs well with hand beater 1 minute.
Pour over broccoli.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let cool 5 minutes before serving.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: great grahams
directions: Spread peanut butter on graham crackers.
Arrange marshmallows on top.
Broil for a few minutes until marshmallows are golden brown.
Then arrange raisins on top.

title: christmas wreath
directions: Combine marshmallows, butter, vanilla and coloring in top of double boiler and heat until melted.
Stir in cornflakes.
Drop into waxed paper and shape into wreath.
Decorate with red cherries or candy.

title: pineapple pretzel salad
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Place crushed pretzels in the bottom of a 9 x 13 inch baking dish.
Pour melted butter carefully over top.
Bake in preheated oven ten minutes.
Cream together cream cheese and sugar.
Fold in whipped topping.
Spread over cooled crust.
Combine pineapple and pudding mix.
Spread over whipped topping layer.
Chill until serving.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients; pour over meat as desired.

title: corn sticks
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Add egg, milk and oil; stir until batter is smooth.
Coat a cast-iron corn stick pan with cooking spray.
Heat in a 425° oven for 3 minutes or until hot.
Remove pan from oven.
Spoon batter into pan, filling 2/3 full.
Bake at 425° for 10 to 12 minutes or until bread is lightly browned.
Yield:
1 dozen (81 calories per corn stick).

title: mrs. g.'s chicken rotel
directions: Season and cook chicken so you will have 1 1/2 quarts broth. Strain broth and cook vermicelli in it.
Add cheese and melt.
Add tomatoes, Worcestershire, drained peas and mushrooms.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add deboned chicken, cut up in bite-sized pieces, and put into casserole.
Bake in moderate oven (300°) for 20 minutes.
Serves 10 to 12.
(Makes 2 large casseroles.)
May be frozen and cooked later.

title: baked parmesan cottage potatoes
directions: In a greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan, arrange potatoes and onions in layers.
Melt oleo and drizzle over potatoes and onions. Combine garlic powder and Parmesan cheese and pepper together and sprinkle over potatoes.
Bake in 450° oven for 25 minutes.

title: prune cake
directions: Beat all ingredients together well.
Bake at 350°
about 45 minutes.

title: eggplant and shrimp casserole
directions: Soak bread in milk until soft enough to make mush.
Add eggs and eggplant; mix well.
Saute onions, bell pepper and garlic in olive oil until clear.
Add shrimp and crab meat; stir until shrimp are pink.
Mix with eggplant mixture.
Add salt and pepper.
Pour into casserole dish and bake 45 minutes at 400°.

title: refrigerator cake
directions: Heat first three ingredients until dissolved.
Blend in chunky peanut butter.
Place corn flakes in large bowl, pour syrup mixture over flakes and mix together.
Roll into balls and place on cookie sheet lined with wax paper.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.

title: breakfast bread pudding
directions: Remove and discard crusts from bread; cut bread into cubes. Toss lightly with cream cheese cubes.
Place in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
In a large mixing bowl, beat eggs.
Add milk, syrup and salt.
Mix well.
Pour over bread mixture.
Cover and refrigerate 8 hours or overnight.

title: baked squash
directions: Also make ahead and freeze.

title: hot cheese surprise appetizers
directions: Grind cheese, bacon, onion and garlic together.
Combine with mayonnaise and mustard until well mixed.
Spread generously on bread.
Place on cookie sheet and broil 6 to 7 minutes about 5 inches from heat.

title: fudge ecstasies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In heavy medium saucepan, heat 1/2 of the chocolate chips, the unsweetened chocolate and margarine or butter until melted, stirring occasionally.
Add eggs, sugar, flour, vanilla and baking powder.
Beat until thoroughly combined. Stir in remaining chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until edges are firm and surfaces are dull and cracked.
Cool cookies on wire rack.
Makes about 36.

title: homemade rolls
directions: Stainless steel bowl is best.
Pour water over yeast in bowl. In saucepan, warm milk.
Add sugar and salt; stir until dissolved. Pour over yeast mixture.
Add enough flour to beat into smooth dough.
Add melted shortening; beat until mixed, then add enough flour to make stiff dough.
Knead real well.
Put back into bowl, cover and let rise until double.
Make out; put in deep pan (skillet) with melted shortening and margarine in it.
Pinch dough, don't cut dough.
Bake at 400° until brown.

title: sausage zucchini bake
directions: Brown sausage, breaking into small pieces.
Drain.
Toss with 1 tablespoon of flour.
Spread on the bottom of a baking dish.

title: green beans and sour cream
directions: Layer beans, onion rings, mushrooms and sour cream in greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle with cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: pizza hot dish
directions: Saute meat, green peppers, onions, spices and tomato sauce. Simmer 15 minutes.
Place noodles in 9 x 13-inch nonstick pan. Pour meat sauce over.
Top with cheese, then mushrooms.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Let set before cutting.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chicken continental
directions: Melt margarine.
Saute	onions and chicken until onions are soft.
Add soup and
broth;
stir well.
Add rice and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cheesecake
directions: Mix well crushed
graham
crackers,
4 tablespoons powdered sugar and melted oleo.
Pat
in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 6 to 8 minutes in 350° oven.
Cool.
Beat together cream cheese, Cool Whip and powdered
sugar.
Put
on
cooled graham cracker crust. Spread pie filling on
top.
Let
set at least 1 hour. Serves 18 to 20 persons.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Mix the water, jello, pineapple and pie filling.
Congeal.

title: lemon squares
directions: Cream together the first 4 ingredients; pat in pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Beat the eggs until light in color.
Add the sugar; whip.
Add the flour and lemon juice.
Pour over crust; bake another 20 to 25 minutes. Cool 10 minutes; sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: pizza
directions: Make it into a circle.
Throw it in the air.
Put on the red stuff and cheese.
Bake it really hot.

title: anytime cheese ball
directions: Mix well, roll ball in extra nuts.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Mix all together and serve with lettuce for a light lunch; add crackers and fruit plate.
Serves 2. Has 250 calories, 10 fat grams; food exchanges equal 2 protein, 1 bread, 3 fats.
